rformance of the assigned team through monitoring the KPIs achievement, following up any obstacles, provide performance feedback and conversations, coaching…etc. to ensure the achievement of the set objectives. Manage, monitor, and develop the assigned staff under this Contract Arrange for the induction and training of all new staff Liaise regularly with supervisors to ensure a smooth run of the operation\nCompetencies: \nCore Competencies: Critical thinking Problem-solving Planning and Organizing Time Management Product knowledge Data analysis Negotiating skills Achieving personal work goals & objectives Relationship-building & networking Entrepreneurial & commercial thinking Deciding & initiating action Results-driven and meeting customer expectations\nJob Requirements: \nEducation Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering/Logistics and Supply Chain/business administration Computer Skills MS Office Suite Languages Arabic English\nNote: you will be required to attach the following:\n1. Resume / CV\n',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Khalid Ali Alturki & Sons Company (Alturki Holding)',NULL),('Senior Quality Auditor','Egypt','Cairo','','Job Summary The Senior Quality Auditor is a senior member of the corporate Quality team . He supports the development and enforcement of corporate quality policies, procedures, tools and templates across K&A in coordination with regional and local quality teams. He participates in setting quality certification targets across K&A\'s offices and jointly works with regional and local teams for the development and implementation of action plans to achieve these certification targets. The jobholder develops quality audit plans across the organization, and tracks the execution of quality audits across K&A offices as per the audit plans to ensure the corporate-wide compliance with quality policies, procedures, tools and templates. He conducts QA activities on design deliverables prepared in the Lebanon design center to ensure the adherence of engineering design works to the organization\'s quality standards. The jobholder supports the delivery of quality training and awareness sessions across the organization in coordination with regional teams to promote an overarching quality culture. Key Responsibilities Support the development of corporate quality policies and procedures and provide guidelines for quality procedures in design Departments, Regions and Geographies Maintain the corporate Quality Management System (QMS) and investigate and recommend changes to the QMS, as needed Support the Director / Senior Manager - Quality with the definition of quality certification targets (e.g. ISO 9001) for all K&A offices Develop action plans for the implementation of quality certification targets across K&A offices, in coordination with regional / local Quality Units Conduct quality assurance activities on design deliverables developed in the Lebanon design center and check compliance of design deliverables to K&A\'s quality policies, procedures and standards Develop the annual quality audit program across K&A Regions and Geographies, in coordination with the Director / Senior Manager - Quality Develop audit standards, checklists, standard audit findings reports and corrective action report templates to be consistently used by Quality Auditors across K&A Regions Participate in executing periodic quality audits in the headquarter and the Levant & Qatar Region to check the compliance of K&A departments with quality policies and procedures, including the distribution of audit requirements lists, circulation of audit schedules to relevant stakeholders and the execution of quality audits on offices, design Departments and supervision sites Identify quality non-conformance issues, summarize findings in periodic quality audit reports and recommend corrective action plans and reports for addressing identified quality non-conformances in the headquarter and Levant & Qatar Region Support Quality Auditors with the review and consolidation of quality audit finding reports from regional Quality Units into a consolidated K&A quality audit findings report Prepare periodic quality performance report, highlighting key quality issues across the organization and recommending corporate quality initiatives to address non-conformance patterns across K&A Support the development and maintenance of a corporate database of quality audits and findings in coordination with regional and local Quality Units Implement corporate policies and procedures Qualification, Technical Skills and Competencies Bachelor\'s Degree in Engineering or Business Administration ISO 9001 Foundation / Internal Auditor Knowledge of the Architecture, Engineering and Planning Industry Knowledge of Quality certification, compliance requirements and audit programs Understanding of local quality regulations in the Middle East is an advantage Strong attention to detail Good communication skills Good organizational skills Strong analytical capabilities Good interpersonal and leadership skills Ability to elicit cooperation from a variety of stakeholders, including senior management Proficiency in spoken and written English & Arabic Specific Experience Required to Execute this Role10+ years of experience in a quality management function, ',NULL,'2023-10-11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Khatib & Alami',NULL),('Sales Manager (software)','Egypt','Dakahlia','','Initiate sales and attain the company’s sales objectives. Sustain and broaden relationships with new and existing clients. Initiate and outsource projects for the company’s software products and custom solutions. Manage the Sales team Design and implement a strategic business plan that expands company’s customer base and ensure its strong presence Build and promote strong, long-lasting customer relationships by partnering with them and understanding their needs Conduct comprehensive market research to understand customer needs, industry trends, and competitors. Develop customized sales proposals and negotiate contracts to close deals with clients. Developing a business plan covering sales, revenue, and expense controls, meeting agreed targets Manage lead generation process','Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, or related field. Proven work experience as a sales Manager in the software industry is a MUSTMust have worked with the Gulf Area Clients. Minimum 5 years of experience as a sales Manager. Outstanding verbal and written communication skills. Very good English Exceptional presentation and negotiation skills Customer service oriented Problem-solving skills Ability to work within a teamjob location (Mansoura ) ','2023-10-08',12,0,4,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Manager ',NULL,'Kian Alraqmih',NULL),('SEO Specialist','Egypt','Dakahlia','Mansoura','* Develop and execute SEO strategies to improve website visibility and organic traffic* Conduct keyword research and identify opportunities to optimize website content and structure* Implement on-page optimization techniques such as title tag optimization, meta description optimization, and image optimization* Build backlinks from high-quality websites to improve website authority','* 2+ years of experience in SEO, with a focus on e-commerce, Word Press, and app store optimization* Strong understanding of search engine algorithms and ranking factors* Experience with keyword research, on-page optimization, link building, and technical SEO* Experience with SEO tools and analytics platforms such as Google Analytics, Google Search Console, and SEMrush* Experience working with e-commerce platforms such as Woo Commerce and Shopify* Experience with app store optimization (ASO)* Excellent written and verbal communication skills* Ability to work independently and as part of a team ','2023-10-11',3,0,2,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Kian Alraqmih',NULL),('Software Marketing Manager','Egypt','Dakahlia','','Evaluating and optimizing marketing 