Z Software, Microsoft Office, Primavera and/or Microsoft Projects. * Knowledgeable of NFPA codes and international design standards.* Bilingual Arabic/English speaking, reading, and writing.* Non-Saudi engineers must obtain minimum of five (5) years of related experience. * Saudi Council of Engineers license is required. ',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('ASSISTANT CONSULTANT NEUROSURGERY','Saudi Arabia','Medina','','Summary Assists in providing medical care in the field of Neurosurgery and supervises interns and residents, in accordance with current medial staff bylaws, rules and regulations and the Hospital\'s policies and procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Clinical Responsibilities-Assists the Consultants in providing required patient care and management in the field of Neurosurgery, in accordance with standards of medical care laid down by KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.).-Studies and performs assessment, examination and the compilation of a case history and assists in the diagnosis and management of the patient in accordance with criteria listed in diagnostic manuals such as the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual. -Registers detailed medical history, conducts a thorough physical examination and creates a plan for patient management and follows-up for discussion with the Consultant. Subsequently, records the consultant’s orders, progress notes and other required documents for outpatients. -Provides on-call coverage for their specialty on a rotational basis during evenings, nights, weekends and public holidays. -Prepares for and participates in consultant and specialist ward rounds as per policy. Documents findings in medical records. -Follows up on investigation results for outpatients and modifies treatment accordingly. -Attends specialty clinics, outpatient clinics, and shares on on-call schedule as per requirements. -Performs any other clinical responsibilities, as assigned. *Academic Responsibilities-Provides orientation, bedside training and supervision of interns, residents and fellows as assigned. -Keeps abreast of all the latest techniques and developments, especially in area of specialization. Implements them on a selective basis to improve technical standards. -Participates in the educational activities and training programs of the Department.-Participates in national and international medical conferences.*Research Responsibilities-Participates in clinical, basic and translational research projects and published papers in accordance with Research Advisory Council Policy in order to advance knowledge, improve the quality of post graduate education and contribute to the national and international recognition of KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.).*Administrative Responsibilities-Undertakes the administrative duties assigned by the Section Head or Chairman of the Department.-Participates in all mandatory Departmental activities and serves on Departmental and Hospital committees, as required.-Assists the Department in the development and implementation of techniques and practices that help maximize the utilization of all resources within the Department and across the KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.).-Abides by the current hospital and medical stall bylaws, all relevant rules, regulations and policies and keeps updated of any changes that might occur. Education Refer to the approved Credentialing guidelines. Experience Required Two (2) years of training in specialty or subspecialty plus post-training experience is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('ASSISTANT CONSULTANT, NEONATOLOGY','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Assists in providing medical care in the field of Neonatology and supervises interns and residents, in accordance with current medical staff bylaws, rules and regulations and the hospital\'s policies and procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties Clinical Responsibilities1. Assists the Consultant in providing required patient care and management in the field of Neonatology in accordance with standards of medical care laid down by KFSH&RC.2. Ensures appropriate patient preparation for procedures/ surgery and assists the consultant in performing procedures/ surgery or performs the procedures/surgery independently, as indicated in the signed Clinical Privilege Form. 3. Provides patient care management (diagnosis, treatment and prevention) on issues relate to the fetus prenatally and issues related to new-borns till the time of their discharge. Provides out-patient follow-up, as required. 4. Provides on-call coverage for Neonatology on a rotational basis during evenings, nights, weekends and public holidays. 5. Prepares for and participates in consultant and specialist ward rounds as per policy. Documents findings in medical records.6. Follows-up on investigation result for inpatients and outpatients and assists Consultants in modifying treatment accordingly. 7. Registers detailed medical history, conducts a thorough physical examination and creates a plan for patient management and follow-up for discussion with the Consultant. 8. Records Consultant\'s orders, progress notes and other required documents for inpatient and outpatients. Academic Responsibilities 1. Provides orientation, bedside training and supervision to residents and fellows as assigned.2. Keeps abreast with all the latest techniques and developments, especially in field of Neonatology, following and implementing them on a selective basis to improve technical standards.3. Actively participates in the educational activities and training programs of the department. Research Responsibilities1. Actively participates in clinical, basic and translational research projects and publishes papers in accordance with Research Advisory Council Policy in order to advance knowledge, improve the quality of post graduate education and contribute to the national and international recognition of KFSH&RC. Administrative Responsibilities1. Undertakes the administrative duties assigned by Section Head  or Chairman of Paediatrics.2. Participates in all mandatory departmental activities along with the Paediatric activities, i.e. Staff meeting, Core Lectures, Research Forum, etc., and serves on departmental an Hospital Committees, as required. 3. Actively contributes to the Division\'s and/or the department\'s documentation of patient care processes and outcomes in the medical charts. 4. Assists the department in the development and implementation of techniques and practices that help maximize the utilization of all resources within the department and across the Hospital.5. Abides by the current hospital and medical staff bylaws, all relevant rules, regulations and policies and keeps updated of any changes that might occur.6. Participates in self and others\' education, training and development as applicable. 7. Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures. Education Refer to the approved Credentialing guidelines. Experience Required Two (2) years of training in specialty or subspecialty plus post-training experience is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('ASSISTANT INVESTIGATOR','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Makes inquiries and investigations into all matters,criminal or non-criminal, and acts as bilingual aide in Arabic/English in theinterpretation and translation of all matters assigned to Investigations, asassigned by Investigator. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Makes inquiries and primary investigations into all complaints, incidents or crimes that occur on Hospital property and submits reports in accordance with established procedure, including written reports, verbal summaries and written information inputs.2. Visits scenes of all crimes, and emergencies, and assists in scene searches or preserving scenes where necessary. 3. Carries out scene searches or preserves scenes when necessary. Collects, marks, and preserves all items of evidence. Conducts interviews and interrogations and records statements. Performs surveillance duties when necessary. Maintains records of current investigations. Complies case file investigation diary on all investigations.4. Assists in investigations of all traffic accidents. Assists to compile traffic case files, which will include traffic accident reports, scale scene sketches and accident scene photograph.5. Carries out liaison with police officers and other government officials. Assists in obtaining written \'police reports\' and \'police release\' documents for vehicle involved in accidents. Facilitates collection and production or drivers and witnesses to and from police officers and acts as Arabic/English translator. 6. Carries out any other Security duties responsibilities as directed. Education Bachelor’s or Associate Degree/ Diploma in Law or other related discipline is required. Experience Required No experience required with Bachelor’s Degree (On- the-Job Training), or one (1) year of related experience with Associate Degree/ Diploma is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)* Saudi Male National Only.* Able to read/write English and Arabic is required.',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('ASSOCIATE CONSULTANT, INTENSIVIST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Reponsible for provision of medical care in the field of Intensivist, in accordance with current medical staff bylaws, rules and regulations and the hospital’s policies and procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties*Clinical Responsibilities-Participates in the duties necessary for the efficient handling and reporting of all examinations.-Establishes and maintains diagnostic services in assigned Intensivist in coordination with Section Head.-Communicates with clinicians and participates in their rounds and conferences.-Assists the patient’s primary physician regarding test utilization and interpretation.-Ensures high levels of employee and patient safety.-Verifies all quality control and proficiency testing and prepare for laboratory inspection.-Monitors performance standards including quality assurance, quality control and troubleshooting.-Provides optimal support of patient care.*Academic Responsibilities-Directs and advices junior physicians on patient management, especially in the area of Intensivist.-Guides and actively assists in the training and teaching of Fellows and Residents in area of Intensivist.-Keeps abreast with all the latest techniques and developments, especially in area of specialization, following and implementing them on a selective basis to improve technical standards.-Actively participates in the educational activities and training programs of the department.-Participates in national and international medical conferences.*Research Responsibilities-Participates in clinical or basic and educational research projects in area of specialization in order to advance knowledge, improve the quality of post graduate education and contribute to the national and international recognition of KFSH&RC.*Administrative Responsibilities-Undertakes the administrative duties associated with the running of the department. -Participates in departmental meetings and serves on hospital committees, as required.-Assists the department in the development and implementation of techniques and practices that help maximize the utilization of all resources within the department and across the hospital.-Abides by the current hospital and medical staff bylaws, all relevant rules, regulations and policies and keeps updated of any changes that might occur.-Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures.-Participates in self and others education, training and development, as applicable.-Performs any other related duties as assigned. Education Graduation from an accredited medical school acceptable to KFSH&RC (Gen. Org). Experience Required Five (5) years of training in specialty and subspecialty plus post-training experience required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('ASSOCIATE CONSULTANT, INTERNAL MEDICINE','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for provision of medical care in the field of Internal Medicine, in accordance with current medical staff bylaws, rules and regulations and the hospital’s policies and procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties Clinical Responsibilities1. Participates in the gross and microscopic processing of surgical specimens, cytological and other related duties necessary for the efficient handling and reporting of all examinations as assigned.2. Establishes and maintains diagnostic services in Internal Medicine in coordination with Section Head.3. Communicates with clinicians and participates in their rounds and conferences.4. Assists the patient’s primary physician regarding test utilization and interpretation.5. Ensures high levels of employee and patient safety.6. Verifies all quality control and proficiency testing and prepare for laboratory inspection.7. Monitors performance standards including quality assurance, quality control and troubleshooting.8. Provides optimal support of patient care. Academic Responsibilities1. Directs and advices junior physicians on patient management, especially in the area of specialization.2. Guides and actively assists in the training and teaching of Fellows and Residents in the area of specialization.3. Keeps abreast with all the latest techniques and developments, especially in the area of specialization, following and implementing them on a selective basis to improve technical standards.4. Participates in the educational activities and training programs of the department as assigned.5. Participates in national and international medical conferences as assigned. Research Responsibilities1. Participates in clinical or basic and educational research projects in the area of specialization in order to advance knowledge, improve the quality of post graduate education and contribute to the national and international recognition of KFSH&RC. Administrative Responsibilities1. Undertakes the administrative duties associated with the running of the department.2. Participates in departmental meetings and serves on hospital committees, as required.3. Assists the department in the development and implementation of techniques and practices that help maximize the utilization of all resources within the department and across the hospital.4. Abides by the current hospital and medical staff bylaws, all relevant rules, regulations and policies and keeps updated of any changes that might occur.5. Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures.6. Participates in self and others education, training and development, as applicable. Education Graduation from accredited medical school acceptable to KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.). Experience Required Five (5) years of training in specialty and subspecialty plus post-training experience required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('CLINICAL ENGINEER II','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Provides for the technical support of medical, diagnostic, therapeutic and analytical devices and systems, utilized for applied patient healthcare and healthcare research. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Provides for the demand and scheduled preventative maintenance of assigned medical and research equipment, Follows manufacturers\' guidelines for this scheduled preventative maintenance.2. Is competent in the basic operation and application of assigned medical and research equipment.3. Reviews schematic drawings, manufacturer\'s instructions and manuals or obtains verbal instructions to diagnose technical problems and facilitates repair and preventative maintenance utilizing this information.4. Utilizes all required testing instrumental and hand tools required to facilitate repair and preventative maintenance of assigned medical equipment.5. Provides for user education and instruction, as required.6. Trains and guides Clinical Engineering Technicians, SCDP participants, Student Interns and other Clinical Engineering staff on the technical support of medical technology, as required.7. Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures.8. Participates in self and others\' education, training & development, as applicable.9. Performs other related duties as assigned. Education Bachelor’s Degree in Biomedical Technology, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required Two (2) years of related experience with Bachelor’s is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Valid license from country of origin. ',NULL,'2023-10-11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('COMMUNICATIONS TECHNICIAN II','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for supporting all billing activities related to telecommunications. Ensures that the telecommunication resources are being well utilized. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Assists in evaluating products or services usage and produce monthly bills.2. Captures call detail records and perform usage tracking.3. Performs telecom audit to ensure that telecommunications usage is optimized and that misuse or abuse is identified.4. Supports legal and regulatory requirements as needed.5. Supports the Analysis of communications infrastructure, administration and costs.6. Assists in the Production of billing reports at the appropriate level (e.g., user, department).7. Liaises with Human Resources as part of the employee clearance process.8. Follows prescribed system safety and security procedures of computing environment.9. Participates in self & others\' education, training and development, as applicable.10. Follows all hospital related policies and procedures.11. Performs other related duties as assigned. Education Diploma in Computer Science or related discipline, or High School Education is required. Experience Required No experience required with Diploma, or one (1) year of related experience with High School Education is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGIST II','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for installing, maintaining, and repairing networks, mobile devices, telephones, Nurse Call System end points, radios and pagers across KSFH&RC. In doing so, this job minimizes the timespans of service interruptions, increases KSFH&RC productivity, and creates a more satisfied user community in the long run. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Installs, repairs, and maintains networks, mobile devices, telephones, Nurse Call System end points, radios and pagers to meet end-user needs.2. Uses schematic drawings, verbal instructions, or manufacturer\'s instructions and manuals to diagnose problems with equipment and make repairs. 3. Provides desktop implementation, schedule coordination, move, add, change and disposal services when requested.4. Provides Level 2 network field support for devices and communication devices. 5. Apply patches to configuration items as deemed necessary by the different infrastructure teams and the Information Security and Disaster Recovery Department.6. Provides onsite technical support during corporate events.7. Administers and implement standard and minor changes as indicated in the change classification matrix.8. Follows prescribed system safety and security procedures of computing environment.9. Participates in self & others\' education, training and development, as applicable.10. Follows all hospital related policies and procedures.11. Performs other related duties as assigned. Education Bachelor’s Degree or Diploma in Computer Science or related discipline is required. Experience Required One (1) year of related experience with Bachelor’s Degree, or three (3) years of related experience with Diploma is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('COMPUTED TOMOGRAPHY TECHNOLOGIST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Performs imaging procedures utilizing computerized tomography imaging scanners. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Reviews exam orders/requisitions. Reviews corresponding protocol and asks questions of superior (s) and prepares for exams as needed.2. Explains procedures to patients. Prepares equipment,supplies, contrast media, and medications.3. Positions patient and attaches or adjusts immobilizing and shielding devices to ensure precise patient position, patient comfort, and to minimize patient exposure to x-rays.4. Adjusts and operates computerized tomographic imaging equipment to scan designated anatomical areas.5. Sets computer controls and laser camera to produce proper images. Assists in injection of contrast media.6. Monitors patient condition during and after scan to ensure patient safety and comfort.7. Retrieves information from computer and processes information in the proper format for interpretation by the radiologist and/or archiving.8. Evaluates completed tests for quality and completeness. Documents all studies performed.9. Records all required information. Labels films in sequence. Notes all pertinent data required by Radiologists for medical diagnosis. Consults the radiologist as needed.10. Performs routine equipment maintenance. Informs supervisor of equipment malfunction or need for repair and documents same. Performs quality control studies on equipment.11. Cleans equipment and room and restores all equipment and supplies for subsequent use.12. Participates in staff meetings, in-services, and/or continuing education.13. Comply with the section policies, procedures and protocols. Follow the section quality improvement program in accordance with CBAHI, JCI, SFDA and other accreditation agencies standards.13. Participates in self’s and others’ education, training, and development, as applicable.14. Comply with the Radiation Safety Rules and Regulations of the Hospital in accordance with KACST and K. A. CARE and other National or International Regulatory bodies.15. Apply ALARA principle Role within the section practice for all procedures. Education Bachelor’s Degree from an accredited program in Radiological Science/ Technology, or equivalent Associate/Diploma degree in Radiological science for North American is required. Experience Required For Grade 08: Two (2) years with Bachelor’s or four (4) years of related experience with Associate/Diploma degree is required. For Grade 09:·Four (4) years as a CT Technologist at KFSH&RC, or (Grade08) related experience is required. ·Average of annual performance appraisal at least (3.5) for the last four (4) years.· fifty (50) hours of cumulative continued medical education [CME] is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)·Current Registration from country of origin and Saudi Commission for Health Specialties(SCHS) is required. ·Registration in the American Registry of Radiographic Technologists, the Canadian Association of Medical Radiation Technologists,or equivalent is required for non-Saudis.',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('CONSULTANT, GYNECOLOGY ONCOLOGY','Saudi Arabia','Medina','','Summary Responsible for the diagnosis and treatment of medical diseases and conditions, as well as the provision of medical care in the field of Gynecology/Gynecologic Oncology, in accordance with current medical staff bylaws, rules and regulations and the hospital\'s policies and procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties*Clinical Responsibilities-Provides high quality patient care in all aspects of Gynecology according to his/her approved clinical privileges.-Provides consultation (inpatient, and emergency room) upon request and responds in a timely manner within the prescribed timeframe as outlined in KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.) policy. -Responsible for the timely completion, competencies, accuracy and eligibility of the medical record.-Provides on-call service and ensures availability and response time within the prescribed timeframe in accordance with hospital policy. -Conducts daily morning rounds to identify patients ready for discharge. Ensures that discharge orders are written 24 hours prior to discharge. -Performs any other clinical responsibilities related to Gynecology, as assigned. *Academic Responsibilities-Provides orientation, bedside training and supervision to interns, residents and fellows as assigned.-Participates in Department’s educational activities and training programs. Partakes in national and international medical conferences.-Maintains and enhances professional knowledge and continuing education requirements.*Research Responsibilities-Participates in clinical, basic and translational research projects in accordance with Research Advisory Council Policy in order to advance knowledge, improve the quality of post graduate education and contribute to the national and international recognition of KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.).*Administrative Responsibilities-Undertakes the administrative duties assigned by Head of Section or Chairman.-Participates in all mandatory departmental activities and serves on departmental and hospital committees and other administrative functions, as required.-Assists the department in the development and implementation of techniques and practices that help maximize the utilization of all resources within the department and across the KFSH&RC (Gen. Org.).-Abides by the current hospital and medical staff bylaws, all relevant rules, regulations and policies and keeps updated of any changes that might occur. Education Graduation from an accredited medical school, completion of required period of training in specialty and/or subspecialty, with Arab or American Board certification, membership and/or fellowship status in the United Kingdom and/or Canada or their equivalent. Experience Required Seven (7) Years of training in specialty or subspecialty plus postgraduate training experience must be equal to or exceed seven (7) years’ experience in the subspecialty. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('CYBER SECURITY RISK SPECIALIST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for identifying, prioritize and respond to cybersecurity risks for the organization to protect its information assets and technology in accordance with the organization\'s policies and procedures, as well as relevant laws and regulations of National Cybersecurity Authority and other related entities. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Responsible for identifying, analysing, prioritising and evaluating of Hospital’s cyber security risks and issues.2. Ability to monitoring, reporting and communicating cybersecurity risks. 3. Capability to respond to risk and planning for mitigation. 4. Assess cybersecurity vulnerability and measurement of vulnerability. 5. Conducts vulnerability testing to identify weaknesses and collaborate with cybersecurity team to update defensive protocols as necessary6. Conducts regularly scheduled reviews of security services quality and provide guidance on protecting the internal network from outside, Internet cyber threats.7. Assists in developing the annual cyber security risk assessment plan. 8. Writes and delivers reports and presentations highlighting findings, identifying and explaining cybersecurity risks, and solutions.9. Ensures that controls are operating effectively, and provide research and analytical support.10. Shows full understanding of the cybersecurity risk framework and ability to demonstrate it. 11. Ability to assess other staff in evaluating, identifying, and mitigating cybersecurity risks 12. Follows all Hospital’s related policies and procedures.13. Participates in self and others\' education, training and development, as applicable.14. Performs other related duties as assigned. Education Master’s, or Bachelor’s Degree in Information Security, Computer Science, Information Technology, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required Five (5) years of related experience with Master’s, or seven (7) years with Bachelor’s Degree is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Saudi National Only.? CISSP or CISM or CEH or IT Risk Fundamentals certifications is preferred.? Certificate in Cyber Security or related field is preferred.',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('EXPEDITER III','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Provides technical support and assistance such that materials, products or supplies, and services are shipped/received in a time-sensitive manner as stipulated in the purchase orders issued by the Buyer/Senior Buyer. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Continually monitors suppliers to ensure progress against purchase order is in line with agreed delivery time. Tracks deliveries from suppliers for purchase orders that are overdue or urgent.2. Reviews requests for purchase or purchase orders for any discrepancy and compliance with prevailing policies and procedures. Provides technical advice to concerned buyers or requesting Department, as necessary. 3. Communicates with concerned end users or with vendors/suppliers to facilitate action on pending purchase orders. Prepares required forms or letters and other correspondence to address or resolve issues concerning a specific purchase order.4. Coordinates with stores or other involved Hospital units to process rush orders. 5. Prepares change orders as required ensuring that these are in accordance with established policies and regulations of the Hospital and within the approved levels of authority.6. Compiles records of all purchased orders processed. Provides assistance in the maintenance of comprehensive databases regarding vendors and suppliers for the entire Supply Chain Management. 7. Assist in monitoring performance of vendors/suppliers vis-à-vis timeliness of delivery and provides required information regarding vendors and suppliers based on existing records.8. Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures.9. Participates in self and other’s education, training, and development, as applicable.10. Performs any other related duties as assigned. Education Bachelor’s Degree or IPA Diploma in Hospital Administration or other related discipline is required. Experience Required No required experience with Bachelor’s Degree or one (1) year of related experience with IPA Diploma is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('HEAD OF ORGANIZATION ENGAGEMENT','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for leading the design, delivery, review and monitoring of Stakeholder engagement and communications strategy and plan. Engages with stakeholders to identify and address communications needs and supports Culture & Engagement Management Director with developing Organization Engagement strategy and plan. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Supports Director of Culture & Engagement Management with the design, development, delivery and management of stakeholder engagement and Organization Engagement activities. 2. Identifies key stakeholders influential to the success of the transformation, and who need to be engaged to secure buy-in. 3. Oversees the deployment of stakeholder engagement plan and run pulse checks. 4. Generates and maintains advocacy at the executive level of the respective Hospital’s and stakeholder buy-in for the implementation project. 5. Oversees and refines stakeholder engagement plans based on feedback. 6. Identifies change agents influential to the success of the transformation and track their support periodically. 7. Involves and mobilizes and Change Agents network and set-up cadence to secure two-way feedback on the specific change being deployed 8. Builds and rollout action plans based on feedback from Change Agents network. 9. Defines Organization Engagement and plan in coordination with Director of Culture & Engagement Management. 10. Ensures adherence to Hospital’s information security policies and procedures, and report breaches or other security risks accordingly. Education Master’s or Bachelor’s Degree in Business Administration, Communications, Public Relations, Change Management, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required Nine (9) years of related experience with Master’s, or eleven (11) years with Bachelor’s Degree, including four (4) years in a senior or supervisory capacity is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Saudi Nationals Only.',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('MAIL SORTER I','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Performs all transactions in Mail Room, such as mail sorting, searching and mail distribution. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Sortsincomingpersonal/businessmailforallthe Hospitaldepartments,employeesandtheir dependents and patients, and which are received from the Riyadh Central Post Office.2. Records incoming personal/business mail such as registered mail and parcels. Issues notices to concerned employees to collect their mail from the Mail Room.3. Receivesandrecordspersonal/businessincomingexpressmail (AI-Bareed AI-Mumtaz)EMSand contacts concerned employees on phone to collect their items from the Mail Room.4. Sorts inter-departmentalincoming and outgoingmail, newspapers & magazinesand all otheritems received from all the Hospital departments and keep ready for delivery to concerned departments.5. Sorts outgoing personal/business mail such as ordinary, registered according to the countries name and make these ready to be delivered to the Riyadh Central Post Office through the Mail Room Liaison Officer.6. Logs all outgoing personal registered mail in the Register Mail Log Form for dispatch through the Mail Room Liaison Officer to the Riyadh Central Post Office.7. Controls Franking Machine and maintains record of postage used, for all personal/business outgoing mail for all the Hospital departments, employees and their dependents including patients.8. Assists in delivering and picking up all mail from/to various Hospital departments, whenever there is shortage of Mail Room Mail Distributors.9. Answers telephone calls regarding mail queries from different Hospital departments and employees.10. Checks all unknown personal/business incoming mail which are received without MBC number or the department name, from the IBM mainframe by the employees family last name.11. Participates in self-and others’ education, training and development as applicable12. Follows all Hospital\'s related policies and procedures. Education Diploma in Hospital Administration, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required One (1) year of relatedexperience is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Saudi National only.',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('MANAGEMENT CONSULTANT, ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Provides seniorprofessional counsel and support in the development and implementation of corporate management processes, programs, plans and systems that contribute strategically to the overall effectiveness and efficiency of Adminsitrative Services management Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Assists the Executive Director in providing advice on all issues pertinent to the Administrative Services.2. Acts as senior capacity as directed by the Executive Director. Acts as a team leader major in Administrative projects as directed by the Executive Director.3. Applies holistic/ system approach in solving problems facing the KFSH&RC Healthcare system.4. Advises supervisors in planning projects, conducting studies/projects, developing and implementation of plans. Provides advise on the preparation,allocation, monitoring and reallocatino of Hospital budget/ resources.5. Makes presentations to high management as assigned by the Executive Director.6. Coordinates the development of management systems for improving efficiency in Administrative Services. Maintains liaison with key management staff and/or Government agencies or Ministries as assigned.7. Takes a lead role in the recruitment of senior-level staff and assist the Executive Director with performance evaluation of employees.8. Assists the Executive Director in conducting special studies and projects. Serves on committees as may be assigned by the Executive Director.9. Maintains knowledge on current trends in specialty and makes recommendations for continuous improvement.10. Reviews documents and files and informs/advises on related significant issues.11. Follows all Hospital related policies and procedures.12. Participate in self and others\' educational,training and development , as applicable. Education Master\'s, Degree in Management, Health Care Administration, Hospital Administration or Organization required. Experience Required Ten (10) years of professional experience in the field of management,including of five (5) years managerial/supervisory experience and in similar duties and function of this job, in hospital setting or a large public organization required. Other Requirements(Certificates)NA',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('MANAGER, AMBULANCE SERVICES','Saudi Arabia','Medina','','Summary Responsible for management of the entire Ambulance Services and participating in the administration of emergency medical services to patients under the care and responsibility of King Faisal Specilist Hospital and Research Centre. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Accountable for the management of the entire Ambulance Services and ensure the proper level of patient care.2. Works with Supervisor, Medical Director and Paramedic Clinical Coordinator/EMT Instructor in all aspects of developemnt, implementation and evaluation of educational programs as well as continuous quality improvement.3. Ensures that equipment is properly maintained and operated. Ensures the safe work practices are followed, lifting, etc. Ensures that all required supplies and materials are present.4. Reviews application for employment and communicates with local and international recruitment partners to ensure best recommendations for hire.5. Develops collaborative team practice models to ensure the best modalities for patient care are followed. Follows and ensure Performance improvement model and practices are explored and implemented to enable optimum patient care and efficiency.6. Assess emergency situations to determine the best course of action and appropriate protocol.7. Provides information and assistance to other departments on assigned functions.8. Responsible for the enforcement of all Personnel policies, and the handling of disciplinary problems as required,.9. Recommends, develops and implements policy changes relating to Ambluance Services.10. Follows all hospital related policies and procedures.11. Participates in self and other\'s education, training and development, as applicable.12. Performs other related duties as assigned. Education Master’s or Bachelor’s Degree in Emergency Health Services with an emphasis in Emergency Medical Services (EMS) is required. Experience Required Grade 11: Five (5) years of related experience including two (2) years in a seniority position with Master’s or seven (7) years with Bachelor’s Degree of similar requirements is required. Grade 12: Seven (7) years of related experience including four (4) years as a Manager, Ambulance Services (Grade 11) with Master’s or nine (9) years with Bachelor’s Degree is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Paramedic licensure from country of origin and the following qualifications: BLS, ACLS, PALS, NRP and PHTLS.',NULL,'2023-10-20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('MASON ASSISTANT','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Assists skilled tradesmen in all masonry works. Actions are normally determined by specific instruction from the supervisor or by following well-defined procedures, methods and practices. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Assists skilled technicians in performing assigned masonry works.2. Operates machine tools such as pneumatic jackhammer, compactor, road saw, vibrator, grinder, chipping tools, concrete mixers and concrete block machine.3. Performs semi-skilled masonry repairs and installation such as pointing up bricks/stone work and patching plaster walls.4. Follows all prescribed safety procedures.5. Follows all Hospital\'s related policies and procedures.6. Participates in self and others\' education, training and development, as applicable. Education Associate Degree/ Diploma, or High School with Vocational Training is required. Experience Required No experience is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A.',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SECURITY MAN I','Saudi Arabia','Jeddah','','Summary Guides and supports subordinates. Operates fixed posts and other assignments as a security officer in order to ensure a safe and secure environment for all KFSH&RC properties and persons. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Guides and supports Security Men assigned to the certain area ensuring compliance with established procedures and policies.2. Provides continual advice, counsel and training to subordinate personnel, as directed.3. Operates fixed posts within the Hospital to channel visitors/vehicles to authorized areas, assists ambulance arrivals, and keeps ambulance entrance clear of obstructions.4. Maintains static posts, makes foot patrols of Hospital complex, observes and reports fire and safety hazards, challenges suspected trespassers and non-badged personnel.5. Responds to all fire alarms, assists in fighting fires and all emergency cases, and calls for security assistance.6. Undergoes cross training as fireman/firefighter.7. Provides surveillance and protection of Hospital staff, patients, visitors and Hospital property.8. Responsible for safeguarding critical sites and sensitive areas. Screens and controls visitors/vehicles to Hospital and housing areas.9. Provides security escorts and protection for VIPs and other dignitaries while in the facility Education Bachelor’s or Associate Degree/Diploma in Law Enforcement Science, Hospital Administration, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required No related experience with Bachelor’s Degree, or one (1) year of related experience with Diploma is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)* Saudi National Only.* Valid motor vehicle driving license is required.',NULL,'2023-10-14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SECURITY MAN II','Saudi Arabia','Jeddah','','Summary Operates fixed posts and patrols the Hospital’s area in order to detect and prevent fire, theft, vandalism and unauthorized entry. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Operates fixed posts to screen and check badges of visitors to the Hospital, and to direct and control motor vehicles.2. Maintains fixed posts within the Hospital to channel visitors to authorized areas. Assists ambulance arrivals. Keeps ambulance entrance clear of obstructions. Opens and locks Hospital doors, as required.3. Patrols Hospital grounds to detect unauthorized persons or vehicles. Confronts unauthorized persons for questioning, routes or detains them, as required.4. Maintains fixed posts at housing unit areas to screen visitors/vehicles; denies entry to unauthorized personnel/vehicles and assists residents, as required.5. Checks cars for parking authorization and prevents cars from parking in restricted areas.6. Reports any unusual conditions or malfunction of heating, plumbing or electrical systems encountered while patrolling and sounds fire signal to alert security and other Hospital personnel in the event of detecting a fire. Education Diploma or High School Education is required. Experience Required No experience with Diploma, or one (1) year of related experience with High School is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)* Saudi National Only.* Valid motor vehicle driving license is required',NULL,'2023-10-20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SENIOR COORDINATOR, EDUCATION SERVICES','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Coordinates plans and supervises all educational activities of the Dept. Keeps continuity and improvement of Educational programs and services. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Plans, Supervises, and coordinates day-to-day educational activities and instructor’s schedules. 2. Provides periodic progress reports regarding educational activities and programs at least on quarterly basis. 3. Conducts educational programs which enable staff to achieve certification in different specialty areas to meet the standards. 4. Develops annual objectives related to educational activities of the Training & Development. 5. Recommends the annual educational budget based on the projected educational needs. 6. Prepares the annual operational plan of educational activities with measurable quarterly targets. 7. Prepares the detailed weekly schedules of instruction/classes including time location, instructor etc. 8. Makes the necessary arrangements and coordination for optimal use of resources. 9. Keeps abreast of current concepts of education through reading and personal contacts with other education professionals in the Kingdom and abroad. 10. Assists in recruitment and in-service training of instructors. Interviews and recommends hiring an educational staff. 11. Coordinates and directly participates in meetings with Education Coordinators of other departments to determine educational needs and enhance collaboration. 12. Participates in educational committees for development, coordination, and implementation of educational programs. 13. Establishes and updates a coding system for all courses and procedures. 14. Acts as a resource person, providing direction, supervision, and guidance of educational staff. 15. Develops and updates unified standards, policies, procedures, protocols and methods related to education and instruction.  16. Determines educational materials based on need assessment tools. 17. Confers with teaching and administrative staff to plan and develop curricula to meet the needs. 18. Visits classrooms to observe and evaluate the effectiveness of instructional methods of each instructor/topic and recommends improvement. Education Master’s or Bachelor\'s degree in Education, Training, Hospital Administration or other related field is required. Experience Required Five (5) years of related experience with Master’s, or seven (7) years of related experience with Bachelor’s degree is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SENIOR ENGAGEMENT ANALYST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Responsible for leading Organization Engagement activities He/she supports the Engagement Section with designing and delivering stakeholder engagement and communications plan. Designs and sets up frameworks and tools to monitor and measure the effectiveness of stakeholder engagement and communications activities/initiatives, assesses gaps and develops recommendations. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Supports the development and execution of stakeholder engagement and communications plan in coordination with the Corporate Communications Department.2. Monitors and track the execution of stakeholder engagement and communication plan deliverables and activities and reports updates to Organization Engagement Specialist on a regular basis.3. Evaluates risks, opportunities and issues related to engagement and communications, and provide mitigation to meet plan’s quality, timeline and objectives.4. Supports organization engagement Section with building and maintaining change agent’s network.5. Facilitates periodical meetings with Change Agents, solicit feedback and document agreed actions items.6. Facilitates change communication and awareness sessions.7. Ensures adherence to organization information security policies and procedures, and report breaches or other security risks accordingly.8. Follows all organization related policies and procedures.9. Participates in self and other’s education, training and development, as applicable.10. Performs any other related duties as assigned. Education Master’s or Bachelor’s Degree in Business Administration Communications, Public Relations, Change Management, or other related discipline is required. Experience Required Three (3) years of related experience with Master’s, or Five (5) years with Bachelor’s Degree is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)Any related professional certificate is preferred. Saudi Nationals Only.',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SENIOR HEALTH INFORMATICS ANALYST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Address and troubleshoots issues escalated by the Service Desk involving workflows, interfaces, and applications for the clinical, medical and biomedical applications used within the enterprise. Helps in ensuring the optimal usage of applications to meet the changing needs of the business. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Address and troubleshoot L2 issues escalated by the Service Desk involving workflows, interfaces, medical device connectivity, and applications for clinical, medical and biomedical applications used within the enterprise.2. Assists end-user with packaged application report development as appropriate related to clinical, medical and biomedical applications3. Manages application downtime and other issues by liaising with the appropriate Application Department and other relevant technical departments, as necessary.4. Ensures downtime and other issues are communicated to relevant stakeholders and report back to stakeholders upon resolution.5. Escalates unresolved issues to the relevant Applications & Health Informatics Department, as necessary (L3 support).6. Oversees the development of training material for users of health applications.7. Administers and implement standard and minor changes to certain applications for certain capabilities as indicated in the change classification matrix.8. Deploys Downtime Medication Administration Record files and Pharmacy Medication files from ICIS to designated end-user devices in all wards and Pharmacy.9. Assists end-user with packaged application report development.10. Follows prescribed system safety and security procedures of computing environment. Education Master’s or Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Informatics, Health Sciences, or related discipline is required. Experience Required Three (3) years of related experience with Master’s Degree, or five (5) years of related experience with Bachelor’s Degree is required. Other Requirements(Certificates)N/A',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('SENIOR MRI TECHNOLOGIST','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Performsimagingproceduresutilizingmagneticresonanceimagingscanners. Assistsother technologists in performing sophisticated procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Prepares the inpatient schedule and coordinates with floors regarding patient’s preparation andtransportation.2. Performs imaging procedures utilizing magnetic resonance imaging scanners. Assists othertechnologists.3. Investigates possible, new procedures.4. Assists in maintaining inventory of stock and non-stock supplies.5. Ensures that equipment is properly maintained. Contacts supervisor for any repair needed.6. Participates in departmental in-services and continuing education and CQI programs.7. Assists with development, revision, and implementation of policies and procedures for the section,department, and Hospital.8. Comply with the section policies, procedures and protocols. Follow the section quality improvementprogram in accordance with CBAHI, JCI, SFDA and other accreditation agencies standards.9. Comply with the Radiation Safety Rules and Regulations of the Hospital in accordance with KACST and K. A. CARE and other National or International Regulatory bodies.10. Apply ALARA principle Role within the section practice for all procedures. Education Bachelor’s or Graduate from an accredited Radiologic Technology program, or successful completion of specialized training at KFSH in Radiological Sciences/Technology is required. Experience Required Grade 09: Four (4) years of related experience with Bachelor’s or six (6) years for Associate Degree/Diploma is required. Grade 10: -Four (4) years as a Senior MRI Technologist at KFSH&RC, or (Grade 09) related experience is required. -Average of annual performance appraisal at least (3.5) for the last four (4) years. -One-hundred (100) cumulative continued medical education [CME]. Other Requirements(Certificates)-Current Registration from country of origin and Saudi Commission for Health Specialties (SCHS) is required. -Registration in the American Registry of Radiographic Technologists, the Canadian Association of Medical Radiation Technologists, or equivalent is required for non-Saudis.',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('TECHNOLOGIST, POSITRON EMISSION TOMOGRAPHY SERVICES','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Summary Performs Clinical Positron Emission Tomogaphy (PET) diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. Essential Responsibilities and Duties1. Reviews exam orders/requisitions, reviews corresponding protocol, and asks questions of superior(s) and prepares for exam. 2. Performs all patient imaging with attention to patient care, quality imaging and efficient management of time. Communicates with the CNM physicians to ensure that all images are satisfactory.  3. Loads, dispenses and administers radioactive isotopes of the PET injector for use in patient studies as well as manual dispensing of doses using the dose calibrator. 4. Performs calibration checks on all the PET equipment as per the manufacturer’s recommendation.  5. Follows physician’s orders, determines appropriate radiopharmaceutical and dosage. Consults with physician as needed. 6. Explains procedures to patients, injects patients and conducts study, and notifies supervisor of any problems. 7. Observes radiation safety techniques and procedures, including use of protective shielding and handling and disposal of radiopharmaceuticals. 8. Informs supervisor of equipment malfunction and/or need for repair and documents all testing proceduresand all studies performed. 9. Participates in-services and/or continuing education and the PI Process. Assists in training and supervision of students, interns and trainees and evaluates their performance. 10. Comply with the Radiation Safety Rules and Regulations of KFSH&RC in accordance with KACST and K. A. CARE and other National or International Regulatory bodies. Education Bachelor’s Degree in Radiological Science/ Technology required for Saudi Nationals, or Graduate from an accredited Radiologic Technology program (minimum 2 years) for non-Saudi is required. Experience Required Grade 08: Two (2) years of related experience is required. Grade 9: Four (4) years as Technologist, Positron Emission Tomography Services at KFSH&RC, or (Grade 08) related experience is required. Average of annual performance appraisal at least (3.5) for the last four (4) years. Fifty (50) hours of cumulative continued medical education [CME]. Other Requirements(Certificates)Current Registration from country of origin and Saudi Commission for Health Specialties (SCHS) is required.  Must be certified as PET Technologist including one of the following: NMTCB, ARRT, ASCP or CAMRT or equivalent for non-Saudis. ',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Research Centre',NULL),('It Specialist and System Administrator','Egypt','Cairo','Sheraton','Install and configure software and hardware Manage network servers and technology tools Set up accounts and workstations Monitor performance and maintain systems according to requirements Troubleshoot issues and outages Ensure security through access controls, backups and firewalls Upgrade systems with new releases and models Develop expertise to train staff on new technologies Build an internal wiki with technical documentation, manuals and IT policies','Proven experience as a System Administrator, Network Administrator or similar role Experience with databases, networks (LAN, WAN) and patch management Knowledge of system security (e.g. intrusion detection systems) and data backup/recovery Ability to create scripts in Python, Perl or other language Familiarity with various operating systems and platforms Resourcefulness and problem-solving aptitude Excellent communication skills BSc/Ba in Information Technology, Computer Science or a related discipline; professional certification (e.g. Microsoft Certified Systems Administrator (MCSA)) is a plus','2023-10-06',48,18,2,3,7000,7500,0,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'Kiromarble for marble and granite',NULL),('Junior React Native App Developer','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','As a Junior React Native App Developer at [Your Company Name], you will have the opportunity to learn and grow in a supportive environment. You will work closely with experienced developers and cross-functional teams to contribute to the development of cutting-edge mobile applications. This role is an excellent opportunity for someone looking to kick-start their career in mobile app development. Responsibilities: Collaborate with senior developers, product managers, and designers to assist in implementing mobile app features. Learn and write clean, maintainable, and efficient code in React Native. Contribute to the development and maintenance of mobile applications for i OS and Android platforms. Assist in optimizing app performance for a smooth user experience. Participate in troubleshooting and debugging activities. Stay up-to-date with industry trends and best practices. Seek guidance and mentorship from experienced team members.','Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or currently pursuing one). Basic knowledge of Java Script and a strong interest in learning React Native. Eagerness to learn and grow in mobile app development. Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail. Excellent communication and teamwork skills. Ability to work in a fast-paced, agile development environment. Enthusiasm for staying updated on the latest technologies and tools in mobile development. Experience with Git is a plus. Knowledge of RESTful/Graph QL API integration is a plus. Experience releasing apps on Google Play Store/App Store is a plus.','2023-10-05',0,0,NULL,NULL,10000,15000,0,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'Klik',NULL),('Senior React Native App Developer','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','                    As a Senior React Native App Developer at Klik, you will play a crucial role in designing, developing, and maintaining cutting-edge mobile applications. You will work closely with cross-functional teams to bring our ideas to life, ensuring high-quality, performant, and user-friendly apps. Your expertise in React Native will be essential as you contribute to the development of our mobile product. Responsibilities:- Collaborate with product managers, designers, and other developers to define and implement mobile app features.- Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code in React Native.- Develop and maintain mobile applications for both i OS and Android platforms.- Optimize app performance for a smooth user experience.- Troubleshoot and debug issues as they arise.- Stay up-to-date with industry trends and incorporate best practices into the development process.- Mentor and provide guidance to junior developers. ','- Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent work experience).- Proven experience as a React Native developer, with a strong portfolio of mobile applications.- Extensive knowledge of Java Script, ES6+, and Type Script.- Familiarity with mobile app architecture patterns (MVC, MVVM, Redux).- Proficiency in RESTful/Graph QL API integration.- Experience with Git.- Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.- Excellent communication and teamwork skills.- Ability to work in a fast-paced, agile development environment.- Knowledge of native i OS and Android development is a plus.- Experience Releasing apps on Google Play Store/App Store is a plus','2023-10-05',20,9,2,8,18000,30000,0,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Klik',NULL),('IT Help Desk Specialist','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','KODE represents a set of values and principles that we strive to live by through all our actions, to build the characters of young children and to develop a principled generation full of life and hope. For us, it’s all about helping every member of our community unleash their potential while inspiring them through our day-to-day interaction, to lead more active and healthy lifestyles, thus becoming better human beings and citizens of a homogenous community. At KODE, we believe that great sportsmanship can only be attained if it comes hand in hand with great character, therefore, our brand follows a set of values, which we believe can build better athletes and ultimately better human beings. Location New Cairo - First Settlement Job purpose: You will be providing an outstanding technical support experience to staff and customers from problem identification to full resolution. When needed, you will collaborate with others to engage subject matter experts, Engineering or Management to attend to reported requests or issues. Your day to day job will be about providing both technical expertise (either on your own or by involving your colleagues) and about being an excellent communicator and a service oriented professional. What do we expect from you: Key duties: Install and configure computer hardware operating systems and applications. Monitor and maintain computer systems and networks. Install and modify operating systems and software programs, such as virus protectionand word processing printers. Talk to staff through a series of actions, either face-to-face or over the phone, to help set up systems or resolve issues. Act as the initial point of contact for phone calls, ticketing and emails from: Internal staff regarding any IT issues and request Members directly (through the ticking system or through tickets coming from the Customer Experience team) with regards to the co-working space or the Club App. Provide the first line support - troubleshooting of IT related problems of software, hardware Laptops, PCs and Printers or redirect the issue to the concerned subject matters Liaise with internal support teams and external service providers as required to resolve Incidents and complete Service Requests, to ensure compliance with SLA’s and OLA’s Escalate unresolved request/incident to the infrastructure support team and back-end team Maintain a high degree of customer service for all support queries and adhere to all service management principles Troubleshoot system and network problems, diagnosing and solving hardware or software faults Replace parts as required Provide support, including procedural documentation and relevant reports. Follow diagrams and written instructions to repair a fault or set up a system. Support the roll-out of new applications. Set up new users\' accounts and profiles and deal with password issues. Test and evaluate new technology Communicate progress and follow up in a timely manner to the manager Sending Daily reports on open tickets and End of Day Report Publishing support documentation to assist staff with requests for information & provide staff training if required Responsible for safeguarding business, staff and customers data of all forms either sensitive or non sensitive or else will be subject to disciplinary action that might lead to dismissal','To perform your job successfully, you need to have the following minimum requirements: Education and experience: Bachelor\'s degree preferable in computer engineering/science or telecommunication Minimum 2-3 years of experience in the same position Skills and knowledge: Ability to prioritize and manage many open cases at one time Must be able to respond well under stress, pressure and in emergency cases High customer orientation Excellent problem solving skills Strong Team Player Excellent communication skills Excellent in time management Willing to work for long hours on occasion Shall be familiar with working in hospitable, and cheerfulness industry Very good English verbal and writing skills Must have computer and network skills. Must be able to respond well under stress, pressure and in emergency cases Should possess high level of integrity and is trusted with sensitive data','2023-10-01',44,11,2,3,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Kode Clubs - Hassan Allam Sports Clubs',NULL),('Sales Executive','Egypt','Cairo','Sheraton','Conduct market research to identify selling possibilities and evaluate customer needs Actively seek out new sales opportunities through cold calling, networking and social media Set up meetings with potential clients and listen to their wishes and concerns Prepare and deliver appropriate presentations on products and services Create frequent reviews and reports with sales and financial data Ensure the availability of stock for sales and demonstrations Participate on behalf of the company in exhibitions or conferences Negotiate/close deals and handle complaints or objections Collaborate with team members to achieve better results Gather feedback from customers or prospects and share with internal teams','looking for females fresh graduated - Computer science - retail & sales back ground - IT back ground ','2023-10-01',23,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Konnekt Union',NULL),('National Project Logistics Customer Excellence Manager','Egypt','Cairo','','We deliver high quality solutions to our customers and we are leaders in the logistics industry. Join us and become a part of our great team. Your Role The National Projects Logistics Customer Excellence Manager is responsible to manage and develop the financial, operational, and strategic results of the PROM profit canters and to ensure smooth execution of general PROM operations and job files for securing new business. He/she monitors department’s coordinators and oversees the operational processes to ensure at the same time a smooth process flow. This in addition to developing the coordinators to their full potential and achieving budget/forecast targets. Your Responsibilities Support the different entities on the technical/commercial part of PROM requests and business implementation including issuing of SOPs based on secured contracts. Act as a point of contact for sales activities of the defined strategic local / regional PROM accounts and within K+N entities Negotiating rates with Kuehne + Nagel offices, Shipping lines, Air lines, truckers, etc.… and providing minimum selling rates to sales for sales accounts. Work closely with Dxb RG, GKAM / RKAM / OKAM team, corporate product managements for Project, Oil + Gas and Marine Logistics as well as sales team for securing/retaining new business. Work closely with IT, ZS-C & customers’ solution desk (ZV-C) for monitoring & achieving required quality targets and coordinate for nominating customers to IT solution. Establish strong, long-lasting business relationships with existing and new customers via a hands-on approach. Regularly visit customers, jointly with sales and travel when/where required. Entry point for bookings from sales & counterparts for assessment of tasks and effecting contract review. Interact between customers, shipping lines, airlines, truckers, and any other subcontractor to effect customers’ requirements and control any deviations to maximize customers’ satisfaction. Support in selection, audit of nominated sub-contractors and preferred PROM vendors, adherence to legal and compliance standards Strictly adhere to QSHE directives (incl. Code of Conduct, Ethical Behavior, FCPA etc.) and ensure they are implemented and applied within the department. Promotes HSE awareness of his approved suppliers as per customers’ standards and requirements. Reporting, communication and follow up on suppliers’ HSE Incidents when handling KN businesses and ensuring that proper corrective actions have been implemented. Preparation of Risk Assessments where necessary ensuring that controls are in place for possible risk mitigation. Your Skills and Experiences 5+ Years’ experience Project logistics and Oil & Gas logistics experience. Strong industry knowledge of Customs requirements / Bid process for the Oil & Gas Industry Proven ability to communicate effectively at all levels. Willingness to travel and mid-term assignments up to 3 months in Middle East / African countries. Leadership responsibility in direct and indirect reporting structures. Strong competent leader and team player. Ability to influence, negotiate and resolve conflicts on internal and external board levels. Having a strategic vision and ability to develop new business opportunities and processes. Questions traditional ways of doing things and encourages change. Proven Success in building competitive and sustainable solutions.',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Kuehne & Nagel Logistics',NULL),('Sea Logistics Expert- Systems and process','Egypt','Cairo','','We deliver high quality solutions to our customers and we are leaders in the logistics industry. Join us and become a part of our great team. Your Role To be responsible for managing the Process and Systems functions in the Customer Care Locations of Egypt. This includes all the related activities of process analysis, continuous improvement, training, support, and maintenance of all sea logistics processes and their related applications. To be responsible and ensure the Customer onboarding process is implemented and the methodology is effectively used. This role undertakes functional and disciplinary leadership as per the relevant organizational structure and ensures methodical, professional, and open leadership and coaching. Your Responsibilities To be responsible for the delivery of day-to-day process support for customer service and management through supporting our sea logistics production systems and customer service tools in cooperation with the regional team. To oversee and ensure the delivery of training (system enhancements, sea freight forwarding, process optimization, and other advanced and dedicated training). To ensure high operational data quality via analysis, review, and action planning together with the Sea Logistics Customer Care Location Managers. To support and oversee supplier electronic data (EDI) interfaces via the definition of requirements, support and communicate with IT teams and Sea Logistics Process Excellence teams for specifications. To drive process optimization and support the implementation of changed processes to improve the quality of operational processes and systems. To oversee the testing and implementation of new releases in cooperation with the Regional Team. Act as the interface between IT and the business by defining + communicating system requirements in cooperation with Regional Team. To drive the analysis of operational procedures for both customers and suppliers and assist with documenting and producing solutions. Your Skills and Experiences 2 years of experience in the same position Needs to bring the right attitude to the job with a focus on driving profitable operational solutions for the organization making sure we are able to deliver, maintain and improve. Should have a focus on leadership, project management, systems knowledge, and above all else, a process improvement mindset. They must be flexible, and trustworthy and demonstrate a high level of business judgment, focus, and commitment to be successful in this role. Team focused mindset Proficiency in English ',NULL,'2023-10-11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Kuehne & Nagel Logistics',NULL),('IT Help Desk','Egypt','Cairo','Nasr City','Provide technical support to end-users via phone, email, and in person. Perform troubleshooting hardware and software issues on desktops, laptops, printers, and other peripherals. Install and configure software applications for the end-users. Maintain accurate records of all support requests and resolutions. Manage user accounts and access permissions. Collaborate with other IT staff to resolve complex issues. Identify and suggest possible improvements in procedures.','Bachelor’s degree in computer science or related field preferred.2+ years of experience in an IT help desk or technical support role. Strong knowledge of Windows operating systems (Windows 10), Microsoft Office Suite, and Active Directory. Excellent communication skills with the ability to explain technical concepts to non-technical users. Ability to work independently as well as part of a team in a fast-paced environment. Good knowledge of Sophos firewall. Excellent in all Microsoft 365 apps V. good in English Working Conditions: Location: Nasr City. Working Days: 5 days + 2 days OFFWorking hours: 8 hours (Flexible till 7 PM)','2023-09-01',311,40,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'LABS',NULL),('SAP HCM Support Consultant','Egypt','Cairo','Nasr City','Helping in reporting in PA, OM & TM - adhoc queries (may be need to create new) & SE16 - may be wage type reporter as well Helping in setting up master data for testing End user will speak from a business point of view as a consultant we have to make them understand how SAP works Creating custom infotype or creating a new field to be included in the standard infotype Undertake short-term or long-term projects to address a variety of issues and needs Conduct situational and data analysis to identify and understand a problem or issue Evaluate the situation periodically and make adjustments when need','Min. 4 years of experience in the related area. HCM consultant with 4-6 years SAP HCM functional knowledge including configuration expertise Master Data and Organization Management, Personnel Administration, Time Management and Payroll. Reasonable level  of Success factors experience. Excellent Analytical skills SAP Certification is preferable. Strong English written/verbal communication Good time management skills and ability to work under pressure. Self-motivated individual who works well in a team environment Self-driven, ability to work under minimal supervision, Self-Learner, and able to grow.','2023-10-19',0,0,4,6,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'LABS',NULL),('SAP Junior Develop','Egypt','Cairo','Nasr City','Understanding the needs and requirements of the clients by coordinating with their representatives and Functional Consultants. Seeking clarity on every minute detail in order to provide the best possible solution. Consulting with professionals from other departments and those working on specific SAP modules such as SAP FI/CO, MM, HCM, SD, PM/CS, SRM, and PP to ensure a consistent experience to the various users on the client\'s side. Ensuring that all programs are completed in schedule as per the client\'s guidelines. To stay updated with the latest technological advancement and changes in the world of SAP development and adapting to these changes by self-training and research work.','Bachelor’s Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or Engineering Good Knowledge of APIs and OData. Good understanding of  Java Script, CSS, HTML5, and j Query. Good Knowledge of database SQL Knowledge of  Object Oriented programming.','2023-09-01',49,19,0,1,NULL,NULL,1,3,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'LABS',NULL),('IT Account Manager','Egypt','Cairo','','Setting an initial plan of action of the required outcomes Setting the companies entire technical infrastructure Manage information technology and computer systems Plan, organize, control and evaluate IT and electronic data operations Manage IT staff by recruiting, training and coaching employees, communicating job expectations and appraising their performance Design, develop, implement and coordinate systems, policies and procedures Ensure security of data, network access and backup systems Act in alignment with user needs and system functionality to contribute to organizational policy Identify problematic areas and implement strategic solutions in time Website creation & management Audit systems and assess their outcomes Preserve assets, information security and control structures Handle annual budget and ensure cost effectiveness Able to work remotely','Ability to recognize quality work Proven working experience as an IT Manager or relevant experience Excellent knowledge of technical management, information analysis and of computer hardware/software systems Expertise in data centre management and data governance Hands-on experience with computer networks, network administration and network installation Ability to manage personnel','2023-11-01',0,0,2,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Manager ',NULL,'Latalia',NULL),('Administration Specialist – Attorney Support','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','The Administration Specialist – Attorney Support is an integral part of Latham’s Attorney Support team. This role will be responsible for performing a variety of secretarial duties of a highly responsible and confidential nature, while maintaining and tracking schedules and calendars. This role will be located in our Riyadh office. \n\nOther key responsibilities include: \n\n•Performing complete secretarial functions for attorneys and/or paralegals requiring knowledge of format, procedure, and specialized terminology.\n•Researching and obtaining a wide variety of information or documents requested by attorneys and/or paralegals.\n•Drafting, revising, and submitting client billings. May contact clients regarding delinquent bills.\n•Processing expenses and/or invoices for payment.\n•Maintaining and tracking inbox and/or calendars for attorneys.\n•Coordinating travel arrangements. Updating attorneys concerning mail and phone messages while traveling.\n\nSuccessful candidates will not only be provided with an outstanding career opportunity and welcoming environment, but will also be provided with a generous total compensation package with bonuses awarded in recognition of both individual and firm performance. Eligible employees can participate in Latham’s comprehensive benefit program which includes: \n\n•Health insurance as well as group income protection and life assurance\n•A pension plan\n•Wellness programs\n•Employee discounts\n•And more!\n\nAdditionally, we have a range of diversity programming including Global Affinity Groups. These groups provide a firmwide platform to share experiences and advice as well as an opportunity to participate in a supportive network with common interests to help make life at the firm even better. \nLatham & Watkins is committed to diversity, equal opportunity, sustainability, and pro bono legal services. We draw from a remarkable wealth of talent to create one of the world\'s leading law firms, and advance these commitments through the work of our Global Citizenship department. Our lawyers, paralegals, and professional staff worldwide comprise a rich mixture of different races, ethnic backgrounds, religions, sexual orientations, cultures, and primary languages. Our diversity makes us who we are.','Skills\nWe’d love to hear from you if you: \n\n•Demonstrate excellent written and verbal communication skills in English & Arabic.\n•Exhibit well-developed and professional interpersonal skills; ability to interact effectively with people at all organizational levels of the Firm.\n•Possess knowledge and proficiency in PC applications required, including word processing (MS Word) and spreadsheet software.\n\nAnd have: \n\n•A college degree or equivalent\n•Secretarial/support assistance experience and ability to interpret law office policies and procedures and produce accurate legal documents with minimal supervision','2023-10-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Latham & Watkins',NULL),('Attorney Support Specialist','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','The 