ities for growth','Proven work experience as a Sales account manager in Fintech field or Sales account executive Hands on experience in sales and an ability to deliver excellent customer experience Knowledge of CRM software and MS Office (MS Excel in particular)Understanding of sales performance metrics Excellent communication and negotiation skills An ability to deliver projects and answer inquiries on time Business acumen with a problem-solving attitude BSc degree in Business Administration, Marketing or relevant field','2023-10-23',17,0,5,10,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Lumin',NULL),('Sales Manager - Software Background (GULF)','Egypt','Giza','Sheikh Zayed',' Initiate sales and attain the company’s sales objectives. Sustain and broaden relationships with new Saudi Arabian and existing clients. Ensure the delivery of sales presentations to superior executive officers. Pricing and creating quotations, for the company’s software products and custom solutions Initiate and outsource projects for the company’s software products and custom solutions. Manage the Sales team ','Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business Administration, or related field. Proven work experience as a Sales Manager in the software industry is a MUSTProven work experience as a Sales Manager in Saudi Arabia is a MUST and the Gulf Area is preferred. Minimum 8 years of experience as a Sales Manager. Strong understanding and knowledge of sales performance metrics. Outstanding verbal and written communication skills. Excellent negotiation skills. Very good English','2023-10-01',16,0,8,12,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Manager ','Bachelor\'s Degree','Lumin',NULL),('Senior .NET Full Stack Developer (.NET Core & Angular)','Egypt','Giza','Sheikh Zayed','Job Brief\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Full Stack Developer to produce scalable software solutions. You’ll be part of a cross-functional team that’s responsible for the full software development life cycle, from conception to deployment.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDesign client-side and server-side architecture\nBuild the front-end of applications through appealing visual design\nDevelop and manage well-functioning databases and applications\nWrite effective APIs\nTest software to ensure responsiveness and efficiency\nTroubleshoot, debug and upgrade software\nCreate security and data protection settings\nBuild features and applications with a mobile responsive design\nWrite technical documentation\n','Requirements Proven experience “4 years minimum” as a Full Stack Developer. Proficiency with fundamental front end languages such as HTML, CSS and Java Script. Knowledge of multiple back-end languages (e.g. C#, . NET core, Java, Python) and Java Script frameworks (e.g. Angular) with professionalism in C# is a MUST. Experience with Microservices is a MUST.2+ years of experience working in an Agile environment is a MUST. Familiarity with database technology such as MS SQL, My SQL, Oracle and Mongo DB. Familiarity with web servers (e.g. IIS , Apache) and UI/UX design. Excellent communication and teamwork skills Great attention to detail Organizational skills An analytical mind','2023-10-01',41,7,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,7,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Lumin',NULL),('Senior Infrastructure Engineer','Egypt','Giza','Sheikh Zayed','Implementing new network solutions and improving the efficiency of current networks Installing, configuring and supporting (LAN & WAN) network equipment including routers, switches, AP. Installing and configuring network devices (Wi-Fi AP, Routers, Switches ... etc.) on multiple vendors. (Cisco, Fortigate, Aruba, HP … etc.)Security architecture development (high- and low-level design implementation). Configuring firewalls, routing and switching to maximize network efficiency and security. Experience with NGFWs, Mail Gateways, Web Gateways, WAF, Endpoint protection, SSL-VPN and IPSec-VPN, Traffic monitoring tools Maximizing network performance through ongoing monitoring and troubleshooting. Detecting & Solving existing network threats and security issues. Determining the latest technologies and processes that improve the overall security of the system. Modifying the technical, legal, and regulatory aspects of the system security. Configure and maintaining security policies. Implementing regulatory systems in accordance with IT security. Reporting the security analysis and monitoring findings. Creating and updating network documentation & diagrams.','6 - 8 years of experience. Certification (CCNA, NSE or higher level)Excellent communication skills. Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues. Excellent knowledge of networking protocols, especially TCP/IP. BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science. Ability to troubleshoot and identify problems, follow directions, collect data, establish facts and draw valid conclusions. Advanced hardware & software troubleshooting skills. Ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously & meet agreed with due dates','2023-10-24',9,0,6,8,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Lumin',NULL),('Solution Architect - Part Time','Egypt','Giza','Sheikh Zayed','Brief: We are looking for an experienced Software Architect to make intuitive high level decisions for software development. You will see the “big picture” and create architectural approaches for software design and implementation to guide the development team. The ideal candidates have a strong technical background and experience in . NET Framework. They are experienced in designing and possess ability to develop a unified vision for software characteristics and functions. The goal is to provide a framework for the development of a software or system that will result in high quality solutions. If you’re also familiar with Agile methodologies, holding a strong background designing scalable systems and enjoying providing end-to-end solutions to software problems, we’d like to meet you. Responsibilities: Collaborate with other professionals to determine functional and non-functional requirements for new software or applications Use tools and methodologies to create representations for functions and user interface of desired product Develop high-level product specifications with attention to system integration and feasibility Define all aspects of development from appropriate technology and workflow to coding standards Communicate successfully all concepts and guidelines to development team Oversee progress of development team to ensure consistency with initial design Provide technical guidance and coaching to developers and engineers Ensure software meets all requirements of quality, security, modifiability, extensibility etc. Approve final product before launch','Qualifications & Experience: Bachelor in Software Engineer or Computer Science. A minimum of 7+ Years of experience in related field/needed technology as a software architect. Culturally fitting with the company’s standards and profile. Adapting to dynamic work environment. Possess general programming skills & SDLC. Fluent English speaker Job Requirements Proven experience as software architect Experience in software development and coding in various languages (C#, . NET, Java etc.)Excellent knowledge of software and application design and architecture Excellent knowledge of cloud architecture Excellent knowledge of UML and other modeling methods Excellent knowledge of security measurements and metrics of software application design High level of comfort communicating effectively across internal and external organizations A technical mindset with great attention to detail Outstanding communication and presentation abilities Experience in microservices, CQRS , Event sourcing, SOA, SAGA and DDDExperience in  docker and Kubernetes Experience in big data such as Mongo Db Experience in search engines such as Elastic Search ,solr,..etc Experience in sharepoint server is a plus Agile certificate is a plus TOGAF certificate is a big plus','2023-09-01',2,0,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Lumin',NULL),('Data Engineer','Egypt','Giza','Agouza','LXT is an emerging leader in AI training data to power intelligent technology for global organizations. In partnership with an international network of contributors, LXT collects and annotates data across multiple modalities with the speed, scale, and agility required by the enterprise. Our global expertise spans over 145 countries and more than 1,000 language locales. Founded in 2010, LXT is headquartered in Toronto, Canada with a presence in the United States, UK, Egypt, India, Turkey, and Australia. The company serves customers in North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, and the Middle East. We are currently seeking a talented and motivated Data Engineer to join our dynamic Data Engineering team. As a Data Engineer, you will play a crucial role in designing, developing, and maintaining data pipelines for our data annotation projects, ensuring efficient data import and export processes. LXT technical calibers are expected to have a high level of ownership, and to be Hands-On engineers that take over the tasks until it passes the finish line. Responsibilities: Data Transformation and Integration: Perform data transformation and integration tasks to ensure data from various sources are accurately processed and made ready for annotation projects and for delivery to clients per client requirements. Data Manipulation: Ensuring efficient data storage, retrieval, and optimization to support data annotation workflows. Data Quality Assurance: Implement data quality checks and validation processes to ensure the accuracy, consistency, and integrity of data used in annotation projects. Data Pipeline Design and Development: Collaborate with the Data Engineering team to design and implement robust and scalable data pipelines for importing and exporting data used in our data annotation projects. Performance Optimization: Identify and address performance bottlenecks in data pipelines to enhance the speed and efficiency of data import and export processes. Automation and Process Improvement: Continuously seek opportunities to automate manual processes and improve data annotation workflows for increased productivity. Collaboration and Communication: Work closely with cross-functional teams, including data annotation teams, backend developers, and project managers, to understand project requirements and provide timely data support. Documentation: Maintain comprehensive documentation of data pipelines, processes, and data structures to facilitate knowledge sharing and seamless project handovers. Troubleshooting and Support: Address and resolve data-related issues, providing technical support to data annotation teams when required. Stay Updated on Emerging Technologies: Stay abreast of industry trends, tools, and technologies related to data engineering, and propose innovative solutions for data annotation projects Additional information: LXT is an equal opportunity employer and ensures that no applicant is subject to less favorable treatment on the grounds of gender, gender identity, marital status, race, color, nationality, ethnicity, age, sexual orientation, socio-economic, responsibilities for dependents, or physical or mental disability. Any hiring decision is made on the basis of skills, qualifications, and experiences. We measure our success as a business, not only by delivering great products and services and continually increasing our assets under administration and market share but also by how we positively impact people, society, and the planet.',' Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Data Engineering, or a related field. Proven experience as a Data Engineer, with 1-3 years of hands-on experience in data pipeline design, data transformation, and data integration. Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, SQL, or Scala, and experience with data manipulation libraries and frameworks. Solid knowledge of data storage and database management systems, including relational and No SQL databases. Familiarity with data visualization tools and techniques to facilitate data understanding and analysis. Experience with cloud-based data platforms, such as AWS, GCP, or Azure, is a plus. Solid understanding of data quality and data governance principles. Knowledge and experience with machine learning projects a big plus. Strong problem-solving skills with a keen eye for detail. Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a team-oriented environment. A passion for data engineering and a desire to contribute to impactful data annotation projects.','2023-10-15',0,0,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'LxT',NULL),('Senior Backend Engineer','Egypt','Giza','Agouza','We are currently seeking a Senior Software Engineer (Backend) at LXT, who will work closely with our engineering, operations and product teams to build the most secure, cutting edge data annotation tools and platforms. LXT technical calibers are expected to have a high level of ownership and to be Hands-On engineers who take over the tasks until they pass the finish line. Responsibilities: Design, develop and test new products, while maintaining the existing Stay up to date with the latest industry trends in software and cloud solutions. Ensure high code and design quality that fulfills business requirements and good design aspects (scalability, fault tolerance). Coach, mentor, and support junior team members by supporting the culture of technical excellence and zero technical debt Supporting technical estimations and effort sizing. Establishing code guidelines and reviewing PRs. Adopting unit testing and integration testing in the system. Design and implement solutions to protect against common security vulnerabilities Directly involved with the Product team to understand Requirements. Provide technical feedback about the supervised team members when required. Help the team to adopt modern software engineering practices, like Scrum, and be an active player in the Agile ceremonies.','A minimum of 4 to 6 years of experience in programming for web server/service applications Expertise in Python, Node(JS/TS), C# or skill in a similar language Experience with Relational and non-relational databases Good understanding of web servers (Apache, Nginx) and essential configurations Excellent problem-solving, design, coding, and debugging skills Technical Understanding of security and online privacy threats and the existing solution space to protect against them Familiarity with the OWASP Top 10 Web Security Vulnerabilities and their mitigation Experience preemptively and actively resolving SRE issues in production systems Familiarity with containerization concepts (e.g. Docker and Kubernetes)Experience with TDD, unit, integration, and end-to-end testing paradigms Strong command of Git and team workflows Professional-level written and spoken English Preferred qualifications: Experience with Python web frameworks (Django, Flask, Fast API, etc...)Experienced with any of the cloud platforms (Azure, GCP, or Amazon AWS)Good understanding of CI/CD, containerization, and container orchestration tools Familiar with Agile project management methodologies','2023-10-04',NULL,NULL,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'LxT',NULL),('Senior Testing Automation Engineer','Egypt','Giza','Agouza','We are currently seeking a Senior Test Automation Engineer at LXT, who will be responsible for all development changes occurring (Automation, Performance, Security & Manual), to mitigate risks as needed, and to ensure quality of the deliverables. Responsibilities: Create test scenarios, conditions, and expected results Create test data and script Test execution, and tracking defects Troubleshooting and document all findings Report and escalate to management as needed Working with software developers, BA’s and project teams Communicate findings to technical and non-technical colleagues Write and enhance the Automation script code. Execute Automation and share the required reports. Write Performance scripts and enhance them as needed. Execute Performance and share the required reports.','From 3 to 5 years experience as a Software Tester. Very good educational background, preferably in the fields of Computer science or Software Engineering. Proven working experience in Software Testing in the information technology sector. Solid technical background with understanding and/or hands-on experience in software testing tools and web technologies. Solid organizational skills including attention to detail and multi-tasking skills. Strong verbal and written communication skills with the ability to liaise with a variety of stakeholders Automation & Performance Skills. (Selenium, Test NG, Jmeter). Solid knowledge of API Testing. Aware of Software Development Lifecycle tools i.e. (Jira, Click Up, etc…)The ability to work in a team and individually.. ISTQB certification is a plus. Ability to analyze and communicate.','2023-10-04',0,0,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'LxT',NULL),('Information Security Senior Specialist','Egypt','Cairo','',' •Diligently maintain Majorel Egypt’s Information Security Framework and underlying policies, procedures, standards and guidelines.•Diligently maintain Majorel Egypt ISO27001 certification process.•Diligently maintain Majorel Egypt’s Information Security Framework and underlying policies, procedures, standards and guidelines.•Take the lead on developing, maintaining and updating the Information Security Strategy and Information Security Program•Take the lead on developing, maintaining and updating the incident management process and communication & Escalation matrix.•Actively ensure appropriate administrative, physical and technical safeguards are in place to protect Majorel Egypt’s information assets from internal and external threats.•Thoroughly conduct and complete annual reviews and audits as required engaging both internal business partners across the organization and external resources.• Make it a priority to manage the disaster recovery and emergency operating procedures and test on a regular basis.•Passionately manage and assist in performing on-going security monitoring of information systems including assessing information security risk through qualitative risk analysis on a regular basis, conducting functional and gap analyses to determine the extent to which key business areas and infrastructure comply with statutory and regulatory requirements, evaluating and recommending new information security technologies and counter-measures against threats to information or privacy, and developing security reports and dashboards.•Ensure effective staff training programs are in place to increase security awareness across Majorel Egypt.','•University degree/College diploma in the field of computer science and/or information security is necessary.•3-5+ years’ information security related work experience.•Possess over the top problem solving and negotiation skills•Demonstrate an in-depth knowledge of Information Security risk and industry best practices.•Be aware of, mitigate enterprise risk factors, and ensure compliance with applicable regulations, legislation and Majorel Egypt policies and procedures.• Be willing to work flexible hours including evenings and weekends as the job demands and travel as required','2023-09-01',9,4,1,4,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Majorel Egypt',NULL),('IT Help Desk Specialist','Egypt','Alexandria','San Stefano','Main Responsibilities•Provide On-site support for technical issues via logged tickets, emails, or phones.•Provide physical support for any activities related to server maintenance, backup, and upgrades.•Deploy and manage storage devices and miscellaneous peripherals.•Manage Asset Tracking to reflect accurate data for new deployments, re-assignments, and returned equipment.•Support for AV equipment and handle video calls support.•Provide technical support for internal/external events such as annual meetings, Board meetings, trainings.•Manage external vendors.•Follow standard Onsite Support processes and procedures.•Perform hardware and software installations & updates.•Troubleshoot desktops, laptops, IP phones, printers and networks problem.•Handling appropriate escalations within the agreed service level of the requests.•Escalate issues or outages & unresolved problems to a higher level of support or the dedicated teams.•Provide essential online security advice and support•Following up on open tickets until closure.•Generate the daily required reports via the applications.•Keep company vision, mission, values and follow all policies and procedures.•Performs miscellaneous job-related duties as assigned.','Competencies and professional background Educational Background:•BS degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or equivalent. Technical Skills: : (knowledge, experiences, IT tools/software, languages)•Level of English: Good Level.•Experience in IT 2-years minimum•Expert in MS Windows 10 troubleshooting•Expert in knowledge of O365 troubleshooting•Expert in Hardware support•Good knowledge of Network basic troubleshooting. Soft Skills•Excellent verbal & written communication•Excellent analytical skills to troubleshoot technical issues•Exceptional problem-solving skills.•Excellent organizational and time management skills.•Interpersonal & presentation skills.','2023-09-01',16,2,0,2,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Majorel Egypt',NULL),('Senior Software Sales Representative','Egypt','Cairo','','About the job: We are expanding our team at Makan E and we are looking to hire a talented Sales Representative- Ecommerce. The ideal candidate will be Client experience-oriented with high communication skills and an efficient set of skills in problem-solving. The job responsibilities and qualifications for the vacancy are as follows: Job Description Identify potential clients and prospects through research and networking Develop and execute sales strategies to meet or exceed sales targets Build and maintain relationships with customers Understand customer needs and recommend appropriate software solutions Conduct product demonstrations and presentations to potential clients Negotiate and close deals with customers Maintain accurate and up-to-date sales records and reports Collaborate with other sales team members to achieve team goals ','Job Requirements4+ years of experience in sales, preferably in e-commerce or technology companies is a mandatory Familiarity with CRM tools and sales automation software is a plus Strong understanding of software products and the software industry Excellent communication and interpersonal skills Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales targets Ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to achieve common objectives Fluent in English and Arabic, both written and verbal','2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,4,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'MakanE Company',NULL),('Agri-Tech Chief Engineer/Engineering Director','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Agri-Tech Chief Engineer/Engineering Director About the job: My client is an innovative startup that provides cutting-edge technological solutions for food and water security in Qatar and GCC countries. They are looking for an experienced head of engineering to lead a pioneering project in designing a portable vertical farm of the new generation. You will be part of the senior leadership team and report to the CPO. You will be responsible for helping to pick project contractors, developing, and designing the layout of the vertical farm with subordinate assistance and managing its assembly. You will be responsible for the supervision of the project from its inception to completion. For this role they are considering both contract and permanent placement candidates depending on whether the employee will decide to remain at the company after the project\'s completion or not. Necessary key requirement for a candidate Engineering experience in design and commissioning of a vertical farms for cultivation. Responsibilities: Supervise a highly specialized Engineering project in Vertical Farming Design from scratch the layout of a multifunctional vertical farm for growing different types of lettuce. Lead the team of subordinary engineers and manage all stages of product\'s assembly. Conduct maintenance and support at the final stage of the product assembly Oversee the key project processes, performance reports, data, and analysis. Conduct research and analysis of large data sets in regards of supplier’s technological solutions for constituent parts of the farm. Determine anticipated level of security of the final model based on the parameters and characteristics of the containers supplied by foreign contractors. Provide engineering thought leadership in the fields of automation and production design – think creatively and proactively. Proactively identify external resources when needed, facilitate contractual relationships, and integrate external resources into development teams. Develop the design of high capital projects in conjunction with corporate engineering. Improve the automation, safety, quality, reduce costs, improve production efficiencies. Work in tandem with the Chief Product Officer, Operations and Quality Managers, review and monitor quality and process improvements.','Skills\nQualifications:﻿Design of vertical farms based on 40ft containers or other modular solutions Engineering Degree or related degree.3 + years of engineering experience within the Agriculture Industry and Vertical Farming Specialization in multi-spectrum vertical farms to grow a wide range of agricultural products is a huge advantage. Demonstrable project leadership/management experience in vertical farming Actual experience in delivering 2-3 projects from start to finish in the relevant field. A proven track record of project management success in Agro-Engineering Ability to provide assistance in Strategy and Budget planning of high-cost projects. Ability to collaborate as a member of a senior-level innovation think-tank. Continuous Improvement experience is required. Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite or related software.','2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('Business Analyst','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Our client is a global leader in the Automotive Industry, and we are looking to hire a Business Analyst. Main Responsibilities: To collect, manage, analyze, and report Macro/Micro Economic factors, Motorcycle market, and Motorcycle sales trend in each country as well as sales performance to expand the Motorcycle sales. Responsible for systematically organizing the market information and persuasively reporting the qualitative and the quantitative outcome Logically analyze the market situation through both online (websites) and offline (actual sites).•Systematically organize the collected information as to utilize as the management decision. Assess sales performance and formulate countermeasures wherever applicable.','Skills\nKnowledge, skills, and experience required :• Fluent in English and in Arabic language or French language is also preferable.• Ability to undertake travel without restrictions in Africa and the Middle East region. • Proficient PC skills including Microsoft Excel, Power Point, Word, and general PC high-level knowledge• Be passionate about the Motorcycle industry and sales in particular• Ability to organize work under pressure and effectively priorities to meet tight deadlines.','2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('DLP Engineer','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job description Our client is looking for a talented Symantec DLP Engineer whose duty will be to operate and finetune DLP solution, day to day operation for modifying policies, following compliance guidelines, troubleshooting and software upgrade. Job requirements Responsibilities DLP solution administration Analyze DLP incidents and report on finding false positives or true negative. Work closely with Infrastructure team, network security team for maintains DLP servers. Creating policies for email, web and endpoint based on data protection. Create Incident report on monthly basis. Creating profiling based on documents and established policies. Demonstrate presentation on-going project milestone achievements. Maintain Oracle database and incident purging. Monitoring all DLP endpoint agents on daily.','Skills\nQualifications & Skills Bachelor’s degree in information security or IT-related matter or equivalent experience. Saudi National are preferred.2 years of experience on DLP solution. Certification on Symantec DLP. Understanding of information security concepts and related technology. Very good presentation skills. Excellent organizational skills in enterprise support. Excellent communication and training skills. Outstanding customer handling, friendly and goal-oriented.','2023-10-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('IT Software/System Integration Coordinator','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Responsibilities:﻿As IT support analyst, you will be responsible for Support & Maintenance of IT systems portfolio in affiliate, building constructive relationship with IT product owners and business functions, diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve registered issues with agreed SLAs within your own capacity (L1/L2) or via coordination with vendors (L3/4). Detailed responsibilities listed below: Support & Maintenance: Register, Diagnose, Troubleshoot, and resolve L1/L2 system related issues, providing timely and effective solutions while coordinating closely with vendors and business stakeholders. Support Monitoring & Vendor management: Monitor the list of all open tickets and work with vendors on issues’ resolution within defined SLAs. Documentation: Maintain up-to-date system documentation, including user guides, best practices, and technical notes. Feedback Loop: Collaborate closely with the IT product owners to provide feedback on potential improvements or adjustments based on user feedback and system analytics. Security & Compliance: Ensure that user permissions, roles, and profiles are maintained appropriately, keeping in line with our company\'s data security and compliance guidelines. Continuous improvement: Regular revisions of existing support process and suggest recommendations on how to improve it further.','Skills\nDesired Skills and Experience:﻿University degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or equivalent Good command of written and spoken English. Experience in IT in a large multinational company or company being service provider to multinational company4 years+ experience in IT Support role with additional emphasis on multiple integrated systems. Experience in supply chain, LSP, POS, and ERP related systems is a plus. At least one year of experience for vendor management Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work under pressure Exceptional communication skills, with the ability to translate complex technical issues in an understandable manner Ability to work independently, assertive, process oriented, self-driven Ability to think “outside the box” and a ”quick learner”Knowledge of ITIL or other IT service management frameworks is advantageous.','2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('IT Support Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Support: Provide first line of support on Infrastructure, Cybersecurity, Apps, Telecommunication, and collaboration solutions within the respective site. Provide support to the digital operations team to maintain the core Infrastructure, Cybersecurity, Apps, Telecommunication, and collaboration solutions at the respective site.  Provide all technical support during the installation, configuration, and rollout phase. Provide computer help desk support in resolving PC, printer, and network problems either directly or Remotely with end-users. Monitor and maintain computer systems and networks. Responding in a timely manner to service issues and requests Basic knowledge of Active DirectoryØ  Repair and replace parts/equipment, as necessary. Troubleshoot hardware and software problems by running diagnostics, documenting problems, and resolutions, and assessing the impact of issues.  Prioritize and manage many open cases at one time. Manage the stock of equipment, consumables, and other supplies. Manage user accounts, and emails, assign rights and access to the digital services. Upgrade, install, and configure computer hardware, software, systems, networks, printers, CCTV, etc. to meet the objectives of the adoption and support unit. Troubleshoot system and network problems, diagnose and solve hardware or software faults, document problems, and resolutions, and assess the impact of issues.  Maintain availability, performance, integrity, and security of digital systems within the site. Check Security logs from (Servers firewalls, switches, routers, etc.), monitor network traffic, run virus scans, and ensure security patches are up to date to avoid security breaches. Analyze incidents, resolve and/or escalate the issues received to ensure the proper resolution. Manage user accounts, and emails, assign rights and access to the digital system and services. Provide the required awareness and training to the end user to ensure the proper use of digital systems and services.','Skills\nCOMPETENCIES: Up-to-date knowledge of the latest IT and software trends Strong technical background in IT systems and support Sound problem-solving and decision-making skills Good knowledge on cybersecurity Ability to quickly establish good working relationships with end users. Ability to prioritize the workload.  Ability to work well in a team. Flexible and open to change  Excellent communication and time management Skills. Willingness to travel when necessary. Minimum Qualifications: Degree in IT/computer science. Minimum Experience:2+ years total experience in IT support.','2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('PRE-OPENING PROJECT MANAGER”.','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Our client is a leading Bakery & Confectionary manufacturing company in UAEWe are looking to recruit a Pre-opening Project Manager Primary Responsibilities will include preparing the store for its grand opening by ensuring that all merchandise is in stock and merchandised in an attractive manner. Job Responsibility:1. Developing a pre-opening timeline before the store opens.2. Setting up the store which includes everything from arranging displays to setting up the point[1]of-sale system to installing security systems.3. Need to develop a budget and timeline for ordering inventory to setting up the store layout. 4. Active search for objects according to the company\'s criteria, obtaining the most favorable rental conditions.5. Commercial assessment of the location. (For the profit of future stores) 6. Conducting negotiations at the level of top officials, signing contracts.7. Communication with related departments of the company for the opening of the store.8. Control of project execution and compliance with the construction schedule.9. Selection of contractors for the project execution.','Skills\n Desired Candidate Profile﻿1. Minimum 5 Years’ experience in a similar position.2. Knowledge and network of vendors contractors in UAE3. Excellent Written and Verbal communication skills','2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('Project Manager - IT Infrastructure','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Principal responsibilities:﻿Build strong relationships with senior stakeholders within IT, Global Businesses, Finance Work closely with their respective Portfolio Manager, the Global CTO PPM Practice team and their senior stakeholders to ensure alignment of their project/programme with the wider change portfolio and group strategy, values and behaviour Provide board level overview of progress, lead and direct multidisciplinary teams across all global businesses, global functions and regions Lead end to end execution and responsibility for all aspects of the project/programme, including definition, planning, execution & implementation, governance & control, financial, resource and change management. Provide financial analysis, including being able to contextualise financial data into business activities and conclusions Ensure the adherence to financial processes and procedures at project/programme level, as set and communicated by CLIENT Group, regulators and CTO PPM Practice. Own the identification and escalation of any budgetary related risks, issues and opportunities to portfolio/function as appropriate. Act as inspirational role model for the CTO PPM colleagues and line managers and contribute to developing its leadership talent and resourcing strategies. These efforts will help position CLIENT as top provider of CTO services in each of its primary markets and achieve maximum profitability and growth.','Skills\nTo be successful in the role, you should meet the following requirements﻿: University degree is a must. Outstanding project and programme management experience which include communications capabilities, decision making and problem solving skills, lateral thinking, analytical and interpersonal skills. Excellent understanding and proven experience of Programme and Project Management methodologies including Waterfall and Agile. Proven experience of positive, challenging interactions with Senior Executives across the business. Outstanding interpersonal and communication skills with a proven ability to communicate effectively and confidently at all levels across the Group. Change agent with proven ability of implementing large scale organizational, procedural, technology and people related change programmes. Proven ability to articulate complex issues concisely and in simple language to recognize to the global remit of this role. Strong financial analytical background and proven ability in financial/analytical reasoning, including being able to contextualise financial data into business activities and conclusions. Experience of delivering large scale change programmes within a Technology organization, with Infrastructure experience. High level of drive and motivation to ensure delivery of a broad range of outputs simultaneously across CLIENT. Experience of leading and managing teams with proven track record of working with diverse, cross functional teams that are located regionally and worldwide.  Experience of driving continuous improvement.','2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('Project Manager - SKID','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','DESCRIPTIONOur client is looking for an energized and capable professional for the role of a Project Manager - Skids. Purpose of the Job Manage planning and execution of Modular Skids (CI Skids, HIPPS, etc.) Projects from job award to delivery within scope, schedule, and budget Principal Responsibilities / Accountabilities Prepare project budget and plan. Organize project execution team for the modular skid projects Prepare a project execution plan indicating the project organization, roles, and responsibilities of the project team. Collate Engineering, Procurement, QA-QC documents for client submission. Manage project procurement and find creative solutions for cost optimization Coordinate with Engineering, Production, Procurement, and QA-QC for availability of materials, manpower, inspection, and fabrication activities as per schedule/plan. Coordination with client and their engineering consultant for approval of basic/detailed engineering documents, and resolution of technical queries. Coordinate with the Engineering team to finalize the SDRL document list and planning at the beginning of the project. Define the KPIs for the team and monitor & implement the effective integrated key milestone plan for timely project delivery. Review and approval of the Project plan and schedule. Track and monitor scope change with reference to the scope of work. Project review: organize and conduct internal and external project review meetings and monitor action lists. Project reporting: Circulate weekly/Monthly Project reports and appraise management on project status and escalate major issues if any. Responsible for complete customer satisfaction (as a minimum) and customer relation (at best)Responsible for Customer / End User’s complaints and feedback','Skills\nREQUIREMENTSEducation Bachelor\'s degree in Mechanical or Chemical engineering from an accredited institute Professional experience of 12-15 years minimum Minimum of 5 - 8 years of project management experience in modular skids projects Minimum 5 years of working experience in UAESkills/Competencies Excellent verbal and written English & knowledge of Arabic would give an edge Excellent leadership skills Good communication, negotiation and interpersonal skills Decision making quality based upon analysis, wisdom, experience, and judgment In-depth knowledge and understanding of project planning, process optimization and information management systems Practical experience of bringing manufacturing excellence for repeatability, productivity and cost effectiveness Experience of establishing manufacturing and execution processes for large scale manufacturing with quality and efficiency Excellent Vendor management skill Customer centric and have strong experience of managing customers globally','2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('Salesforce Analyst','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Responsibilities:﻿As Salesforce analyst, you will be responsible for Support & Maintenance of IT systems portfolio in affiliate, building constructive relationship with IT product owners and business functions, diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve registered issues with agreed SLAs within your own capacity (L1/L2) or via coordination with vendors (L3/4). – Salesforce Service Cloud and Salesforce Commerce Cloud. Detailed responsibilities listed below: Support & Maintenance: Register, Diagnose, Troubleshoot, and resolve L1/L2 Salesforce.com related issues, providing timely and effective solutions with understanding business’ needs and conducting analysis on how to increase support experience. Support Monitoring & Vendor management: Monitor the list of all open tickets and work with vendors on issues resolution within defined SLAs. Documentation: Maintain up-to-date system documentation, including user guides, best practices, and technical notes. Feedback Loop: Collaborate closely with the IT product owners to provide feedback on potential improvements or adjustments based on user feedback and system analytics. Security & Compliance: Ensure that user permissions, roles, and profiles are maintained appropriately, keeping in line with our company\'s data security and compliance guidelines. Contininious improvement: Regular revisions of existing support process and suggest recommendations on how to improve it further.','Skills\nDesired Skills and Experience:﻿University degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or equivalent Good command of written and spoken English Experience in IT in a large multinational company or company being service provider to multinational company4 years+ experience in IT Support role4 years+ experience with Salesforce.com products (especially SFSC and SFCC)At least one year of experience for vendor management Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work under pressure Exceptional communication skills, with the ability to translate complex technical issues in an understandable manner Strong communication skills, work independence, assertiveness, process orientation, self-driven Ability to think “outside the box” and a ”quick learner”Knowledge of ITIL or other IT service management frameworks is advantageous Knowledge of following tools: Jira, Service Now, Confluence Team: no direct reports Contract: opportunity to extend the contract in the future Budget: 15,000 AED / month','2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'ManpowerGroup Middle East',NULL),('IT Help Desk Specialist - 10th of Ramadan','Egypt','Cairo','10th of Ramadan City','Receive request by Internal program and solve the request by priority. Work on the call remotely or move to help the user physically if needed. Participate in team meeting to manage upgradingdeployment any requested software. Provide investigation, diagnosis, resolution and recovery for hardware/software problems as applicable. Provide basic network troubleshooting, when unable to resolve, escalate to second level support either inside Mantrac or with the ISP directly. Manage service requests, software installations, new computer setup, upgrade, etc. Basic Hardware replacement using the available items in IT store Maintaining the inventory by checking and update the inventory with all computer and user\'s details.','BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science or relevant field. Hands-on experience as an IT Help Desk Rep. or similar Fluent English Language proficiency. Basic understanding of CCTV, Access Control, Intrusion and Networks. Strong written and verbal communication skills. Strong personality; maintaining order and dealing with confrontation.','2023-10-01',208,18,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Mantrac',NULL),('Web Developer','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Web Developer shall be responsible for the coding, innovative design and layout of multiple industries websites. Web developer responsibilities include building websites from concept all the way to completion from the bottom up, fashioning everything from the home page to site layout and function. The Web developer shall answer clients’ business needs by translating the design requirements and desired functionality of websites into the code that delivers them.  ','Proven working experience in web programming Top-notch programming skills and in-depth knowledge of modern HTML/CSSFamiliarity with at least one of the following programming languages: PHP, ASP. NET, or Javascript A solid understanding of how web applications work including security, session management, and best development practices Adequate knowledge of relational database systems, Object Oriented Programming and web application development Hands-on experience with network diagnostics, network analytics tools Basic knowledge of the Search Engine Optimization process Aggressive problem diagnosis and creative problem-solving skills Strong organizational skills to juggle multiple tasks within the constraints of  timelines and budgets with business acumen Ability to work and thrive in a fast-paced environment, learn rapidly and master diverse web technologies and techniques. BS in computer science or a related field','2023-10-01',1,0,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Marketopia',NULL),('Product Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Suppose you have superior communication skills, goal-oriented behavior, and eagerness to win. Well, today is the day you cash in on these skills! We are looking for an enthusiastic Product Manager to join our growing Product team. As a software product manager, your primary responsibility is to oversee the development and management of software products from inception to launch. You will work closely with development teams, designers, and stakeholders to ensure that the product is delivered on time, within budget, and meets the needs of the target market. Whom should you be to succeed in this opportunity? Ideally, you would be a big thinker who sees beyond what’s available to you; more than resources and tools, you will look for opportunities to rip apart the current status quo and develop a solid plan to make it happen. You will be a champion in bringing value to customers with your strategic thinking, by knowing how your product stands against competitors and how to place it on the market. You would obtain superior communication skills and be able to break down technical information in a way that you can explain it to your mom, or your customers, who may not always be technical. As a product manager It’s also important for you to be empathetic to the feelings of other people around you. This includes your team and your customers. It starts with the customers, your stakeholders, as you must be able to get their pain points, why they have them, and come up with a good solution on how to solve them. About Marn: Marn is a technology company established in 2017. It was acquired by Jahez International Group recently. The company develops Point of Sale (POS) software integrated with payment services to provide a one-stop solution for businesses in F&B, Retail, Entertainment, and Services. Marn grew massively in the past two years and continues to accelerate the growth of its customer base. Here at Marn, we aspire to become close friends working together towards disrupting the industry. We plan to accomplish our vision & mission via a strong desire to win, embrace mistakes, and make bold moves. We rely on radical candor in our learning to never repeat the same mistakes. We care personally, yet challenge directly. Being part of Marn, you should expect to make mistakes, be challenged while challenging others, and WIN big. What You\'ll Do: You will be a wizard in conducting market research and identify areas of opportunity for new software products. You will be a champion in understanding Marn’s software, the competition, the buyer\'s persona, Marn’s value proposition, and market dynamics. Use the knowledge you have about Marn, its customers, and its market to develop a product vision, strategy, and roadmap. Work closely with Marn’s cross-functional teams to develop and launch software products ensuring all customer needs are met. Define and prioritize product features and requirements. Create and maintain product documentation, including user guides and release notes. Monitor product performance and make data-driven decisions to improve product features and user experience. Work with development teams to ensure that products are delivered on time and within budget. Act as the voice of the customer and advocate for their needs throughout the product development processes. Be a consultant of prospective clients via understanding their needs, then close with them only if Marn can satisfy their needs 100%. Requirements & Skills: Bachelor\'s degree in computer science, engineering, or a related field 3+ years of experience in software product management. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills. Ability to work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment. Experience with agile development methodologies. Familiarity with software development tools such as JIRA and Trello Knowledge of software development lifecycle (SDLC) processes and methodologies Experience working with cross-functional teams.',NULL,'2023-10-15',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Marn',NULL),('Senior Business Analyst','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Works with the technology and business groups to define product specifications. Understanding product objectives and capturing business requirements through active listening & questioning techniques. Analysis of stakeholder activities to understand their strengths and weaknesses to determine opportunities to automate processes and functions. Translates complex business, functional and technical requirements into detailed work tasks and prepares product scope statements. Develops innovative solutions for customers’ requirements. Prepares detailed analysis documents with defined and appropriate techniques for functional and non-functional requirements. Participates in the lifecycle development process of product definition through design, development, test, release, and maintenance. Supports developers and QC engineers by clarifying requirements or business concerns generated anytime within the lifecycle development process. Understanding the dynamic market needs and provide inputs for additional features for existing products. Communicates effectively with business development teams’ insights and supports cross-functional team members and management. Perform product demos to customers and develop relationships in key clients. Staying up to date on the latest process and IT advancements to automate and modernize systems. Participates in planning assigned tasks durations (WBS).','Banking software industry background is a must. Knowledge of software technology, computer programming experience, and business knowledge. Proficient in Microsoft Office programs (Access, Excel, Project, Power Point, etc.) and Software Design Tools. Ability to elicit and document functional requirements, write specifications, use cases, user stories, and design user interface requirements for products. Basic concepts of Programming. Understand fundamentals of software development processes and procedures. Experience with iterative development and agile/scrum. Very good English writing/reading and verbal skills. Strong attention to detail and multi-tasking skills. Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Positive attitude even under high pressure and stressful situations Be aware of the payment market needs and innovation and suggest innovative opportunities to help the business grow. A solid leadership skill.','2023-10-01',0,0,7,10,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Masria Digital Payment (MDP)',NULL),('IT Sales Executive','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','1- Identifying potential customers through networking initiatives, cold-calling, and email communications.2- Contact & follow up new leads.3- Setting meetings with clients.4- Giving sales presentations to a range of prospective clients.5- Identifying potential clients to evaluate needs or promote products and services.6- Preparing weekly and monthly reports. ','1- Bachelor degree in computer science or relevant 2- 1 to 2 years experience in the same field  3- Very good command of Arabic and English.4- Outstanding communication & negation skills.5- Ability to build relationships with clients and manage accounts effectively','2023-10-09',0,0,1,2,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Mass Technology',NULL),('IT Help Desk','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Max Muscle Elite for Supplements Now is hiring#IT_Help_Desk Location: New Cairo Job brief: We are looking for an excellent Help desk technician that must have good technical knowledge and be able to communicate effectively to understand the problem and explain its solution. They must also be oriented and patient in dealing with problems. Responsibilities:• Providing first-level support through taking calls and supporting Service Requests .• Installing and troubleshooting computer hardware, software, systems, networks, printers, and scanners.• Install, configure, and manage software and its functions according tospecifications.• Repair and recover from software failures.• Following-up LAN(local area network) and WAN (Wide Area Network).• Develop and maintain the local network.• Manage routers and configure them ( Wlan, DHCP, Port mapping, Port forward, public Ip ) for all branches.• Repair any network failure and follow up with ISP .• Make a Periodic visit to all Branches and Wearhouse.• Set up new surveillance ( CCTV Cameras and DVR ).• Solving problems for all employers• Responding in a timely manner to service issues and requests.• Creating incidents and service desk tickets in the system and helping other IT colleagues with inventory and other IT-related work.• Providing technical support across the company’s branches.• Keeping the inventory of the IT hardware up to date.  ','• Males Only• BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science, or a relevant field• Excellent communication skills• From 1 to 2 Years of experience in the IT Field.• Basic Knowledge of Sophos• Basic Knowledge of Microsoft 365• Proven experience as a help desk technician or other customer support role.• Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues.• Preferred certified CCNA -MCSA- Linux - Firewall\'s at least experience and awareness• Advanced knowledge in Network Troubleshooting & Microsoft office...• English Language: Very good writing, Speaking, and reading. Prefer (Nasr City - New Cairo - Masr el gedida - Mokattam - Maadi ) Residents','2023-09-01',46,0,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'Max Muscle',NULL),('IT Assistant','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Proven work experience as a senior administrative assistant, virtual assistant or executive administrative assistant In-depth understanding of office management and daily operations Hands on experience with MS Office Working knowledge of office equipment, like printers and fax machines Excellent verbal and written communication skills Strong organizational and time-management skills High School degree; additional qualification as a personal assistant or secretary will be a plus',NULL,'2023-10-17',19,8,5,9,8000,12000,0,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Mazar construction',NULL),('IT Specialist','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','-Provide technical assistance and support for incoming queries and issues related to computer systems, software, and hardware.-Install, modify computer hardware , software and POS peripherals in the stores Clean up computers.-Provide technical advice and assistance to office staff as needed-Design and generate reports as requested-Responsible for maintenance and backup of internal development servers','Bachelor’s degree . Microsoft Windows Operating systems knowledge  Microsoft Office knowledge Network principals knowledge ( network devices / IP Configurations / Troubleshooting) ','2023-10-16',8,6,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Mazaya',NULL),('Senior PHP Developer','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','This person uses expertise and experience to product development work on a wide variety of web projects. Working with confidence and professionalism, they will maintain high standards ensuring the quality of web development services delivered to our clients. With responsibility for the quality of work they produce, they will be accountable for the delivery of projects according to agreed timescales as well as ensuring code is well constructed, secure, and suitable for the specific application. Duties & Responsibilities Understand and implement project management practices Create website back-ends and web services using open-source technologies, particularly PHP. Integrate back-ends with existing front-ends, using HTML / CSS / AJAX as needed Participate in the development process from specification and design through build to testing, release, and maintenance. Break down problems into viable actionable chunks, and solve them with clarity and precision. Deliver projects according to agreed timescales. Handle some basic website-related administrative duties, e.g. SSL and DNS management. Interact with the client to create technology specifications from business requirements for modules within the project. Monitor development activities and report project progress. Manage, mentor, and provide technical guidance/support to project teams. Review/Improve upon current processes/methodologies. HR & Admin Department. Improve the technical competence of the team through training & development of existing and new team members.','Good foundation in programming skills, with strong skills in at least one language.4-6 years of experience in creation of web applications. Excellent understanding of PHP frameworks (laravel). Experience of server-side programming for web. Knowledge of PHP and ability to self-teach as required on the job, with support from the Technical Director. Analytical and methodical with strong problem-solving skills. Enthusiastic, with a desire to learn and expand knowledge. Self-starter able to make progress with minimal supervision seeks help when required. Ability to work with minimal supervision Excellent problem solver, specifically within the domain of software development Enjoys programming Excellent oral and written communication skills Understanding of security vulnerabilities in the software stack, and familiarity with risk mitigation strategies Diligent with time management','2023-10-01',36,5,4,6,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Mc Ledger',NULL),('Business Analyst Intern','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','','Who You\'ll Work With You will join one of our offices around the world for ~10 weeks, usually in the summer, to work in teams and directly with our clients. In this role, you will help our clients in the private, public, and social sectors solve some their most pressing problems. You will also work with a range of experts in the firm, from data scientists to researchers to software and app designers. What You\'ll Do You\'ll work in teams of typically 3 - 5 consultants, to identify, and oftentimes implement, potential solutions for a specific client problem or challenge. Together, you will help clients make lasting improvements to their performance and realize their most important goals. Over the course of each project, you will gather and analyze information, formulate and test hypotheses, and develop and communicate recommendations. You\'ll also present results to client management and implement recommendations in collaboration with client team members. Some examples of the specific work may include interviewing clients, leading client teams, building financial models, and working with Mc Kinsey subject experts to develop perspectives and insights for the client. Depending on your area of focus or client needs, you will be asked to travel to your client site. When you join Mc Kinsey, you are joining a firm whose culture is distinctive and inclusive. We will accelerate your development as a leader to create positive, enduring change in the world. As a business analyst intern, you will receive training and coaching on how to better: Structure ambiguous problems and take action to solve them Synthesize complex information into clear takeaways and recommendations using both qualitative and quantitative methods Work effectively with diverse teams to come up with the best solution and move people and organizations to act Establish trust-based relationships with clients to better serve their organizations Communicate effectively with all audiences, including senior leaders, in a structured manner Develop your leadership style, leveraging your own passions, strengths, and personal values Mc Kinsey believes in strengths-based development and coaching, and you\'ll receive frequent mentoring from colleagues. This will include a senior colleague from your office or practice who will help you grow and achieve your career goals. Additionally, you will have a professional development manager who manages staffing to help you choose projects based on your priorities as well as the needs of client service teams. Our business analyst intern program gives a group of undergraduate students and eligible graduate students first-hand experience with consulting at Mc Kinsey. At the end of your internship, you may receive an offer to join us as a full-time business analyst after the completion of your degree. Qualifications In your junior year of an undergraduate degree; with an expected graduation dates between December 2024 - August 2025Junior year of your undergraduate degree or second year of your non-M. B. A masters Or in your senior/final year of undergraduate studies and planning to enter a one-year master\'s program (in some geographies) Or currently completing your first year in a non-business, 2-year master\'s program and have less than 2 years of work experience  Or are in your first year of a two year commitment with Teach for America and have 3 years or fewer of work experience to date  Ability to work collaboratively in a team and create an inclusive environment with people at all levels of an organization  Capability to drive an independent workstream in the context of a broader team project  Comfort with ambiguous, ever-changing situations  Ability to break down and solve problems through quantitative thinking and analysis  Ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing, in English and local office language(s) ',NULL,'2023-10-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'McKinsey & Company',NULL),('IT Technical Support','Egypt','Sharqia','Alsalihiyyah Aljadidah','     Maintain helpdesk support and resolve problems to the end user’s satisfaction.▪       Check and respond quickly and effectively to requests received through the IT helpdesk.▪       Check service desk for tickets assigned to the queue and process first-in first-out based on priority.▪       Check configurations, utilities, software default settings, etc. for the local workstation.▪       Ensure each workstation has a computer, monitor, keyboard, mouse, hard drive, and any additional specialized equipment.▪       Install, test and configure new workstations, peripheral equipment and software.▪       Review inventory of all equipment, software and software licenses.▪       Follow up issues for escalation and check as appropriate.▪       Coordinate PC setup and deployment for new employees using standard hardware, images and software.▪       Assign users and computers to proper groups in active directory.▪       Carry out timely workstation hardware and software upgrades as required.▪       Perform other job-related duties as assigned.','B. Sc.  Computer Engineering, Computer Science, or equivalent discipline.','2023-10-04',6,0,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'MCV',NULL),('web developer','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Write well designed, testable, efficient code by using best software development practices. Create website layout/user interface by using standard HTML/CSS practices. Integrate data from various back-end services and databases. Gather and refine specifications and requirements based on technical needs. Create and maintain software documentation. Be responsible for maintaining, expanding, and scaling our site. Stay plugged into emerging technologies/industry trends and apply them into operations and activities. Cooperate with web designers to match visual design intent.','Proven working experience in web programming. Top-notch programming skills and in-depth knowledge of modern HTML/CSSFamiliarity with at least one of the following programming languages: PHP, ASP. NET, Java Script or Ruby on Rails A solid understanding of how web applications work including security, session management, and best development practices. Adequate knowledge of relational database systems, Object Oriented Programming and web application development Hands-on experience with network diagnostics, network analytics tools Basic knowledge of Search Engine Optimization process Aggressive problem diagnosis and creative problem-solving skills. Strong organizational skills to juggle multiple tasks within the constraints of timelines and budgets with business acumen. Ability to work and thrive in a fast-paced environment, learn rapidly and master diverse web technologies and techniques. BS in computer science or a related field','2023-10-11',15,11,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Measuresoft oil and gas Services',NULL),('IT Help Desk','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','will handle incoming technical support requests, troubleshoot issues, and provide timely assistance to end-users. Their presence during morning and evening hours will significantly improve response times and reduce downtime. Manage internet lines (LSD), landline phones, and ADSL services for all office locations. Provide IT helpdesk support and troubleshooting for all hardware, software, and application issues faced by users. Install new applications as needed. Manage printer rental contracts - negotiate prices, and specifications for renewals or new locations. Receive returned and distribute new devices to employees. Deal with access control ZK system and infra. Serve as the first point of contact for customers seeking technical assistance over the phone or email Perform remote troubleshooting through diagnostic techniques and pertinent questions Determine the best solution based on the issue and details provided by customers Walk the customer through the problem-solving process Direct unresolved issues to the next level of support personnel Provide accurate information on IT products or services Record events and problems and their resolution in logs Follow-up and update customer status and information Pass on any feedback or suggestions by customers to the appropriate internal team Identify and suggest possible improvements on procedures','BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science or relevant field2 years + experience as a help desk technician or other customer support role. Ability to work on rotational shifts basis . Their presence during morning and evening hours will significantly improve response times and reduce downtime. Tech savvy with working knowledge of office automation products, databases and remote control Good understanding of computer systems, mobile devices and other tech products Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues Proficiency in English Excellent communication skills Customer-oriented and cool-tempered','2023-10-25',0,0,2,4,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'MedVAlley S.A.E',NULL),('System Administrator','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','   They will oversee the maintenance, configuration, and optimisation of our internal systems, servers, and network infrastructure.   Their expertise will be vital in ensuring the smooth functioning of our hub operations during critical hours. Manage the organization\'s Online Systems (OPS) platform for user account creation and provisioning. (System admin)Manage the organization\'s Odoo platform for user account creation, provisioning, and permissions. Configure modules and customize settings/workflows as needed. Maintain integration with other systems. Create and provision new user accounts based on team/location setup. Manage user profiles, and passwords and assign appropriate security roles. Administer Odoo modules for HR/Payroll, CRM, Project Management, Inventory, Accounting, etc. Configure fields, workflows, and automation. Develop/customize new Odoo apps and business processes as needed. Perform upgrades, testing, and user acceptance testing. Troubleshoot platform issues, optimize performance, backup data and manage overall Odoo infrastructure. Train users, develop documentation, and act as a support contact for Odoo-related queries. Liaise with developers for complex customizations or integrations requiring code-level work. Manage internet lines (LSD), landline phones, and ADSL services for all office locations. Provide IT helpdesk support and troubleshooting for all hardware, software, and application issues faced by users. Install new applications as needed. Manage printer rental contracts - negotiate prices, and specifications for renewals or new locations. Receive returned and distribute new devices to employees. Deal with access control ZK system and infra. Install and configure software and hardware Manage network servers and technology tools Set up accounts and workstations Monitor performance and maintain systems according to requirements Troubleshoot issues and outages Ensure security through access controls, backups and firewalls Upgrade systems with new releases and models Develop expertise to train staff on new technologies Build an internal wiki with technical documentation, manuals and IT policies','BSc/Ba in Information Technology, Computer Science or a related discipline; professional certification (e.g. Microsoft Certified Systems Administrator (MCSA)) is a plus3 years+  experience as a System Administrator, Network Administrator or similar role1 - 3 years  experience with Odoo System . Experience with databases, networks (LAN, WAN) and patch management Knowledge of system security (e.g. intrusion detection systems) and data backup/recovery Ability to create scripts in Python, Perl or other language Familiarity with various operating systems and platforms Resourcefulness and problem-solving aptitude Excellent communication skills','2023-10-25',0,0,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','MedVAlley S.A.E',NULL),('Junior Software Engineer','Egypt','Cairo','Heliopolis','\nThis is a Software Engineering / IT Service Management vacancy. You will mainly work on configuring, customizing, and developing enhancements for Enterprise Solutions from IBM Software Solutions Portfolio.\nThis is a unique opportunity to be part of a leading Global IT organization with real opportunity for career growth.\nThis is a challenging role that will further your IBM Software Implementation skills, your strong team working ethics and your dedication to every client success.\n\nWhat Awaits?\n\nA number of new and exciting projects, opportunities to work on large composite systems and be part of an elite team who is at the cutting edge of implementing IBM solutions, working with prestige clients to deliver value from their Automation and Enterprise Asset Management solutions.\nWorking alongside our talented and widely experienced consultants, you’ll have the opportunity to determine innovative solutions which overcome complex business challenges.\nOn a daily basis, you’ll transform asset management performance and deliver real business improvements for our clients. Whether it is strategy and planning or procurement and maintenance, your advice will help our clients to operate more efficiently and effectively.\nIdeally, you will engage in all key phases of full projects life-cycle from pre-sales activities, implementation and training our customers.\nYou are expected to be able to hit the ground running as a confident and professional communicator who prides themselves on delivery excellence.\nAs well as a motivated and enthusiastic approach, you’ll need plenty of ambition and a talent for teamwork.\n','Candidates must exhibit the following key skills: A strong academic record. A strong IT background. Ability to communicate articulately and effectively at all levels of business. Ability to building excellent client relationships and outstanding communication and presentation skills, ideally client facing. Strong skills in analysis, design and problem-solving. Ability to produce high-quality documentation. Understanding package implementation methodologies. Consistently working as part of a project team focused on client success. Willingness to travel according to the project location. Required: Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Sciences, Computer Engineering or relevant degree. English: Fluent, both spoken and written (Highly Required). Exemption / Completion of military services (for Egyptians). Experience Level: Fresh Graduates or those with 1-2 years of experience. Preferred: Information Systems and Software Engineer Majors. Background in Development (C++, C#, . NET, Java, or Java Script). Background in writing SQL Queries. Experience working with Domains or Development Tools. Basic knowledge of Windows Server Operating Systems. Basic knowledge of Database Concepts. Basic knowledge of Networks.','2023-10-23',0,0,0,2,NULL,NULL,1,4,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','MegaSoft',NULL),('Applications Development Consultant (.NET)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Applications Development Consultant (. NET)\nJob Purpose: Will be responsible for designing, executing, assessing, and troubleshooting software programs and applications which include: configuring, analyzing, designing, coding, developing, unit testing and documenting software specifications throughout the project life cycle. This responsibility will extend to contributing in the estimates of projects, the quality and timeliness of the deliverables and the projects compliance to the organizational processes and standards.﻿Tasks and duties: Developing front end and back end applications and/or systems. Designing and developing APIs. Ensuring cross-platform optimization for mobile phones. Troubleshooting issues in the product (application and data), database server, web server(IIS), and networks, to minimize the risk of disruptions. Ensuring reviews are fully documented and actions are raised and fulfilled Being involved in changes to the service operation tools, processes, and working practices. Coordinating with Product Development and Implementation teams to support product updates. Create security and data protection settings. Build features and applications with a mobile responsive design. Develop, test, and maintain web and web service applications built on open-source technologies. Work closely with the Development team on analysis, requirements gathering and reporting project status. Design, develop, and test applications in accordance with established standards. Prepare reports on the status, operation and maintenance of the software. Participle in any related solution reviews and design codes. Develop and tune integrations between applications. Analyze and resolve technical and application problems. Ensure adherence to our internal procedures regarding Quality, Security, Incident Management, Problem Management, Change Management, and Service Level Management. Provide end-to-end support/operations service to clients through investigation, diagnosis, and fix preparation. To provide the client means to resolve tickets and to provide information and knowledge about the solution. Develop scripts for data rectification for data-related issues cause by a bug in the modules. Find root causes through problem investigation and management to reduce incidents and increase customer satisfaction. Adapt to different processes managing change lifecycle end to end in order to address clients demands and requests as fast as possible.﻿Perform health checks on the application level. Qualifications and skills: Bachelors degree in computer science or computer engineering. Minimum 5 Years of proven work experience, preferably within a technology organization as both a hands-on architect and/or a software engineer. Proven experience as a . NET Developer. Undertaking continuous improvement in the operation. Strong experience and in-depth knowledge of . NET, ASP. NET Core, ASP. NET Razor, ASP. NET MVC, C#. NET, MS SQL Server Strong experience in software Design Patterns (OOP, ), architecture style (SOA, REST, APIs) and architectural patterns (MVC, ) Solid knowledge and experience in Java Script, HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap. Strong Experience with Web Services, WCF, OData, Web API Experience with . NET (Entity Framework) Experience with No SQL databases (Mongo DB, ) is preferable Experience in any one of the modern Java Script frameworks (React.js, Angular.js, Vue.js, ...) Experience with development source control (Git Hub, TFS, ) and CI/CD (Dev Ops, Git Hub Actions) Azure App Services, and Azure Functions are preferable. Strong knowledge of Software Development Life Cycle and Agile methodologies. Excellent command of English language. Very good analytical, creative problem-solving skills and have a keen eye for quality and details. Fair knowledge of Phyton, AI, machine learning concepts is preferable. Good knowledge of Docker or Kubernetes is preferable. Able to write a clean/high-quality code. Experience in SSO. Hands-on unit testing. Good understanding of security and scalability issues. Experience with complex client-side data flows, consuming APIs and JSON. Ability to multi-task, organize, and prioritize work. kendo-UI (Telerik component) is preferable. Mobile development is preferable. Reporting Tools (like: SSRS, Telerik Reporting, Crystal Report,) is preferable. Web Security Standard knowledge (OWASP) is preferable.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Business Systems Integration Manager','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Business Systems Integration Manager\nITS Specialist Business Systems Integration Manager Jobs in Brief: Responsibility for planning, coordinating and testing of business system integration elements of ROMD projects ensuring consistency in testing, performance and data integrity Responsibility for witnessing integration tests on behalf of Client and coordinating any input required from other Client contractors for the testing Support the continued update, review and analysis of the optimum ITS system architecture to meet Clients evolving needs for ITS operations Responsibility for troubleshooting any data sharing issues with Clients stakeholders with regard to the sharing of ITS data Responsibility for preparing and presenting project and progress updates for Client Senior Managers and key Stakeholders Responsibility for coordinating the requirements for testing and implementing systems integration with Client departments and third party contractors Responsibility for managing the integration of ROMD ITS projects and coordinating the integration and handover of Client Project Affairs ITS projects into operation/maintenance Responsibility for reviewing and analysing contractor integration design documentation, test plans and test results Coordinate with the ITS Programme Manager the scheduled activities associated with projects and systems integration and highlight risks and mitigatons for keeping integration activities on track Monitor and report on contractor compliance with the Qatar national ITS Standards, Specifications and deployment guide Focal point for external stakeholders technical queries with regards to sharing data with RMC systems or accessing RMC data feeds Work in collaboration with other disciplines to ensure the integrity of the integration design elements of each project. Lead the resolution of technical issues relating to systems integration and data sharing and provide technical guidance to other team members Maintain on-going communication with relevant stakeholders and sub-contractors to build relationships and communication networks ensuring quality of service. Identify key trends and provide suggestions for improving ITS/ Tunnels System performance and capabilities Work under minimum supervision and competent to check the work of others and supervise less experienced or junior staff Keep up to date with industry best practice and apply best practice to ensure professional development Adhere to Health and Safety policy and procedures and comply with new work instructions Perform other duties / tasks as required Qualification: Minimum Bachelors Degree in Engineering or other relevant subject Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Chartered Membership in Engineering or relevant professional body would be an advantage Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 18 years cumulative experience in a relevant field. Minimum of 10 years experience in ITS area including ITS deployment, systems integration and optimisation Ability to establish strong working relationships with key stakeholders Ability to influence and engage staff at all levels within the organization Competent in Microsoft Office Packages Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is essential Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Control System Engineer (E&P)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Control System Engineer (E&P)\nQualifications Degree in Engineering or Science majoring in Engineering in the area of specialization Knowledge and/or Experience 8 years experience in DCS, Plant Shutdown System within Oil and Gas Environment. Preferrable in Plant Operation Simulator development. Computer literate, with advanced knowledge of all relevant engineering software tools, systems and tools. Fluent in English language (demonstrated verbal and written skills). Key Job Accountabilities ﻿1.	Plan and prepare work activities during the project phase to ensure a smooth completion of planned activities. \n2.	Ensure control system engineering activities are conducted in accordance with company regulatory requirements. \n3.	Ensure that the Engineering documents are reviewed considering Safety in Operabilty / Maintainability  4.	Ensure control system engineering activities during simulator development, model acceptance test (MAT), factory acceptance test (FAT), Installation, commissioning and project close out. \n5.	Provide technical support during installation to to assure safe execution and company compliance. \n6.	Resolve engineering issues that may arise and communicate with the Project Management Team (PMT). 7.	Support other engineers in complex analyses and assignments and provides expertise to ensure completion of activities within schedule.  8.	Mentor the National Developee as per the development plan﻿\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('DEVELOPMENT ENGINEER','Qatar','Doha','','About the job DEVELOPMENT ENGINEER\nJob Description\nThe position report to Dukhan Redevelopment Team Leader. Manage Project Initiation, Feasibility & Early Concept Optimization Studies for Dukhan development projects Work with Onshore Development, Project Engineering & Operations on Studies strategies & plans. Develop and manage the schedule & cost. Manage contracts (including changes and variations) for the Studies Manage review & finalization of Study deliverables. Manage and communicate performance, implement lessons learnt & participate in audits and reviews. Manage transition of projects during and after Studies to Project Engineering. Support engineering definition, operational requirements and philosophies into the project, construction activities, operational readiness and assurance process including commissioning and start-up, handover, and close outs. Identify threats, opportunities, and constraints to the projects, and evaluate risk mitigations Identify and evaluate new technologies. Support pilot projects\nRequired Qualifications, Experience and Expertise: Bachelor\'s degree or higher in Mechanical, Chemical or Petroleum Engineering,15+ years of direct experience in engineering, project management and execution of oil & gas projects Experience in typical upstream facility mechanical/process design principles such as multiphase flow, separator/ pump/compressor capacity evaluation, pipe/valve sizing, hydraulic analysis, etc. Knowledge of process engineering, hydraulic modelling and supporting software Well-developed planning and organization skills, including the ability to work independently, prioritize activities, meet deadlines, and actively manage time in a dynamic work environment',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Head of System Completion COMP1 (F-4480-Q)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Head of System Completion COMP1 (F-4480-Q)\nQualifications Bachelors degree in appropriate engineering discipline Knowledge and/or Experience  15+ years of experience with 5 years at senior system completion supervision level with overall responsibility for systems completion execution. Broad and extensive knowledge in projects execution, engineering, operations, and systems completion. Experience of managing Brownfield Projects and Simultaneous Operations (SIMOPS)Pipeline and subsea skid experiences Demonstrated ability and sensitivity to work with people from a variety of cultural backgrounds Technical and Business Skills Excellent written and spoken English skills. Strong organizational, planning and coordination solving skills. Strong technical, analytical and interface skills. Strong communication, interpersonal and influencing skills. Good time management skills Proficient in Microsoft Office and experience of system completion management systems',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Head Project Controls EPC-2 (N-1965)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Head Project Controls EPC-2 (N-1965)\nJob Description Highlights: The position is located at RLIC site and is responsible to deliver the most cost-effective method of performance for project administration, controls, cost and schedule through timely execution of key activities and compliance with standardized processes.\nBachelor degree in Engineering or Business related subject.\n12 years experience in a major project environment within the oil and gas industry, with exposure in business management including project controls, cost and schedule development, tender preparation and contract management and 3 years supervising multi discipline and multi-cultural teams and as head of control for mega projects.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Head Project Engineer Utilities / Offsite (EPC-1) (N-1606)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Head Project Engineer Utilities / Offsite (EPC-1) (N-1606)\nJob Description Highlights: Provide project management and technical assistance to the EPC-1 Area Division Managers for Utilities and Inlet /Offsites/ He Ru#4/CO2.\nProject management in general, preparation or finalization of technical notes and presentations, transverse coordination with the EPC-1 Project Management Leadership Team, interface coordination and reporting for engineering, procurement, construction, pre-commissioning, commissioning, handover and completion.\nExcellent written and spoken English skills.\nStrong technical and analytical skills.\nGood planning and organisational skills.\nGood influencing and negotiation skills.\nComputer literacy involving the regular use of professional office and technical applications.\nThink out of the box approach technical skills required to successfully perform the role.\nStrong communication and interpersonal skills.\nBachelors Degree in engineering generalist engineer also acceptable. \nMinimum 10 years of experience in multicultural project execution related environment within the oil and gas industry (LNG would be a plus) with proven knowledge and experience of project management, detailed engineering, interfaces management, project controls and planning, construction and commissioning.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('ICSS Lead Utilities EPC-1','Qatar','Doha','','About the job ICSS Lead Utilities EPC-1\nJob Description Highlights: The role is at RLIC site and is responsible to lead Integrated Control and Safety Systems (ICSS) Pre commissioning and Commissioning (PC&C) activities for Onshore Project EPC scopes consisting of Inlets, offsites, CO2, LNG Process and Utilities areas. Provide leadership, support contractors in completions and handover of ICSS scopes by fully complying with project deliverables, project and international standards and standardized processes. Providing clear guidance and facilitate resolution to issues to complete ICSS handover activities by coordinating with Field Engineering, construction, and PC&C Contractor.\nBachelor Degree in Instrument Engineering or equivalent\n15 years experience working in Instrument and Controls, in a Major Oil and Gas Project with broad knowledge of Honeywell experion Control system engineering and field execution including design standards, specifications, codes, Cyber Security criteria, construction and operations. \nPrevious knowledge of Smart Junction Box or similar Technologies preferred.\nRequires demonstrated broad Instruments & Controls equipment and Honeywell systems experience (DCS & SIS, HIPPS, PMS, IAMS, Fire & Gas, System Virtualization, BN system 1 Network) and familiarity with relevant interface requirements and relevant industry codes. \nField commissioning experience desirable.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('ICSS Lead Utilities EPC-1 (N-1884) - 3','Qatar','Doha','','About the job ICSS Lead Utilities EPC-1 (N-1884) - 3\nJob Description Highlights: The role is at RLIC site and is responsible to lead Integrated Control and Safety Systems (ICSS) Pre commissioning and Commissioning (PC&C) activities for North Field Expansion (NFXP) Onshore Project EPC scopes consisting of Inlets, offsites, CO2, LNG Process and Utilities areas. Provide leadership, support contractors in completions and handover of ICSS scopes by fully complying with project deliverables, project and international standards and standardized processes. Providing clear guidance and facilitate resolution to issues to complete ICSS handover activities by coordinating with Field Engineering, construction, and PC&C Contractor.\nBachelor Degree in Instrument Engineering or equivalent\n15 years experience working in Instrument and Controls, in a Major Oil and Gas Project with broad knowledge of Honeywell experion Control system engineering and field execution including design standards, specifications, codes, Cyber Security criteria, construction and operations. \nPrevious knowledge of Smart Junction Box or similar Technologies preferred.\nRequires demonstrated broad Instruments & Controls equipment and Honeywell systems experience (DCS & SIS, HIPPS, PMS, IAMS, Fire & Gas, System Virtualization, BN system 1 Network) and familiarity with relevant interface requirements and relevant industry codes. \nField commissioning experience desirable.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Instrumentation Lead Utilities EPC-1 (N-1881)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Instrumentation Lead Utilities EPC-1 (N-1881)\nJob Description Highlights: Responsible for overseeing Pre-Commissioning & Commissioning activities for assigned Utilities Areas to ensure EPC PC&C Contractor and Subcontractor executes instrumentation activities and delivers systems and subsystems as per agreed planning until completion. Ensures PC&C engineering (preparation), such as systemization, pre-commissioning and commissioning planning, database set-up in coordination with other stakeholder disciplines and company and contractor/subcontractor departments, i.e. planning. \nExcellent written and oral English skills.\nStrong organisational, planning and coordination skills.\nStrong technical, prioritisation and management skills.\nProficient in Microsoft Office suite of software programs, etc. \nBachelors Degree in engineering or equivalent.\nMinimum of 10 years experience as an Instrumentation Commissioning Engineer with a broad knowledge of commissioning planning and execution experience, for Utilities areas or LNG liquefaction facilities or large Oil & Gas facility.\nExperienced pre-commissioning/commissioning large Utilities packages such as Boilers, Steam Turbines, GTGs, HSRGs and field instrumentation such as Smart Transmitters (HART), Smart Junction Boxes, Instrument Asset Management Systems, Fiscal Metering Systems, Tank Gauging, Specialty Analyzers / sampling systems, Gas Chromotographs, Control & On / Off Valves, ESDV, Blowdown Valves and accessories, MOVs, Fire & Gas devices, BMS / Flare Panels and specialty instruments associated with large compressors. \nGood understanding of International (ISA/IEC) Standards and best practices in the areas of Instrumentation installations.\nDemonstrated experience of using Instrument calibration tools and instrument configuration set-ups.\nExpertise in systemization, development of instrumentation pre-comm/comm procedures.\nStrong leadership skills, experience leading contractor teams. \nExperience with Smart Completions database use and set-up desirable.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Electrical Offplots Shared Resource (N-2731-1)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Electrical Offplots Shared Resource (N-2731-1)\nJob Description Highlights: Responsible for overseeing Electrical Engineering activities in Offplots scope for NFE Onshore LNG Project.\nEnsure all technical requirements such as project specifications, data sheets, etc. are in full compliance with project requirements, standardised processes, and delivered to the highest technical quality standards. \nEnsure all technical activities associated with the electrical engineering discipline by the EPC contractor and third parties are executed to NFE Projects specifications and Client LNG requirements.\nCoordinate with Quality and Document Control department to setup a distribution matrix and provide training on review of FRB Books. Estimated around 34,000 Binders.\nLead electrical engineering design and planning activities and ensures EPC contractor develops detailed design in accordance with local regulatory requirements, industry standards, project specifications and any approved variations.\nFamiliar with broad Electrical equipment and systems experience (HV/MV/LV electrical systems design, power system study & relay protection coordination, Power Management Systems (PMS), Electrical Integrated Controls System (ELICS) and large Motors (10MW+), Cathodic Protection, Emergency Generation and Distribution System, Lighting and Small Power distribution and familiarity with relevant manufacturing processes and relevant industry codes.\nStrong skills in English communication, technical and discipline management, influencing, interface skill and proficient in Microsoft Office suite programs. \nBachelor Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent.\nMinimum 10 years experience of Electrical Engineering, preferably in a major LNG Projects. Broad knowledge of engineering execution including design standards, specifications, codes, safety criteria.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Execution (Offshore) - E-1230-Q','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Execution (Offshore) - E-1230-Q\nQualifications Bachelors degree in Mechanical, Chemical or equivalent. Knowledge and/or Experience Total 15+ years of experience in a Offshore Project Execution engaging major FEED and EPC contractors, experience of working in the Offshore fields with Brownfield Projects, Simultaneous Operations (SIMOPS), and debottlenecking of operating facilities with broad experience of projects and engineering. Demonstrated ability and sensitivity to work with people from variety of cultural backgrounds Strong leadership, communication and interpersonal skills. Strong organisational, coordination, planning and interface skills. Good proactivity, negotiating and influencing skills Excellent spoken and written English skills Computer literacy involving the regular use of professional office applications and some technical applications',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Interface NFS EPC-2 (N-1617)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Interface NFS EPC-2 (N-1617)\nJob Description Highlights: Bachelor Degree in Engineering discipline \nMinimum eight (8) years of experience in the oil and gas industry preferably in LNG industry with a minimum of 3 years in a management position.\nIdentify, develop, and lead closure of interfaces for the North Field South (NFS) CLLNG Balance of Plant (BOP) Contract applicable to NFXP EPC-2 project specifically related to Common Corridors owned by RLIC and Client (OPCO).\nEnsure activities (including approvals) and interfaces with RLIC are undertaken in accordance with Project and NFXP EPC-2 Contractors needs in general, and compatible with Project schedule and cost objectives to avoid delays, change orders and claims.\nLead all internal and external Project Interfaces with NFS Onshore Project team, other EPCs (EPC1, EPC2, EPC3, EPC4), RLIC and third-party asset owners to secure alignment and expedite approvals of corridors, crossings, Plans and drawings as required to meet Project objectives.\nLead and coordinate all technical approvals and development of agreements for Land Lease, Corridor Lease, Utilities, Crossings, etc. with RLIC and Client LNG asset owners in a timely manner to ensure project activities are not delayed. \nSupport and provide guidance to NFXP EPC-2 Contractors for interface matters related to RLIC and OPCO approvals. Assist in resolution of technical issues with RLIC and OPCO.\nLead and coordinate design, development, negotiation, interpretation, implementation, and delivery of executed commercial agreements with RLIC and Client LNG asset owners. Coordinate input and support from Client LNG Commercial and Legal for execution of commercial agreements and legal crossing agreements with RLIC and Client LNG asset owners.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Internal Project Interfaces Shared Resources (F-1298-Q)-3','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Internal Project Interfaces Shared Resources (F-1298-Q)-3\nJob Description Highlights: Identify, develop, coordinate, expedite and steward closure of NFPS Compression EPCs (EPC-1/2/3/4/5/6/7/8/9) with initial focus on EPC 1/2/3/8a & 9 in term of Contract Interfaces. Assist Head of Project Interface with respect to the Commercial and Physical interfaces applicable to 9 Compression EPC Contracts and close coordination with the Interface & System Completion Division Manager. Ensures activities (including approvals) and interfaces with all internal and external parties are undertaken in accordance with Projects needs in general, and compatible with Project schedule and cost objectives to avoid delays, change orders and claims. Represent the interests of the NFPS Compression EPCs by attending to all important meetings, including ensuring comprehensive and fully documented actions list and minutes of meeting are prepared and signed by the Parties involved. Support and provide guidance to NFPS EPCs PMT team for interface matters related to the 9 EPCs including assist in resolution of technical issues. Bachelor of Science in Engineering with proven project management and execution experience specifically extensive knowledge of procedures, rules & regulation of Qatar will be added advantage Minimum of fifteen (15) years of experience in the oil and gas industry and preferably offshore project related with a minimum of 5 years in a management position. Proven experience as Discipline Engineer, Project Engineer, Interface Engineer and Interface Head. Excellent oral and written English skills. Able to write Technical reports in English. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Strong leadership skills',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Planning COMP1/3 (F-1210-Q)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Planning COMP1/3 (F-1210-Q)\nJob Description Highlights: The Planning Specialist is responsible for the Project Engineering, Procurement and Construction (EPC) Contract(s) schedule and all aspects of the Progress Measurement System. This includes development, maintenance, monitoring, controlling and integration of the EPC schedule(s) including verification and reporting in addition to ensuring that all activities comply with standardized processes and are delivered to the highest possible standards.\nExperience developing work methods in accordance to established Company policies, directives from Management, schedules and professional engineering standards.\nGood computer literacy skills (Primavera P6, Word, Excel and Power Point).\nHands on working experience in Primavera P6 Version 18 and above.\nGood knowledge of using Primavera Schedule Risk Analysis software for conducting Schedule Risk Analysis.\nBachelors Degree in Business or Engineering \nMinimum of 10 years experience in project scheduling and controls for EPC oil and gas facilities capital projects / operating companies \nThorough and extensive knowledge of project controls principles, theories, and concepts. \nAt least five (5) years site/field scheduling experience.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Planning COMP1/3 Shared Resources','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Planning COMP1/3 Shared Resources\nJob Description Highlights: The Planning Specialist is responsible for the Project Engineering, Procurement and Construction (EPC) Contract(s) schedule and all aspects of the Progress Measurement System. This includes development, maintenance, monitoring, controlling and integration of the EPC schedule(s) including verification and reporting in addition to ensuring that all activities comply with standardized processes and are delivered to the highest possible standards.\nExperience developing work methods in accordance to established Company policies, directives from Management, schedules and professional engineering standards.\nGood computer literacy skills (Primavera P6, Word, Excel and Power Point).\nHands on working experience in Primavera P6 Version 18 and above.\nGood knowledge of using Primavera Schedule Risk Analysis software for conducting Schedule Risk Analysis.\nBachelors Degree in Business or Engineering or Equivalent Experience\nMinimum of 10 years experience in project scheduling and controls for EPC oil and gas facilities capital projects / operating companies \nThorough and extensive knowledge of project controls principles, theories, and concepts. \nAt least five (5) years site/field scheduling experience.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Process/Utilities (F-4212-Q)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Process/Utilities (F-4212-Q)\nJob Description Highlights: Provide Process Engineering subject matter expertise during Detailed Design /EPC phases of the COMP2 project. Leads the process engineering discipline activities for the assigned project (greenfield and brownfield scope). Ensures that technical requirements (e.g. basis of design, simulations, reports, studies project specifications, data sheets, etc.) developed during FEED fully comply with project requirements. Provides Process Engineering direction, guidance and leadership to NFPS COMP2 PMT and CONTRACTOR(s) for work within the assigned area. Develop fit-for-purpose process /technical engineering definition of surface facilities. Effectively collaborates and interfaces with Project team, Contractor, Client stakeholders (Operations, OES, E&P and etc.) as required to ensure that the Topsides and facilities scope of supply is fully integrated and optimized. Provides oversight of the EPC Contractor team and timely review and approval of project deliverables within project budget and schedule. Technical evaluations of multiple EPC tenders for large, capital projects, including risk based evaluation of complex technical issues, which may have a significant commercial impact on project execution, ensuring they are compliant, technically qualified, and consistent with project requirements. Contribute to the development of Qatari employees.\nBachelors or Masters Degree in Chemical/Process engineering\n15 years experience \n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Project Engineering COMP3 (F-4322-Q)-2','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Project Engineering COMP3 (F-4322-Q)-2\nJob Description Highlights: Coordinate various engineering scopes of work required to progress the NFPS Compression project. The role is required to demonstrate understanding of the requirements of FEED and EPC phases, effectively communicating and translating company requirements and data into an efficient delivery from the contractor in compliance with company requirements, standards, specifications and instructions \nBachelor\'s degree in Engineering. \n8 years\' experience in discipline with 3 years demonstrated lead engineer experience in major capital projects in the oil and gas industry. \nRequire previous experience working in a multi-cultural environment and knowledge of offshore EPC contractors, subcontractors and vendors involved in the oil and gas industry.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Quality BGD - Lean Gas Lines (N-1961)-2','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Quality BGD - Lean Gas Lines (N-1961)-2\nJob Description Highlights: The Onshore Lead of Quality BGD - Lean Gas Lines is responsible to oversee the implementation of the Quality Program and verify that all Quality and Non-Destructive Examination (NDE) procedures are established in accordance with project requirements. Perform as Quality Lead for BGD welding engineer for the review Contractor deliverables including Welding Procedure Specifications (WPSs) and Procedure Quality Records (PQRs). \nExperience with multi-national contractors, in particular those involved in the construction of LNG production facilities, \nAssertive Quality management leadership skills. Must be capable of communicating Quality and Welding requirements, results and status throughout Company and contractor management and craft labour levels. \nConsiderable relevant experience in the construction of onshore Oil & Gas installations. Demonstrated sound technical knowledge and extensive experience in welding processes. Expert knowledge in welding of high strength steels and corrosion resistant alloys (CRA) used in oil and gas industry. \nFully conversant with international codes and standards used in oil and gas industry. Well experienced in NDE methods, especially, AUT & RT, specifically intermediate RT on clad materials. Validation of AUT & RT. \nMechanical testing including corrosion and pitting tests. Strong preference given to candidates with prior Qatar Gas or IOC project experiences.\nDegree in Metallurgical/Welding Engineering (or Mechanical Engineering with Welding Engineering). \n15 years experience associated with Welding Quality Control & coordination of Welding activities within the Oil & Gas Construction Industry.\nQualifications in Auditing, Welding & Materials fields are desirable.\nNDT Level-II (RT, UT, PT, MT, AUT), and welding professional qualification (CSWIP, EWE, IWE or AWS) (where equivalent is proposed, evidence of equivalence shall be provided).\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Security and Emergency Response (S-1521) - 3','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Security and Emergency Response (S-1521) - 3\nQualifications Emergency Response related degree /diploma; or 20 years experience in lieu of degree. FEMA Professional Development training suite or equivalent. Tap Root® Advanced Root Cause Analysis training or equivalent. Knowledge and/or Experience Minimum of fifteen (15) years industry relevant HSE experience. International project experience with Tier-1 EPC Contractors or Client, involved in the construction of onshore production facilities (i.e. greenfield and brownfield work). Sound knowledge of the project execution process in large-scale project environments (expenditure >US$ 1 Bn).',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Site Planning EPC-3/4 (N-1217-1)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Site Planning EPC-3/4 (N-1217-1)\nJob Description Highlights: Oversight, monitoring and verification of contractors Site schedule (typically Level 4 and further), schedule performance, progress measurement and reporting.\nDevelop KPIs by interpreting valuable information from contractors deliverables to aid decision making.\nGood organizational, planning and execution skills.\nFluency in English.\nGood Software skills: Primavera P6, Advanced excel; Computer literacy (MS Office, SAP).\nDeveloped coordination and planning skills; Well-developed interpersonal skills with the ability to communicate with several organisational levels.\nBachelors degree in engineering or construction alternatively relevant experience in oil and gas industry.\nMinimum of 10 years of major EPC project experience within the Oil and Gas Industry.\nGood knowledge of LNG construction and commissioning.\nExperience in Primavera P6 scheduling tools and advanced excel.\nKnowledge and hands on of working with large construction data to produce KPIs.\nExpert knowledge of developing schedules, in particular Level 4; understanding of baseline, actual and forecast plans and progress data.\nKnowledge of WBS and rules of credit for progress measurement in all phases of project.\nTeam player, flexible and experienced of working in a diverse team environment.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Static Equipment Shared Resources (F-1247-3-Q)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Static Equipment Shared Resources (F-1247-3-Q)\nJob Description Highlights: Responsible for coordinating all aspects of Static Equipment design, technical and execution definition, including planning for Tendering, Detailed design etc. Ensures technical requirements (e.g. project specifications, data sheets, etc.) developed during FEED are clearly translated into tender documentation. Responsible for static equipment related tender bulletin, technical clarification and evaluation. Responsible for the technical engagement with Supply Department and Execution team. When applicable, responsible for Long Lead Equipment OEMs and Vendors during bid clarifications and technical evaluation, award of LLEs though EPC novation.\'Bachelor Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.15+ years of experience in static equipment design with at least five years in lead position and with minimum 2 major scale projects, preferably offshore project. Added advantage if possess past experience with equipment fabricator. Experience with EPC contractors, sub-contractors and vendors involved in the oil and gas industry Demonstrated ability and sensitivity to work with people from a variety of cultural backgrounds Knowledgeable in Codes & Standards',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Telecom (F-1307,F-1306, F-1288) - 3','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Telecom (F-1307, F-1306, F-1288) - 3\nJob Description Highlights: Leads telecoms activities for North Field Production Sustainability (NFPS) Projects, ensuring EPC Contractor and Telecom System Integrator (TSI) deliver the project that is in compliance with the Project and Cyber Security requirements, provide secure interfaces with third party systems and ensuring that all Telecom systems are in compliance with the industrial Codes and Standards. \nBachelor\'s degree in Engineering \n10 years experience working in telecoms, in large Oil & Gas Facilities having broad knowledge of engineering execution including design standards, specifications, codes, safety criteria, onshore and offshore facilities design, construction and operations. \nConversant with relevant Telecommunications national and international standards and has a broad understanding of all aspects of Telecommunications systems and a deep understanding of own speciality(ies). \nProven track record of delivering a portfolio of Telecom EPC projects including complex and multiple vendor projects within international settings. \nRequires hands on expertise and design experience with telecoms equipment and systems design (OTN, UHF TETRA VHF radio Systems, IP Networks), security (access control, CCTV surveillance networks, fence intruder detection, ANPR), public/emergency announcement (PAGA), and networks (WANs, LANs, Industrial Wireless Networks Wiring, Routers, Switches, Servers etc), ship/shore communication systems, Hazardous area requirements (EExd, EEi, EExe). \nShall be proficient in fibre optic cabling network design, copper cable networks and relevant infrastructure such as duct banks, cable / ladder tray designs. This shall include transition of design engineering to construction deliverables. \n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead of Transportation and Installation Execution for Pipelines/Cables (F-1283-Q)-2','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead of Transportation and Installation Execution for Pipelines/Cables (F-1283-Q)-2\nJob Description Highlights: Position provides execution leadership to COMP2 Project, with support from Shared Services Integrated T&I Organization, guided by the following principles:\nOne Team project organization accountable and responsible for effective and efficient delivery of the various scopes in NFPS Compression development \nWhile position may report to the Compression Project COMP2 Head of T&I Execution and supported by Shared Services Transportation and Installation Division Manager, position is accountable and responsible to EPC Leadership for safe and successful execution of respective T&I scopes to meet EPC and overall project objectives\nRecommended 12+ years of experience with at least 10 years demonstrated T&I project management experience \nPreferred Engineering Degree or relevant on the job experience\nExperience in multiple T&I execution and operational aspects including offshore heavy lifts, float-over, pipeline, and cable installations, load-out and transportation; with float-over installation engineering and execution experience considered an advantage\nExperience with float-over installation is preferred\nWorldwide experience with contractors in particular those involved in the Offshore projects\nExcellent interpersonal and communication skills with a focus on teamwork and the ability to communicate and interact within a PMT\nApplication and in-depth knowledge of stakeholder specifications and a working knowledge of Industry standards \nOPITO certification is considered a plus\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Lead Project Assessment (E-1235-Q)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Lead Project Assessment (E-1235-Q)\nQualifications Bachelors degree in Engineering discipline.  Knowledge and/or Experience Minimum 15 years experience working within oil and gas industry in a Project Execution related environment with broad experience of projects, engineering, construction and Fabrication in EPC contracts. Experience in both Upstream and downstream will be an added advantage. Experience in multiple project phases like Pre-FEED, FEED and EPCC is preferred Excellent written and verbal English language communication skills. Well-developed interpersonal skills and the ability to influence decisions using presentation, negotiation and facilitation skills. Ability to manage development and implementation of Projects Managements Systems adapted to Oil & Gas industry. Ability to interact with senior leaders and shareholders confidently. Requires strong analytical, organisational and planning skills',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('MP Quality Governance and Management System Lead (T-1541)-2','Qatar','Doha','','About the job MP Quality Governance and Management System Lead (T-1541)-2\nQualifications Bachelor\'s degree in Engineering, Project Management, or a related field Knowledge and/or Experience At least 15 years of experience in project assurance role and risk management, with experience of managing complex projects Proficient in QMS, ISO 9001, 29001, 140001, OHSAS 18001, and API Q2Knowledge of regulatory compliance in the oil and gas industry. Strong leadership skills, attention to detail, and the ability to effectively navigate complex stakeholder dynamics. Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Excellent organizational skills, with ability to effectively collaborate with stakeholders at all levels Strong understanding of project management methods and project governance frameworks Demonstrated experience in developing and implementing project governance policies and procedures Experience of developing and implementing project assurance processes and procedures Strong understanding of project management tools such as Prince2 or Agile Strong analytical and problem-solving skills Strong Knowledge in various Quality tools, Six Sigma and lean process Demonstrated experience in Auditing Projects organizations. Certified Lead Quality Auditor is a plus Experience in the oil and gas industry is strongly preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Project Controls Specialist EPC-4 (N-2025) - 2','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Project Controls Specialist EPC-4 (N-2025) - 2\nJob Description Highlights: The position is located at RLIC site and is responsible to support all aspects of project controls activities including reporting, schedule development, progress verification and change control.\nMonitors the Contractors project controls performance in the areas of scheduling, progress measurement and reporting providing advice where necessary to make certain the Companys objectives are achieved.\nBachelor of Science in Engineering or relevant industry experience with thorough and extensive knowledge of a) Project controls principles, theories, concepts, and tools. b) Greenfield and brownfield.\nMinimum of ten (10) years broad experience in the area of project controls, including cost, schedule, and progress reporting.\nMinimum five (5) years experience associated with engineering, procurement, and construction for large (> $1BN) Onshore Facilities.\nMinimum five (5) years experience associated with engineering, procurement, and construction of large onshore LNG plants.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('QA/QC Engineer','Qatar','Doha','','About the job QA/QC Engineer\nJobs in Brief: Perform activities as directed to ensure successful achievement and maintenance of ISO accredited Quality Management System (QMS). QA/QC Representative for Framework Contracts Management Team of Roads Networks O & M / ROMD. Review and approve the project submittals / documents (PQP, ITP, Final Dossier, O & M Manuals, QA/QC Weekly/Monthly Reports and Contractors Key Personnel CVs). Carry-out inspection activities for all purchased items from suppliers (Project Spares, Supply Contracts and LPOs) and ensure that they meet requirements/standards. Carry-out Site Surveillance Inspections and Hand over / Taking over Inspections related to Framework Contract and Roads Networks O & M Dept./ROMD Contracts. Carry out internal and external QA/ QC Audits Support Public Works Authority (CLIENT) and contractor compliance with new business processes (including but not limited to those associated with Enterprise Roads Asset Management System (EAMS/Frameworks), identify redundant and/or duplicate activities which could be discontinued and make suggestions for improvement Maintain and update professional QA/QC knowledge on a regular basis to ensure best practice standards are achieved and maintained. Upload and maintain the QA/QC records in Client CDMS. Review and approve of work orders in Maximo related to QA/QC & Third Party Inspections in Framework Contracts. Ensure adherence to Quality, Health and Safety Policy and Procedures and comply with any new work instructions. Perform other duties/ tasks as required Qualification: Minimum Bachelors Degree in Engineering/ Relevant Subject Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Chartered Membership in relevant professional body (Chartered QA/QC Engineer) preferred and would be an advantage Physically fit to enter and work in confined spaces and the ability to undertake competency assessment to level required (essential)Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 10 years work experience in a similar position Experience of implementing and maintaining QMS to ISO 9001 standard Experience of working in a multidisciplinary Organization preferably in the Middle East Extensive knowledge of Health and Safety Policies and Procedures Knowledge of Microsoft Office Packages and in particular Microsoft Excel 2010Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is essential Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Road Pavement Specialist','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Road Pavement Specialist\nRoad Pavement Specialist Functional Responsibilities Provide technical support on pavement materials, design, construction, maintenance and rehabilitation treatments and practical applications. Lead advanced pavement investigations in critical sites to identify causes of defects and propose appropriate repairs. Conduct advanced research, analyze data, and provide recommendations and improvements to current or proposed Clients pavement management procedures such as performance modeling, and effectiveness of pavement maintenance. Develop and implement new technologies, suitable for the road network in Qatar, for pavement evaluations and preservations. Provide technical advice on monitoring and evaluating materials and maintenance and rehabilitation treatments. Support ROMD Sections in achieving recycling targets in pavement maintenance and rehabilitation activities. Provide training and knowledge transfer to ROMD staff and partners on performance-based contracts and bets practices. Review and update current procedures, codes of practice and manuals for pavement distresses, maintenance and rehabilitation activities. Qualification: Bachelors Degree in Civil Engineering or higher-level qualification in a relevant subject. Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Holder of Chartered Membership in relevant discipline (e.g. Engineering) would be an advantage Holder of Accreditation from known Institute would be an advantage. Holder of current/valid Qatar Driving License Experience: A minimum of 18 years related experience, including pavement engineering, pavement management and non-destructive testing of pavements. A post-graduate degree related to pavement engineering and/or management would be considered an asset. Knowledge of pavement engineering demonstrated by experience in pavement design, investigation, and research. Knowledge or experience of USA or UK pavement design methodologies Knowledge of materials behavior underlying standard specifications Construction inspection experience related to paving. Strong client management experience. Previous experience as a Project Manager, having led teams involved in pavement engineering and management. Well-developed written communication skills in the preparation of technical reports, correspondence and proposals are also important. Proficient in the use of Microsoft suite of applications (Excel, Power Point, Word)',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('SAP Sr FICO Techno Functional Consultant','Qatar','Doha','','About the job SAP Sr FICO Techno Functional Consultant\nPosition Senior SAP FICO Techno-Functional Consultant Duration 12 months (extendable)﻿Job Purpose: Senior SAP development Consultant with extensive ABAP development experience (> 10 years) in SAP FI/CO/PS modules Development experience in SAP JVA (Joint Venture Accounting) would be beneficial Experience in multiple SAP projects (New Implementations/Upgrades) Experience in ABAP OO programming (New ALV grid CL_SALV_TABLE) Experience in ABAP dynamic programming Experience in SAP CFin / SLT Migration Experience in new SAP ABAP 7.40 (>) syntax Experience in SAP development best practices Experience in SAP performance issues (Tracing SAP standard and improving Custom programs) Experience in troubleshooting/debugging/searching for SAP notes and application of SAP notes Experience in enhancing SAP standard (BADI/CMOD/BTEs) Experience in FI Validations and Substitutions Experience in Form development (Smartforms/Adobe Forms) Experience in SAP Workflow Experience in S4 HANA would be beneficial (Fiori apps, CDS views, Database Procedures, Output Management, Flexible Workflow)Key Responsibilities Candidate will do technical development & document specification. Understand of best practices and develop low maintenance, low fragile and scalable solutions Build SAP workflows Enhancement of SAP standard objects by using the appropriate frameworks Be able to improve performance of long runtime programs Use new ABAP syntax introduced in SAP7.40 and above Assist in good testing frameworks SAP Migration with SLT / CFIN on S4 Persona Educational Qualification A Bachelor\'s degree in Software development or equivalent. ABAP Certified in S/4 HANA﻿Required Professional Qualifications/Skills ABAP/Technical Consultant with more than 10 years hands-on experience Functional knowledge of Finance functions and processes including JVA Knowledge of HR and Logistics processes would be beneficial Experience in the FI/CO/JVA modules At least 5 SAP project implementations S4 Experience is must Good project management skills, operating as part of a team organizing, planning, and executing largescaleprojects from vision through implementation. Strong verbal and written communications skills, with an ability to express complex business concepts intechnical terms. Strong analytical, problem solving and conceptual skills. Strong interpersonal skills; ability to work well on cross-functional project teams and foster teamcommitment to tasks. Working knowledge of Advanced features of MS Office, Share Point and other tools etc.)',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Security Lead','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Security Lead\n﻿﻿Develop, maintain and implement SOC processes and procedures including use cases, indicators of compromise, run books Develop security requirements for applications, End-points including mobile devices, local area networks (LANs), wide area networks (WANs), virtual private networks (VPNs), routers, firewalls, application firewalls, wireless network and related security and network devices Monitor security procedures, ensuring compliance with all aspects of the program including personnel, physical and administrative security practices and procedures Define firm-wide security controls for the Microsoft environment including Share Point, MS Server, Directory Services (LDAP/Active Directory), Governance processes will leverage supporting utilities including SCCM(SMS), EMET (hardening), Global Catalog, and various other solutions In consultation with the TOPM, establish security Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) for all team operations Define firm-wide security controls for mainframe/midrange understanding the complex and diverse nature of JPMCCreate an execution strategy that focuses on embedding mainframe security controls into existing practices to enhance effectiveness Create an execution strategy that focuses on embedding Windows security controls into existing practices to enhance effectiveness The Cyber Security Policy Lead will work under the direction of the Governance and Compliance Tower Lead to development AMs information security policy and standards ecosystem Contribute to other risk, security, compliance initiatives and services as appropriate',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior Administrative Assistant','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior Administrative Assistant\nPosition Brief The Senior Administrative Assistant is responsible to compile and maintain records of business and office activities, performing a variety of duties and utilising knowledge of systems or procedure. Functional Responsibilities Co-ordinate and distribute papers and documents as appropriate Prepare correspondence and documents as instructed according to the department-established procedures Use agreed correspondence systems as required to track progress of outstanding actions/sign off and follow up Ensure both paper and electronic filing systems are developed and maintained to the standard required Book rooms and make travel arrangements or other requests as necessary for the Section Head and proactively follow up Answer phone calls and respond to queries related to Workshops generic activities or divert calls to relevant staff Receive, check, record and file all technical and non-technical documents as per established policy and procedures and keep under safe custody Input document data into required registers ensuring that the information is accurate and up to date Retrieve and record clearly on document register to whom they have been issued, date and distribute as appropriate Provide document control reports as requested, review progress and point out errors and/or delays or issues to relevant staff Liaise with subject matter experts on technical subjects to prepare controlled documents Adhere to Health and Safety policies and procedures in work and other corporate procedures and comply to any new work instructions Perform other duties / tasks as required. Qualification: Bachelors degree or higher level qualification in a relevant subject. Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 12 years of experience in secretarial/administration tasks Experience of working in a multidisciplinary Organization preferably in the Middle East Ability to produce Executives reports is compulsory Ability to influence and engage stakeholders and staff at all levels within the Organization Competent in Microsoft Office Packages Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is mandatory. Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic would be an advantage.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior Application Analyst','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior Application Analyst\nResponsibilities Identifying organizational need for new applications Preparing technical specification as a roadmap for software Implementing, testing and integrating new applications Performing routine application backups and upgrades Installing new applications upgrade and releases Providing instructions and training to staff when necessary Monitoring, recoding and responding to requests for support Investigating and diagnosing system faults and errors Resolving technical issues Analyzing error trends aimed at reducing/minimizing down time Communicating messages regarding application issues to users in a timely manner Liaising with application suppliers when needed to fulfil the requirements of the organization Scheduling and running regular tests to enhance the current application. Identifying and developing functionality changes Maintaining documentation of key databases and applications linked to them. Perform lead/supervisor duties as and when assigned. Analysis/options or feasibility research of needs and possible solutions. Visually map solution and present in an easy-to-understand manner to get a decision. Identify technology and/or business requirements. Gather, document and update business requirements. Complete detailed workflow process mapping. Develop testing strategies and execute test plan to mitigate deployment risk. Qualification/ Education BS in Computers Science or related subject Knowledge of SQL, SAS Visual Analytics, SSRS, or other reporting technology Exposure to and understanding of work structure/operations. Experience Overall 10+ years of experience; Minimum of 5 years experience in following areas: Administration, monitoring and maintenance of software infrastructures and applications. Oversee practices and processes to ensure integrity, safety and availability of all data and applications as part of organizations information systems. Ensure that the processes needed for a business to function and succeed are running smoothly. Technical point of contact to fix application and systems issues, usually on an immediate basis.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior Application Expert [Administration]','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior Application Expert [Administration]\nResponsibilities Must have experience that demonstrates a strong background in application administration skills using various technologies. The candidate should have strong organizational skills, as well as the ability to multi-task and work independently and as a team player. Must have experience of Open layers, Geo Server, Bootstrap, SQL Server, Oracle, Arc GIS etc. Experience using Microsoft Office Suite, software development project management methodologies (e.g. AGILE), and design tools is required. Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with managers are required. Analytical and hardware/software troubleshooting skills are required. Perform lead/supervisor duties as and when assigned. Analytical and hardware/software troubleshooting skills are required. Qualification / Education BS in Computers Science or related subject Experience Minimum Overall 13 years of experience as an administrator into . Net technology and GIS Data Management applications/ tools. At least 5 years total experience with developing in multiple languages / protocols (ASP. NET, C#, VB. NET, Java Script, XML, Python, PHP, JSON, HTML5)At least 2 years experience of applications/tools for GIS Data Management. Experience working in an Agile/Scrum development process. Solid experience with data modeling, business logic, and RESTful APIs.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior Engineer (IT)','Qatar','Doha','','\nAbout the job Senior Engineer (IT) \n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('SENIOR OPERATIONS ENGINEER (OFFSHORE)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job SENIOR OPERATIONS ENGINEER (OFFSHORE)\nJob Description Manage the team of Operations Engineers who are responsible for well design and thereafter the operational support for all offshore wells according to agreed policies, procedures and standards to achieve the CLIENTannual drilling objectives. Review and approve the drilling programs prepared within the section to ensure they are technically correct, the optimum design has been selected and that they comply with CLIENT policies standards and procedures. Identify and mitigate risks in all offshore drilling operations through a systematic approach to hazard management with the objective to protect people, the environment and CLIENT assets and reputation. Ensure that HSE considerations are fully addressed at the well design stage by using systematic risk and hazard management technique with the clear objective to eliminate all significant accidents. Initiate change and champion best practice and new technology application to enhance well designs and operational performance to ensure fit for purpose wells at the lowest cost. Required qualifications, experience and expertise:\nBSc. Engineering Degree. IWCF Certification at Supervisor level Seasoned professional with at least 20 years experience in Drilling Operations of which at least 5 years in a Senior OE position. Minimum of 5 years as an Operations Drilling Engineer with a major IOC or NOCMinimum of 2 years well site experience. Knowledge of Process Safety related to drilling Operations and a proactive mind set for managing safety. Mastery in well design, tubular design, wellbore construction, drilling fluids, well control, and a good understanding of geology. Demonstrated leadership and people management skills and a keen awareness for cultural sensitivity. Fully conversant with and ability to use all Drilling Engineering Software within EDT (Engineers Desktop) including; Compass; Well Plan; Stress Check and Casing Seat. Excellent verbal and written skills in English Ability to coach and support Qatari Development staff. Preferable Experience and Expertise\nExperience with hydrogen sulphide well designs and safety practices. Knowledge of tendering and contracting procedures and practices. Experience with workover operations in high pressure gas wells Experience in working with CLIENT standard Drilling Engineering Software Open-Wells.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior SAP JVA Techno-Functional Consultant.','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior SAP JVA Techno-Functional Consultant.\nPosition Senior SAP FICO Techno-Functional Consultant Duration12 months (extendable)﻿Job Purpose: Senior SAP development Consultant with extensive ABAP development experience (> 10 years) in SAP FI/CO/PS modules Development experience in SAP JVA (Joint Venture Accounting) would be beneficial. Experience in multiple SAP projects (New Implementations/Upgrades) Experience in ABAP OO programming (New ALV grid CL_SALV_TABLE) Experience in ABAP dynamic programming Experience in SAP CFin / SLT Migration Experience in new SAP ABAP 7.40 (>) syntax Experience in SAP development best practices Experience in SAP performance issues (Tracing SAP standard and improving Custom programs) Experience in troubleshooting/debugging/searching for SAP notes and application of SAP notes Experience in enhancing SAP standard (BADI/CMOD/BTEs) Experience in FI Validations and Substitutions Experience in Form development (Smartforms/Adobe Forms) Experience in SAP Workflow Experience in S4 HANA would be beneficial (Fiori apps, CDS views, Database Procedures, Output Management, Flexible Workflow)﻿Key Responsibilities Candidate will do technical development & document specification. Understand of best practices and develop low maintenance, low fragile and scalable solutions Build SAP workflows Enhancement of SAP standard objects by using the appropriate frameworks Be able to improve performance of long runtime programs Use new ABAP syntax introduced in SAP7.40 and above Assist in good testing frameworks SAP Migration with SLT / CFIN on S4 Persona﻿Educational Qualification A Bachelor\'s degree in Software development or equivalent. ABAP Certified in S/4 HANA﻿Required Professional Qualifications/Skills ABAP/Technical Consultant with more than 10 years hands-on experience Functional knowledge of Finance functions and processes including JVA Knowledge of HR and Logistics processes would be beneficial Experience in the FI/CO/JVA modules At least 5 SAP project implementations S4 Experience is must Good project management skills, operating as part of a team organizing, planning, and executing large-scale projects from vision through implementation. Strong verbal and written communications skills, with an ability to express complex business concepts in technical terms. Strong analytical, problem solving and conceptual skills. Strong interpersonal skills; ability to work well on cross-functional project teams and foster team commitment to tasks. Working knowledge of Advanced features of MS Office, Share Point and other tools etc.)',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior SAP Security and GRC Consultant','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior SAP Security and GRC Consultant\nJob Description We are looking for a Senior SAP Security & GRC Consultant having Functional, Technical, S/4 Upgrade and troubleshooting experience with strong knowledge of ERP processes and Information Security principles, critical thinking, and great communication skills. The ideal applicant will have the following experience: At least 4 full cycle SAP Implementations including Implementation in the Oil & Gas industry and at least 2 S/4HANA upgrades. Deep knowledge of various aspects of SAP Security, both from a technical as well as business process perspective. Knowledge of SAP authorization concept for both on-premises systems such as ECC, BW, MDG, S/4 HANA, Fiori roles, HANA DB, BTP etc. and new SAP Cloud solutions. Knowledge of HANA Database roles, privileges and schemas using HANA studio. Excellent knowledge of S/4HANA migrations and system transformation including business process reengineering. Familiarity with SAP Enterprise Threat Detection (ETD) Experience in designing, configuring and Implementing SAP GRC Access Request Analysis (ARA), Access Request Management (ARM), Emergency Access Management (EAM) Experience in building SOD ruleset, configuring ruleset in SAP GRC 12.0 systems and full understanding of user/role level risk analysis. Should participate in process Improvement and procedures including but not limited to change controls, project management methodology Excellent written, Interpersonal and communication skills.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Senior Structural Engineer','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior Structural Engineer\nSenior Road Engineer Senior Structural Engineer Jobs in Brief: Understand the Road Operation and Management Department scope task and target. Coordinate with stakeholders for executing operations and maintenance of road networks in coordination with the Management Consultants (MC)/ contractors. Plan and program road repair works on the networks Monitor stakeholders work schedules, set priorities, and ensure the appropriate assignment of equipment, materials, and personnel. Administer, prioritize and oversee major repairs on the road network, oversee assignment maintenance crews to repair networks. Ability to undertake supervisory and inspection ( for contract compliance) tasks as assigned by Lead Engineers Work proactively with the RMD and design consultants to resolve any design related issues. Prioritize projects and assign work to outsourced maintenance crews to repair road networks, taking into consideration criticality of work to be executed. Ensure that incidents / emergencies reported are attended to and resolved by the maintenance contractors or in-house teams Perform emergency road maintenance and respond to public complaints and requests/ calls received from Customer Contact Centre / Road Management Centre Prepare all specifications for maintenance vehicles and equipment and assists in the purchase of motor vehicles, off road equipment and others, as required. Assist the project team in ensuring that road upgrading, and maintenance works are carried out to the specified technical standards and that corrective action is taken as needed. Develop the quarterly, annual and long-term preventative and routine maintenance plans to ensure that the road networks perform to the specified level of operations based on asset management standards and recommendations Coordinate with the Design Department to develop and implement improvements to existing road networks. Manage the performance of maintenance contractors to ensure adherence to defined SLAs Raise any issues that require consideration to the road networks Engineering Advisor / Expert for advice on actions/ recommendations. Ensure adherence to Health and Safety Policy and Procedures within the section and comply with any new work instructions. Perform other duties/ tasks as required Ability to write project scope of works (tendering/quotation purposes) for new and maintenance works Qualification: Bachelors Degree in Civil Engineering or relevant Subject Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Holder of Chartered Membership in relevant discipline (e.g. Engineering) would be an advantage Holder of current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum 15 years cumulative experience of road networks including 8 years managing contractors and leading a team Experience of working in a multidisciplinary Organization preferably in the Middle East Knowledge and experience in contract management Knowledge of Bridges, Tunnels, Road works, Environment policies, procedures, and regulations. Ability to deliver and support change Competent in Microsoft Office Packages Microsoft Project/Primavera Ability to influence and engage stakeholders and staff at all levels within the Organization Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is mandatory. Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Specialist EPM Solutions (Oracle)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Specialist EPM Solutions (Oracle)\nThe Senior Specialist EPM Solution (Oracle) is a consultant who drives EPM Cloud solution by interfacing with key customer stakeholders. The post holder drives the solution in collaboration with the vendors by creating solution architecture, high level design, migration approach and overall test strategy. S/he delivers high quality code deliverables for a module and leads a team during all types of testing and support activities related to implementation. Key Roles Provides functional & technical consulting services to clients Works closely with client management and users to define requirements and scope of development needs Configures, develops, and implements Oracle EPM Suite of products-based solutions based on identified clients requirements Provides mentoring and training services Provides application support for a variety of clients Performs the analysis necessary to design and architect solutions that meet client requirements Adheres to Client standards as they appear in the Code of Conduct and Conflict of Interest policies Experience7+ years of relevant work experience inclusive of 4 years of experience in design, modeling, implementation, development and maintenance of EPM applications using Oracle Hyperion suite of products.2-3 years of end-to-end hands-on experience in implementing latest versions of Oracles Cloud Hyperion Education Bachelors Degree in a relevant Information Technology field ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('SR PLANNING AND BUSINESS SUPPORT SPECIALIST','Qatar','Doha','','About the job SR PLANNING AND BUSINESS SUPPORT SPECIALIST\nPrimary Purpose of the Job\nPrepares the Subsurface (VU) Directorate business planning process. Supports all VU functions on KPIs and performance monitoring and reporting. CLIENTAudit liaison for VU Directorate. Supports VU Directorate RMR with Quality Management System processes. Principal Accountabilities\nAdheres to and implements the Company\'s occupational safety and health and environment policy effectively in all of his/her work Works closely with all asset heads and function leaders to ensures timely preparation of various documents, data and reports necessary to obtain management and shareholders\' approval of proposals and activities including business plans, operating plans and work program and budget Develops the yearly oil & gas wide business plan in collaboration with all functions and teams Gathers input and analyses data, and coordinate with management teams and other functional departments to prepare single year work programs & budgets and subsequent periodic outlook projection (Quarterly, monthly etc.)Co-ordinates the timely and quality input of the Department and International Assets information into all necessary CLIENTinternal and external reporting requirements biweekly reports, monthly reports, annual reports, etc)Provides an oversight to management of the companys strategic planning, financial forecasting, annual budgeting process, and operating plan variance analysis Provides in-depth analysis and presents findings on key drivers of monthly outlook variances Analyzes and monitors KPIs, highlighting trends and variances Develops and executes processes to allow for routine analytical reviews of company financial and operational performance, leveraging business unit analytical resources and tools Routinely communicates business unit consolidated financial and operational performance trends, historical and forecasted, using appropriate metrics. Determines trends, resulting operational and strategic implications, and key recommended actions Works closely with Corporate HSE and asset heads to incorporate Subsurface Directorate owned assets HSE performance into corporate reporting Works closely with Corporate Risk Management function and asset heads to include VU Directorate risksinto CLIENTrisk reports and suggests mitigation actions in coordination with asset heads Preparation of presentation materials for executive management and Board of Director meetings as requested Supports the Department RMR on Quality Management System processes and compliance Ensures all field audit work are adequately prepared and timely delivery of all requests from the auditors Decision Making Authority\nClosely communicates and interacts with Contracts, Legal and Finance on contracting matters and provides recommendation to assets and function heads and management team Custodian for VU Directorate business plan and Work Program and Budget input and deliverables Context / Special Features / Challenges:\nWorks independently guided by functional objectives Manages activities by setting and controlling specialized professional standards Regular contacts with Contracts and Procurement, Finance and Legal on contracting matters Close coordination of work program and budget delivery within the Department as well as the VU Planning focal point Qualifications / Knowledge / Skills / Experience:\nMinimum Qualifications: BSc/Bachelor Degree in Engineering or other Business related fields Postgraduate Degree and commercial and business training or certification will be an advantage Minimum 10 years of relevant Oil & Gas experience Job-Specific Skills:\nPlanning and organizational skills Business processes and contracting skills Negotiation and problem solving skills Excellent command of English language and communication skills Excellent command of computer skills',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Technical Writers (OES)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Technical Writers (OES)\nQualifications HND in Engineering or equivalent. Knowledge and/or Experience 5 years experience in a relevant process operation in LNG production including 3 years experience as a technical author in the hydrocarbon or petrochemical industry. Technical and Business Skills Expert in written and spoken English. Must be proficient in word processing, desktop publishing, project planning and scheduling, spreadsheets, flowcharts, graphics, technical drawing, and other computer-related utilities. Proficiency must include a working knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, and Power Point) and MS Share Point.﻿Key Job Accountabilities1. Develops required documentation for Operations plants in compliance with established Company policies and procedures, oil & gas industry and international standards, and ISO 9000 & 14000 requirements.2. Revalidates Operations Group procedures and standing instructions to ensure the continued availability of accurate, detailed, step-by-step documentation that enables the safe and efficient operation and maintenance of Company facilities.3. Reviews and revises existing plant operations documentation and proposes criticality levels for Operations procedures.4. Produces concise and accurate technical and safety related documents that reflect industry best practice and client lessons learned.5. Develops Operations and Maintenance procedure assessment packages in accordance with established Company competency assurance standards.6. Facilitates appropriate reviews and input to ensure continued development of concise and accurate technical and safety-related documentation and As-is and As-built information and instructions are reflected in relevant documentation.7. Identifies areas of improvement to enhance the capacity of Operations to mitigate business risk and meet emerging needs. Ensures technical changes are cascaded to the relevant departments to be updated in all plant documentation and related competency assessments.8. Supports the identification of operational areas that require technical changes or alterations to accommodate varying operating conditions and develops procedural solutions within Operations groups and across all relevant facilities.9. Administers the document review process to ensure that all Operations documentation reviews effectively capture the changes requested by concerned stakeholders.10. Works closely with the Graphics Officer and the Engineering Group documentation section to ensure that changes to all P&IDs are properly captured and reflected within simplified drawings.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Telecommunications','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Telecommunications\nSenior ITS Engineer - Telecommunications Jobs in Brief: Monitor and support the Road Management Centre (RMC) systems necessary to ensure secure and reliable 24/7 ITS communications to deliver the performance and availability service levels required for ITS operations Review and witness ITS project commissioning to ensure the telecommunications elements fully meet the Client ITS specifications and telecommunications strategy requirements Perform required activities associated with projects and existing ITS assets (investigation, analysis and design) to support effective programme delivery and maintaining the integrity of the Client ITS telecommunications network Review and analyse the day-to-day management and performance of the ITS telecommunications maintenance & operations contractor to ensure the availability and performance targets for the network are being met and that best practices are being followed Monitor the preventive maintenance activities of the ITS telecommunications maintenance & operations contractor to ensure that secondary and contingency measures are available and will work should any equipment fail across the network Understand detailed plans, specifications and estimates for roadway Intelligent Traffic System implementation projects and advise on suitability of proposed telecommunications design and configuration Prepare and register all relevant documentation and design reports and ensuring that all documentation is accurate and received within the system held by Client. Work in collaboration with other disciplines to ensure the integrity of the overall design of projects and ensure as-built drawings and data sheets are accurate and complete. Contribute to the resolution of technical issues, such as substandard products, on projects and providing technical guidance to other team members Maintain on-going communication with relevant stakeholders and sub-contractors to build relationships and communication networks ensuring quality of service. Carry out site visits and survey inspections and supervise Client sub-contractors Conduct studies on the requirement of Telecommunication and Network for ITS/ Tunnels. Identify key trends and provide suggestions for improving ITS/ Tunnels telecommunications efficiency and performance Identify any gaps in Telecommunication and Network ITS assets within the main corridors of Qatar and propose the most cost effective way of filling those gaps Undertake any work of a technical nature that falls within ability and competence to provide a solution to engineering problems and lead the telecommunications input in to any troubleshooting triage activities for RMC faults Work under minimum supervision and competent to check the work of others and supervise less experienced or junior staff Keep up to date with industry best practice and apply best practice to ensure professional development Adhere to Health and Safety policy and procedures and comply with new work instructions Perform other duties / tasks as required Provide input into the reviewing and updating of the I&EMP as appropriate. Ensure adherence to Health and Safety Policy and Procedures and comply with any new work instructions Qualification: Minimum Bachelors Degree in Engineering/ Relevant Subject Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Chartered Membership in Engineering or Relevant professional body would be an advantage Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) Education qualifications or equivalent for Telemetry, Network Hardware and software Education qualification Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 15 years cumulative experience in a relevant field. Minimum of 8 years experience in specialist area including experience in deploying and managing Wide Area Networks and Local Area Networks Ability to establish strong working relationships with stakeholders Ability to influence and engage stakeholders and staff at all levels within the organization Competent in Microsoft Office Packages and Network Management Systems Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is essential Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('TPC Operator','Qatar','Doha','','About the job TPC Operator\nTPC Operator Jobs in Brief: Ensure all claims/issues are captured in the systems. Update the source systems namely Enterprise Asset Management System (EAMS)/ Customer Relationship Management System (CRMS) as required. Ensure all work assigned is completed within the agreed KPI/SLAUnderstand claims issues and requirements and process all Claims Requests in a timely manner, ensuring KPI/SLA are met. Escalate any potential workflow issues to the TPC Team Leader in a timely manner. Maintain awareness of recurring problems on the Roads network and geographical boundaries and alert/escalate to the Team Lead and immediate manager for their onward actions. Identify issues which prevent smooth processing of claims requests (Client public and vice versa) and suggest ideas for resolution Liaise with Insurance company adjusters and stakeholders throughout Client where appropriate, using various channels of communication, to ensure Client interests are protected. Act as an ambassador for Client and deal with customers in a professional and courteous manner always Cover for and/or assist other colleagues where required and according to business need. Adhere to Health and Safety policies and procedures in work and other corporate procedures and comply with any new work instructions. Perform other duties/ tasks as required. Including accident location inspection. Qualification: Diploma in relevant subject or above Physically fit to enter and work in confined spaces and the ability to undertake competency assessment to level required (essential)Able to understand the report from Insurance adjusters. Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 6 years work experience in a similar position In depth knowledge of Insurance claims and complaints registration. Knowledge of Maximo EAMS or equivalent system with regard to operation, system administration and training Knowledge of CRMS or equivalent system with regard to operation, system administration and training Knowledge of Microsoft Office Packages and in particular Microsoft Excel 2010Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is essential. Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Traffic Signals','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Traffic Signals\nSenior ITS Engineer Traffic Signals Jobs in Brief: Monitor and support the Road Management Systems (RMC) necessary to ensure the availability and performance service levels for Traffic Signals are being met Ensure the high availability targets of the Client Traffic Signals Assets and Systems across the network are being met Responsibility for the management and co-ordination of traffic signals maintenance contracts and future ITS contracts, resources and third party support;Responsibility for ensuring new schemes are correctly handed over into the Client Traffic Signal Maintenance. Responsibility for dealing with contract issues and verify that traffic signal Maintenance Contractor invoices are accurate and are backed up by the traffic signal Maintenance technician documented reports. Responsibility for monitoring and managing the traffic signal maintenance contractors are meeting their minimum performance measures, such as response times Carry out feasibility studies as necessary to assess the viability of different traffic signal maintenance options and provide recommendations of best option based on cost-benefit analysis. Carry out cost estimation of various traffic signal maintenance works. Respond to reactive traffic signal maintenance needs at short notice as necessary including emergency works to safeguard the safety of the public and to protect the integrity of the traffic signals. Ensure that all proactive, reactive and planned maintenance across the network and that the maintenance contracts are compliant to their delivery requirements;Review traffic signal design and installations. Responsibility for ensuring traffic signal inspections are carried out including defect identification, classification and coding and that installations meet the latest ITS and Traffic Signals specification and standards. Monitor the maintenance contractors compliance with traffic management requirements for traffic signal and ITS devices inspection and maintenance activities including Work Zone Traffic Management Guide (WZTMG)Work under minimum supervision and competent to check the work of others and supervise less experienced or junior staff Keep up to date with industry best practice and apply best practice to ensure professional development Adhere to Health and Safety policy and procedures and comply with new work instructions Perform other duties / tasks as required and provide input into the reviewing and updating of the I&EMP as appropriate. Ensure adherence to Health and Safety Policy and Procedures and comply with any new work instructions Qualification: Minimum Bachelors Degree in Engineering/ Relevant Subject Education qualification obtained from North America, West Europe, Australia Chartered Membership in Engineering or Relevant professional body would be an advantage Current/valid Qatar Driving License would be an advantage Experience: Minimum of 15 years cumulative experience in a relevant field. Minimum of 8 years experience in Traffic Signal design, implementation and maintenance Knowledge of asset hierarchy, asset types and related asset attributes. Ability to establish strong working relationships with stakeholders Ability to influence and engage stakeholders and staff at all levels within the organization Competent in Microsoft Office Packages and SCATS Technology Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in English is essential Ability to communicate verbally and in writing in Arabic is preferred',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('Training Instructors (OES)','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Training Instructors (OES)\nJob Purpose Design and develop competency based training courses, training assessments, work place learning material and tests and advise line departments on development and corrective action plans﻿Qualifications Bachelors degree in Engineering or equivalent.. Knowledge and/or Experience Minimum 6 years experience oil and gas industry, including 3 years as an instructor. Experience in plant process, production equipment and understanding of basic DCS process control systems. Experience in procedure development, analysis, and plant Operations and Maintenance.﻿Key Job Accountabilities1. Design, develop, teach advanced level theory and practice, and assess using various learning methodologies in an assigned technical subject area , role plays, simulations, technology-delivered training, and workplace learning or e-learning.2. Analyse the knowledge and skills gap in alignment of OJT (On Job Training) programs matrix and design learning materials to meet individual needs, in coordination with Line supervision.3. Design and develop simulator training and assessments or source appropriate test materials where necessary. Evaluate learner performance and prepare reports of progress.4. Design and develop Process/Technical Unit training and Procedure Competency Assessments or source appropriate test materials where necessary.5. Recommend learning solutions with course curriculum and responds to feedback from learners and makes adjustments or enhancements to the learning solution based on feedback.6. Develop operations process scenarios and modify lesson plans and learning materials and use instructional methods and media effectively.7. Liaise with Simulator Engineer and Training Coordinator to develop the operations process scenarios to maintain Operator Training Simulator Hardware and perform OTS software housekeeping.8. Maintain and follow-up trainee records including attendance and assessment results in LSO (SAP Learning Solutions). Communicate feedback reports for Training Coordinator on trainee progress.9. Ensure operations process safety standards are implemented and followed.10. Ensure recommendations and enhancements regarding effectiveness of training resources are implemented.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('UAT Tester','Qatar','Doha','','\nAbout the job UAT Tester \n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Mekdam Holding Group',NULL),('IT Help Desk Technician','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','IT Help Desk Technician● Proven experience as a help desk technician or other customer support role● Tech savvy with working knowledge of office automation products, databases and remote control● Good understanding of computer systems, mobile devices and other tech products● Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues● Proficiency in English● Excellent communication skills● Customer-oriented and cool-tempered● BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science or relevant field','IT Help Desk Technician● Proven experience as a help desk technician or other customer support role● Tech savvy with working knowledge of office automation products, databases and remote control● Good understanding of computer systems, mobile devices and other tech products● Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues● Proficiency in English● Excellent communication skills● Customer-oriented and cool-tempered● BSc/BA in IT, Computer Science or relevant field','2023-10-01',55,12,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'