pport HR team in recruitment, onboarding, and employee record management. Contribute to HR documentation and record-keeping. Assist with HR projects and initiatives. Collaborate with the team to ensure HR compliance and best practices. Operations Intern: Support the Operations Team in various operational tasks. Assist in general operational functions. Contribute to process improvement and documentation. Collaborate with the team to meet operational goals and objectives. Carry out other operational tasks as needed. Qualifications:\nOpen to Emirati nationals. Must have a Bachelor\'s Degree Duration: Up to 12 Months Enthusiasm to learn and contribute to the organization. Excellent communication and teamwork skills. Ability to work well in a dynamic environment. Strong commitment to professional growth and development. Note:\nA work permit from the Ministry of Human Resources and Emiratization (MOHRE) is required for these internship positions.',NULL,'2023-10-21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Nathan & Nathan',NULL),('Field Service Specialist (Oil & Gas): Dammam Saudi Arabia','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Description CLOSING DATE: 9 NOV 2023. NOTE: Please ONLY apply if you have sufficient experience and skills required as per job description below. Job Summary: The primary function of the Field Service Specialist is to oversee critical bit & tool runs and have responsibility for monitoring drill bit and BHA performance, advising on the correct drilling parameters throughout the bit run and collecting data in real-time to enable further, more detailed analysis to be undertaken. RESPONSIBILITIES:• Liaising with Operator Representative, Drilling Crew, Directional Personnel and Geologist prior to and during drilling • Report to Operator Representative on a daily basis with written summary report of previous days drilling • Report to Sales Engineer on a daily basis with relevant information including previous days drilling and up to date drilling at time of contact • Hydraulics calculation (simulation) to be performed prior to and during drilling • Inspection of drill bit and nozzle preparation prior to trip in hole • Drill out procedures for cement and casing float/shoe • Conduct “Drill Off Tests” for each formation and record results (WOB, RPM, Torque and ROP relationships) • Advise on correct combination of drilling parameters for each application (relationship between ROP and durability, directional drilling requirements etc) • Ability to recognize and monitor different downhole vibration modes (Axial, Lateral and Torsional vibration) from surface and downhole measurements • Ability to apply correct drilling parameters to minimize any such vibration • Ability to interpret real-time e-log data • Familiarization of all downhole failure modes for each drill bit type and (remove) (ability to interpret) interpretation of surface and downhole indications • Full dull grading of both the drill bit and BHA components when pulled to surface including likely fail characteristic of the drilling system (if applicable) • Preparation of a full post run report with photographs, operating parameters chart, and survey data • Recommendation of subsequent bit run choices based on dull condition • Input 100% of all drilling data into Bit Trak including photographs into Image Manager • Preparing the Bit Condition Report to be offered to the Sales Engineer who will pass on to the customer • Debriefing session post run with relevant Sales Engineer (recommendations, problems, lessons learned) • Assist with onshore office and warehouse duties as required. Qualifications: Engineering or relevant degree is highly desired. Extensive industry experience can be viewed as possible substitutes. 1-3 years relevant oilfield experience desirable. Job requirement:• This position will require travel. • Observes safety regulations, wears required safety equipment, encourages safe working practices, corrects obvious hazards immediately or reports them to Management. • Work within established company guidelines. • Adheres to all HSE requirements. Competencies:• Functional/Technical Skills • Technical Learning • Learning on the Fly • Problem Solving • Action Oriented • Standing Alone • Written Communications • Approachability • Integrity and Trust • Listening • Time Management • Understanding Others • Perseverance • Drive for Results • Organizing Technical Skills:• General Oilfield • General Engineering • Drill Bit • Drilling Dynamics • Hole Opening • Coring • Motors • Drilling Tools • Fishing Tools • Advanced Drilling Tools • Service Equipment • Gammaloy Products • Intervention and Completion Tools Basic Every day, the oil and gas industry’s best minds put more than 150 years of experience to work to help our customers achieve lasting success. We Power the Industry that Powers the World Throughout every region in the world and across every area of drilling and production, our family of companies has provided the technical expertise, advanced equipment, and operational support necessary for success—now and in the future. Global Family We are a global family of thousands of individuals, working as one team to create a lasting impact for ourselves, our customers, and the communities where we live and work. Purposeful Innovation Through purposeful business innovation, product creation, and service delivery, we are driven to power the industry that powers the world better. Service Above All This drives us to anticipate our customers’ needs and work with them to deliver the finest products and services on time and on budget. Job Category Field Service',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'National Oilwell Varco, Inc.',NULL),('Product Line Manager - Drill Bits EHO (O&G, Sales, Marketing): Dubai Dubai, United Arab Emirates','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Job Description CLOSING DATE 20 NOVEMBER 2023. NOTE: Please only apply if you have relevant experience and skills required as per job description below. Job Summary. The Product Line Manager (PLM) – EHO will lead, set, and communicate the strategic direction of the drill bit product line. The PLM must understand both internal and external product needs, and work with the relevant functional groups to assure the product strategy is developed and implemented. The strategy should balance sales, operational, and business development needs. The PLM must be an excellent communicator, able to lead without direct authority, understand the sales, customer, and competitive environments, know the product technically along with its applications, and have good general business acumen. ROLE & RESPONSIBILITIES: Manage the drill bit product line to achieve Company short- and long-range objectives including sales, market share, new product and market development, return on investment, and profitability measures. Meet frequently with customers and NOV sales to understand the market, competitive landscape, and needs for products, services, information, and training. Develop annual formal marketing strategies and comprehensive business plans for the drill bit product line over the prescribed period. Upon approval, this plan will direct functional activities and priorities, and support investments - particularly in the current year. These will address marketing mix (product, price, promotion, and distribution) issues in detail for target markets, and provide pro forma financial statements and resource requirements for the product line business. Provide optimum technical and business model offerings and manage rationalization of the product line. Provide input for production planning and manage the Company\'s investment in finished goods inventories to support both sales and service. Approve product forecasts and manufacturing build plans for unsold speculative units, working to ensure competitive deliveries, optimum inventory position and customer satisfaction. Work with Manufacturing and Engineering to identify and implement cost & quality improvements. Work with engineering to set priorities relative to the development of new products and sustaining of existing products, managing the new product development process in accordance with company policy. Create New Product Functional Requirements Document (FRD) outlining the requirements of the drill bit Product Line. Develop Business Cases for new product ideas, and other general efforts affecting the drill bit Product Line, to ensure allocation of resources will provide acceptable return on investment. Direct the development and approve the type and content of marketing materials used in promotion of assigned products. Prepare and deliver effective oral and written technical, marketing and training presentations to customers and company personnel. Sponsor preparation and presentation of technical articles and papers to enhance Company image and develop new markets and applications. Review and provide appropriate direction and information for company training courses. Maintain a competitive database for all products, including market share and product performance. In conjunction with Engineering ensure that appropriate resource exists within the company for technical support to the sales organization. BEHAVIORAL SKILLS/COMPETENCIES: Customer Focus Business and Financial Acumen Drive for Results Process Management Managing and Measuring Work Hiring, Developing and Confronting Direct Reports Timely and Quality Decision Making Time Management/Priority Setting Conflict Management and Problem Solving Peer Relationships Effective Communication Skills EXPERIENCE/EDUCATION/SKILL-SET REQUIRED: Bachelor’s Degree in relevant subject. Minimum 5 years of experience Proficient in Microsoft suite. Knowledge of Data Management software (e.g., Power BI, Tableau, Spotfire).* Oil and gas Background.',NULL,'2023-10-21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'National Oilwell Varco, Inc.',NULL),('Quality Engineer (Audit, API/ISO, Welding, QA/QC): Dubai Un