atus updates to stakeholders Job Requirements Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business or a related field. Minimum of 3 years of experience in implementing, Presales & Demos for Odoo ERP solutions. Various Experience in Multi-industries, Projects & Modules.knowledge of Python programming language is a plus. Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal. Excellent knowledge of Accounting is a plus. Ability to work independently as well as part of a team. Working Conditions*Working Hours: - 8 hrs.*Days off: - 2 days*Location: - Mohandessin Benefits*Social & Medical Insurance*Annual Increments*Hybrid Policy','2023-09-01',12,0,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,4,'Manager ',NULL,'Peerless',NULL),('QA/QC Engineer','Qatar','Doha','','About the job QA/QC Engineer\nQA/QC ENGINEERWe require a QA/QC Engineer with 5 years of experience in Oil & Gas Requirements: Electrical Engineering Degree/Diploma At least 5 to 7 years of experience in the Oil and Gas industry Thorough knowledge of QA/QC Documentation and ISO 9001, 45001Strong communication and organizational skills. Preference will be given to those who have Local Visa transferable Qatar Experience Valid Qatar Driving Licence Accommodation will be provided by the company Job Description: Preparing project reports and conducting inspections Coordinating inspections with clients and consultants Ensuring construction, installation, and operational testing conform to specifications and client requirements Supporting all QHSE (Quality, Health, Safety, and Environment) policies and procedures implemented by the company Proactively supervising the closure of NCRs (Non-Conformance Reports)Maintaining QA/QC documents legible and conducting internal quality audits Being proficient in dedicated software for MEP construction and MS Office tools Responsible for implementing the QA/QC management system on-site, coordinating quality inspections with all the site sub-contractors and vendors, and coordinating all non-des