 existing systems and procedures, making necessary changes and improvements. Engage in cross-technical, cross-discipline project teams to maximize the benefits of Enterprise Resource Planning systems. Offer operational support in the development and maintenance of the enterprise information architecture. Support ERP initiatives by participating in the design, development, and implementation of plans that translate enterprise information system objectives into technical business systems. Contribute to person-centered care initiatives undertaken by 2P. Enhance the customer experience with compassion, respect, and dignity. Undertake other relevant tasks as needed. Collaborate closely to establish a well-managed service. Oversee and contribute to the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) to ensure that 2P\'s ERP and GRP systems remain state-of-the-art. ','Educational/Professional Qualifications: Educational     : Bachelor degree Professional    : IT, Finance. Business Administration, MISCertification    : Oracle Unified Method-Business Suite or relevant certifications Licensing         : Optional OCS OUM , AIM, PMP , TOGAFProfessional Experience:            Eight (8) years of professional-level expertise in functional configuration, modification, or maintenance of ERP Financial systems, with a preference for experience in a team management or supervisory role.         Specialized Knowledge: Knowledge of ERP Financial Management systems modules with an emphasis on Finance, Reporting, Budget Control System, and Funds Management Knowledge of Finance modules with an emphasis on Accounts Receivables, Accounts Payable, General Ledger, Fixed Assets and AGIS. Working experience on using techniques of systems analysis, functional configuration, and testing Well understanding for public sector finance processes and procedures Methods of developing operational process specifications Characteristics and capabilities of state-of-the art technology in financial information processing. Maintain professional standards for business systems, procedures, and methods within the areas of finance, budgeting, and accounting. Knowledge of kingdom laws, ordinances, codes, and regulations related to financial, budgetary, and accounting information processing. Principles of organization and management Principles of documentation Principles of supervision, team building, and training. Core Competencies Driver of Excellence Team Builder and Effective Communicator Safety and Health Promoter Customer Sponsor Person Specifications: Ability to learn new technologies and implement them successfully. Self-confidence and interpersonal skills Delivering Results and Meeting Customer Expectations Able to manage time effectively, set priorities appropriately, schedule calls Highly energetic, well organized and multitasking Awareness of sensitive cultural differences Stress & Time Management Working patiently with Users and Management Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities','2023-10-22',19,19,8,10,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Perfect Presentation',NULL),('Senior Front End Developer (Blockchain)','Egypt','Giza','6th of October','Build backend APIs and services that power new products that interact with Ethereum (or other) blockchains Build front-end Web3 interfaces that interact with your backend code Solid understanding and appreciation for clean, scalable architecture A mastery of Node.js and React, and database design (Postgres/Mongo/etc)Mastery of designing APIs and building scalable RESTful services Ability to quickly iterate on and ship code using test-driven development patterns Experience using web3 related libraries such as web3.js and ether.js Exposure to Web3 tools such as hardhat, truffle etc. Experience with, Next.js, Typescript You have excellent verbal and written communication skills—especially the ability to clearly and concisely communicate complicated technical concepts to diverse audiences. Technologies used React.js Node.js Typescript (preferred)Javascript Ethers.js / web3.js Hardhat Solidity','BSc.  Degree/master in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.least 4 years of experience, ideally within a Software Engineer role. Proficient in HTML / CSS / Javascript, familiar with ES6/Typescript. Proficient in React Framework. Proficient in using but not reliant on mainstream front-end libraries. Experience with blockchain and web3.js. Possess good coding habits. Good communication skills.','2023-09-01',29,29,4,6,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Perfect Presentation',NULL),('Senior systems analyst','Egypt','Giza','6th of October',' Implements computer system requirements by defining and analyzing system problems; designing and testing standards and solutions. Defines application problem by conferring with clients; evaluating procedures and processes. Develops solution by preparing and evaluating alternative workflow solutions. Controls solution by establishing specifications; coordinating production with programmers. Validates results by testing programs. Familiar with data analytical tools Ensures operation by training client personnel; providing support. Provides reference by writing documentation. Updates job knowledge by participating in educational opportunities; reading professional publications; maintaining personal networks; participating in professional organizations. Accomplishes information systems and organization mission by completing related results as needed','Bachelor of Engineering or a Bachelor of Technology degree from a recognized university.8+ years of relevant experience.   Exceptional analytical and conceptual thinking skills. The ability to influence stakeholders and work closely with them to determine acceptable solutions. Advanced technical skills. Excellent documentation skills. Fundamental analytical and conceptual thinking skills. Experience creating detailed reports and giving presentations. Competency in Microsoft applications including Word, Excel, and Outlook. A record of accomplishment of following through on commitments. Excellent planning, organizational, and time management skills. Preferred to have experience in Power BI, Web Services & DB ','2023-10-02',10,10,8,10,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Perfect Presentation',NULL),('BIM Solutions Architect','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Persistence Recruitment, working on behalf of Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund (PIF) Sovereign Fund Tourism and Culture Giga-Project, is seeking a talented Digital Construction BIM Solutions Architect to play a key role in advancing construction technology for one of the most ambitious cultural and tourism development projects in the world. This project represents a US$50 billion investment in creating a global cultural and tourism destination, and we are looking for exceptional talent to join our team.',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('BIM Solutions Designer','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Persistence Recruitment is a leading recruitment agency specializing in sourcing top talent for critical projects worldwide. We are proud to represent the Public Investment Fund (PIF) of Saudi Arabia in their ambitious US$50 billion Sovereign Fund Tourism and Culture Giga-Project. This groundbreaking initiative aims to revolutionize the tourism and culture sector in the region, and we are seeking an exceptional Solutions Delivery Manager to contribute to its success. Role Overview: As a Digital Construction BIM Solution Designer, you will play a pivotal role in designing and implementing Building Information Modeling (BIM) solutions, with a specific focus on BIM-360. Your expertise in BIM technology and design will be instrumental in enhancing construction processes and outcomes within this transformative project. Key Responsibilities:  Solution Design: Collaborate with project stakeholders to design BIM solutions, ensuring alignment with project requirements and goals.  BIM Modeling: Develop and manage BIM models, templates, and libraries using BIM-360 and other relevant tools  Quality Assurance: Conduct regular quality checks to ensure BIM models adhere to industry standards and project specifications.  Documentation: Maintain comprehensive documentation of BIM design processes, standards, and guidelines.   Training and Support: Provide training and technical support to project teams to facilitate effective use of BIM solutions  Innovation: Stay current with industry trends and emerging BIM technologies, proposing innovative solutions to enhance project efficiency and quality..  Collaboration: Foster effective communication and collaboration among cross functional teams, including architects, engineers, contractors, and subcontractors. Qualifications Bachelor’s degree in Architecture, Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or a related field. Advanced degrees and relevant certifications are advantageous Proven experience as a BIM Solution Designer in construction projects, with expertise in BIM-360. Proficiency in BIM software and tools, including Auto CAD, Revit, and Navisworks Strong understanding of BIM standards and best practices. Effective problem-solving skills and attention to detail  Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.  This is a unique opportunity to be part of a historic project that will reshape Saudi Arabia\'s construction industry. If you are a talented Digital Construction BIM Solution Designer with expertise in BIM-360, we invite you to join us on this transformative journey. Persistence Recruitment is committed to diversity and is an equal opportunity employer. Candidates from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. To apply for this position, please submit your resume along with a cover letter highlighting your relevant experience and explaining why you are the ideal candidate for this role',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('Business Analyst - Saudi National Preferred','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','About Us: Persistence Recruitment is honored to represent a prominent client working on behalf of Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund (PIF) for the USD $17 billion Sovereign Fund Culture and Tourism Destination Giga-Project. Our client is dedicated to transforming Saudi Arabia\'s culture and tourism sector with a vision to create a world-class destination. Role Overview: We are looking for a dedicated Business Analyst, with a preference for Saudi National candidates, to join our dynamic team. As a Business Analyst, you will play a crucial role in shaping the future of Saudi Arabia\'s culture and tourism sector. Your primary responsibilities will involve working closely with stakeholders, collecting and analyzing data, and providing valuable insights to support the project\'s success. Key Responsibilities: Data Gathering: Collaborate with various stakeholders to gather and document business requirements for the project.  Analysis: Conduct in-depth analysis to identify process improvements and efficiencies that align with the project\'s objectives.  Documentation: Translate business needs into clear technical specifications to guide project implementation.  Alignment: Ensure that IT solutions and project strategies align with business objectives and goals ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('Construction Apps - Solutions Delivery Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Persistence Recruitment is a leading recruitment agency specializing in sourcing top talent for critical projects worldwide. We are honored to represent the Public Investment Fund (PIF) of Saudi Arabia in their ambitious US$50 billion Sovereign Fund Tourism and Culture Giga-Project. This transformative initiative aims to redefine the tourism and culture sector in the region. We are seeking an exceptional Solutions Delivery Manager with expertise in Primavera P6, Unifier, Aconex, and In Eight to contribute to the success of this groundbreaking project Role Overview: As a Solutions Delivery Manager in the field of Digital Construction and Construction Apps, you will have a pivotal role in ensuring the successful implementation of key project management and construction technologies. Your expertise in Primavera P6, Unifier, Aconex, and In Eight will be instrumental in streamlining project processes, enhancing collaboration, and driving efficiency across the Giga-Project Key Responsibilities: 1. Solution Implementation: Lead the end-to-end implementation of Primavera P6, Unifier, Aconex, and In Eight solutions across various project sites, ensuring they align with project-specific requirements. 2. Stakeholder Collaboration: Collaborate closely with project managers, construction teams, and other stakeholders to define project goals and requirements. 3. Technology Integration: Oversee the integration of these solutions with other project management and construction tools to ensure seamless data flow and information exchange. 4. Quality Assurance: Implement robust quality control processes to maintain accurate and reliable data within the project management and construction apps. 5. Training and Support: Develop training programs and provide support to project teams in effectively utilizing these technologies for enhanced project delivery. 6. Continuous Improvement: Stay updated on industry trends and advancements in construction technology to recommend improvements and optimizations.',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('CRM - Solutions Delivery Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Persistence Recruitment is a leading recruitment agency specializing in talent acquisition for transformative projects. We are proud to represent the Saudi Arabia Public Investment Fund (PIF) and their ambitious US$50 billion Sovereign Fund Tourism and Culture Giga-Project, a visionary endeavor set to reshape the tourism and culture sector. Job Description: We are seeking an experienced Solutions Delivery Manager with expertise in CRM & e Commerce and skilled in SAP C4C, Google Analytics, Databox, Sprinklr, Chatbots, Data & Analytics to join our team for this groundbreaking project. In this role, you will be responsible for overseeing the successful delivery of CRM and e Commerce solutions, ensuring they align with project objectives and drive optimal performance. Key Responsibilities: 1. CRM Implementation: Lead the implementation of CRM systems, particularly SAP C4C, ensuring alignment with project objectives and timelines. 2. e Commerce Integration: Collaborate with the e Commerce team to integrate CRM solutions seamlessly, enhancing customer interactions and driving revenue growth. 3. Data & Analytics: Utilize tools like Google Analytics, Databox, and Sprinklr to gather insights and drive data-driven decision-making within the CRM and e Commerce platforms. 4. Chatbots Integration: Work closely with chatbot developers to integrate AIpowered chatbots into the CRM and e Commerce systems for improved customer engagement. 5. Performance Monitoring: Develop and implement monitoring processes to track CRM and e Commerce performance, identifying areas for improvement and optimization. 6. Team Leadership: Manage a team of specialists in CRM, e Commerce, data, analytics, and chatbots, providing guidance, support, and fostering a culture of excellence. 7. Stakeholder Collaboration: Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure CRM and e Commerce solutions align with broader project goals. 8. Reporting: Generate regular reports on CRM and e Commerce performance and provide insights to project stakeholders.',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('eCommerce - Solutions Delivery Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Persistence Recruitment is honored to represent a prestigious client on behalf of Saudi Arabia\'s Public Investment Fund (PIF), who is driving the USD $17 billion Sovereign Fund Culture and Tourism Destination Giga-Project. This visionary initiative aims to revolutionize Saudi Arabia\'s culture and tourism sector by creating a world-class destination. Role Overview: We are seeking a skilled Solutions Delivery Manager specializing in CRM & e Commerce to join our team. As a Solutions Delivery Manager, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the successful implementation and management of e Commerce solutions, with a focus on platforms such as Sitecore, Kentico, Word Press, Ticketing Platforms, and Event Management Key Responsibilities: 1. Project Leadership: Lead and oversee project teams to ensure the successful delivery of CRM and e Commerce solutions. 2. Solution Implementation: Collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement and manage CRM and e Commerce systems. 3. Platform Management: Work with platforms like Sitecore, Kentico, Word Press, Ticketing Platforms, and Event Management to create exceptional customer experiences. 4. Quality Assurance: Ensure high-quality project outcomes and deliverables in line with business objectives',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('IT Business Analyst - Saudi National Preferred','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','About Us: Persistence Recruitment is honored to represent a prominent client working on behalf of Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund (PIF) for the USD $17 billion Sovereign Fund Culture and Tourism Destination Giga-Project. Our client is dedicated to transforming Saudi Arabia\'s culture and tourism sector with a vision to create a world-class destination. Role Overview: We are looking for a dedicated Business Analyst, with a preference for Saudi National candidates, to join our dynamic team. As a Business Analyst, you will play a crucial role in shaping the future of Saudi Arabia\'s culture and tourism sector. Your primary responsibilities will involve working closely with stakeholders, collecting and analyzing data, and providing valuable insights to support the project\'s success. Key Responsibilities: Data Gathering: Collaborate with various stakeholders to gather and document business requirements for the project.  Analysis: Conduct in-depth analysis to identify process improvements and efficiencies that align with the project\'s objectives.  Documentation: Translate business needs into clear technical specifications to guide project implementation.  Alignment: Ensure that IT solutions and project strategies align with business objectives and goals ',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('Senior Product Manager - CRM & Ecommerce','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Persistence Recruitment is working on behalf of a prestigious client, the Saudi Arabia Public Investment Fund (PIF), which oversees a groundbreaking $17 billion Sovereign Fund dedicated to Culture and Tourism. This visionary project aims to transform the tourism sector, revitalize culture, and enhance visitor experiences on an unprecedented scale. Job Description: As a Senior Product Manager specializing in CRM and Ecommerce, you will play a pivotal role in shaping the digital landscape of the $17 billion Culture and Tourism Destination Giga-Project. In this capacity, your primary objective is to lead the development and management of CRM and Ecommerce solutions. Your expertise will contribute to the delivery of exceptional experiences for tourists and culture enthusiasts. Key Responsibilities: 1. Product Strategy: Develop and execute a comprehensive product strategy for CRM and Ecommerce that aligns with the project\'s objectives and vision. 2. Product Lifecycle Management: Oversee the entire product lifecycle, from conceptualization to post-launch performance monitoring, ensuring its continuous improvement. 3. Cross-functional Collaboration: Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including developers, designers, marketers, and business analysts, to translate the project\'s vision into practical solutions. 4. Market and Competitor Analysis: Conduct in-depth market and competitor analysis to identify trends, opportunities, and threats. Use this information to refine product strategies. 5. User-Centric Design: Champion user-centered design principles to ensure the products are intuitive, engaging, and customer-friendly. 6. Feature Prioritization: Define and prioritize product features, creating detailed product specifications and requirements. 7. Performance Metrics: Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure and evaluate product performance. Continually analyze data to drive product improvements. 8. User Feedback: Collect and analyze user feedback to make data-driven decisions. Conduct user testing and customer surveys to gain insights. 9. Stakeholder Communication: Maintain clear and open communication with stakeholders, providing regular updates on product development progress. ',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Persistence Recruitment',NULL),('Senior SEO / Senior Search Engine Optimization','Egypt','Giza','Mohandessin','Responsibilities·       Execute tests, collect and analyze data and results, identify trends and insights in order to achieve maximum ROI in paid search campaigns·       Track, report, and analyze website analytics and PPC initiatives and campaigns·       Manage campaign expenses, staying on budget, estimating monthly costs and reconciling discrepancies.·       Optimize copy and landing pages for search engine marketing·       Perform ongoing keyword discovery, expansion and optimization·       Research and implement search engine optimization recommendations·       Research and analyze competitor advertising links·       Develop and implement link building strategy·       Work with the development team to ensure SEO best practices are properly implemented on newly developed code·       Work with editorial and marketing teams to drive SEO in content creation and content programming.·       Recommend changes to website architecture, content, linking and other factors to improve SEO positions for target keywords.',NULL,'2023-10-31',NULL,NULL,3,5,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','PETC',NULL),('Advisor I - HSSE','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Petrofac is a leading international service provider to the energy industry, with a diverse client portfolio including many of the world’s leading energy companies. We design, build, manage and maintain infrastructure for our clients. We recruit, reward, and develop our people based on merit regardless of race, nationality, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, marital status or disability. We value our people and treat everyone who works for or with Petrofac fairly and without discrimination. The world is re-thinking its energy supply and energy security needs, planning for a phased transition to alternative energy sources. We are here to help our clients meet these evolving energy needs. This is an exciting time to join us on this journey. We support flexible working requests and have adopted a hybrid approach for most of our office-based roles. We ask employees to be present in the office at least three days per week. Are you ready to bring the right energy to Petrofac and help us deliver a better future for everyone? JOB TITLE: ADVISOR 1 - HSEKEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Assist with developing HSE plans that comply with Company policies and procedures as well as client requirements.\nEnsure training, toolbox meetings, and drills are implemented as part of the training and HSE program, i.e., emergency response systems, etc.\nInvestigate and complete the process for close out of all Accident Investigation Reports and prepare/submit lessons learned for promulgation to the management.\nOversee day-to-day HSE activities in accordance with designated areas of responsibility. Assistance in the implementation of HSE component.\nAssist in the development of project specific HSE procedures. \nConduct HSE trainings and orientation to all new employees as required.\nApplication of hazard identification and risk assessment processes in designated areas of responsibility and implementation of appropriate control measures to reduce the risks to ALARP.\nEnsure HSE requirements are communicated to all relevant personnel in designated areas of responsibility and verify compliance by all appropriate means (meetings, inspections, monitoring, and audits).\nPromote HSE awareness through participating in HSE awareness campaigns.\nParticipate fully and openly in all compliance assurance audits, inspections, performance meetings, etc.\nCarry out other related tasks as advised by the supervisor.\nESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS: Bachelor Degree(4 years) OR Diploma (3 years) (from an institution of higher learning authorized to grant academic degrees in the country of issue)\nNEBOSH IGC or equivalent \nLead or Internal Auditor (ISO 45001/ ISO 14001)\nMinimum 4-5 years’ experience in HSE in any industry, with at least 1 year experience in construction, fabrication, installation and/or commissioning projects / operations / production in the oil & gas or petrochemical industries.\nAbility to conduct HSE orientation / induction/HSE awareness sessions to workers\nAbility to understand and implement HSE plans, Welfare plans, Emergency response procedures/plans and site specific HSE procedures / work instructions.\nPractical experience in implementation of Safe System of Work (PTW/ WMS/ Risk Assessment etc.) \nAwareness of practical H2S control measures.\nAbility to conduct HSE inspections\nAbility to understand and implement incident reporting and investigation procedures\nAbility to speak read and write English with good communication skills\n        #LI-SJ1\nAdditional Information ',NULL,'2023-10-11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Petrofac',NULL),('Engineer I - Quality','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Petrofac is a leading international service provider to the energy industry, with a diverse client portfolio including many of the world’s leading energy companies. We design, build, manage and maintain infrastructure for our clients. We recruit, reward, and develop our people based on merit regardless of race, nationality, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, marital status or disability. We value our people and treat everyone who works for or with Petrofac fairly and without discrimination. The world is re-thinking its energy supply and energy security needs, planning for a phased transition to alternative energy sources. We are here to help our clients meet these evolving energy needs. This is an exciting time to join us on this journey. We support flexible working requests and have adopted a hybrid approach for most of our office-based roles. We ask employees to be present in the office at least three days per week. Are you ready to bring the right energy to Petrofac and help us deliver a better future for everyone? JOB TITLE: Engineer I - Quality, Piping (Test pack/Hydrotest)KEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Review pressure test packages as per P&ID, Isometric drawings, test limit drawings and all related documents.\nEnsure installation of piping is in compliance with isometric drawings and code requirements with respect to; material, alignment, supports, valve type, valve orientation, heat trace, insulation, marking, tapings, take offs. \nEnsure satisfactory identification of materials, proper protection of piping and fittings. \nEnsure operation of flange management system to include correct flange class, flange type, alignment, gasket, orifice plate, bolts, washers, nuts, bolt torque, use of insulation kit. \nLine check prior to pressure test, ensuring provision of additional supports when required, spring hangers are locked, instruments, orifice plates and equipment are isolated or removed, blind flanges are correctly rated and certified, valves removed or isolated, vent and drain valves installed. \nPrepare punch list prior to pressure test, categorize items, ensure all A-items cleared prior to pressure test. \nWitness pressure test ensure gauges and recorders are within valid calibration, inhibitors in use as required by specification, line flushed, vented and filled. Monitor pressure and sign off records. \nPrepare final punch list of outstanding actions/items, categorize and monitor clearance.\nInspect line reinstatement, drain, dry and preservation and sign off records.\nESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS: Diploma or Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent. \nShall have 10 years of relevant industrial experience, including 6 years’ experience as Piping - Test pack/Hydrotest Inspector.\nPreferably having ASNT NDT Level II in MT, RT, PT, UT methods \nHaving CSWP 3.1 or AWS CWI certification is an added advantage.\nShall have a demonstrated background and thorough knowledge of codes such as ANSI B 31.3, 31.4 and 31.8, ASME Section V and IX, AWS D1.1, required for the execution of the work.\nShould have experience in oil & gas/petrochemical industry.\nShould have previously worked with major EPC contractor or their sub-contractors.\n\nAdditional Information ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Petrofac',NULL),('Principal Engineer - Cathodic Protection','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Petrofac is a leading international service provider to the energy industry, with a diverse client portfolio including many of the world’s leading energy companies. We design, build, manage and maintain infrastructure for our clients. We recruit, reward, and develop our people based on merit regardless of race, nationality, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, marital status or disability. We value our people and treat everyone who works for or with Petrofac fairly and without discrimination. The world is re-thinking its energy supply and energy security needs; planning for a phased transition to alternative energy sources. We are here to help our clients meet these evolving energy needs. This is an exciting time to join us on this journey.   We support flexible working requests and have adopted a hybrid approach for most of our office-based roles. We ask employees to be present in the office at least three days per week. Are you ready to bring the right energy to Petrofac and help us deliver a better future for everyone? JOB TITLE: Principal Engineer - Cathodic Protection KEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Accountable for overall discipline related activities for the successful completion of project within allotted schedule, manpower and costs.\nPrepare and issue Cathodic Protection Design basis, Specification and other technical documents\nReview of Vendor offers and design package\nCoordinate on technical issues with other Engineering Disciplines as required. Provide the necessary inputs/data to other disciplines as per the requirements and procedures.\n\nParticipate in 3D Model and Constructability reviews along with Client and representatives of other engineering disciplines\nMeet with vendor representatives, inspect at vendor works and workshops and provide assistance to Quality Department as required.\n\nInterface and provide clarifications, guidance and technical support to Construction and Commissioning teams as required.\nESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS: Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical/Metallurgy/Electrochemical Engineering \nMinimum of 15 years related oil & gas/petrochemical experience preferable, with a background of working for EPC/consultancy organizations/CP specialist Vendors\n\nAdditional Information ',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Petrofac',NULL),('Principal Engineer - Information Management','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Petrofac is a leading international service provider to the energy industry, with a diverse client portfolio including many of the world’s leading energy companies. We design, build, manage, and maintain infrastructure for our clients. We recruit, reward, and develop our people based on merit, regardless of race, nationality, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, marital status, or disability. We value our people and treat everyone who works for or with Petrofac fairly and without discrimination. The world is re-thinking its energy supply and energy security needs and planning for a phased transition to alternative energy sources. We are here to help our clients meet these evolving energy needs. This is an exciting time to join us on this journey. We support flexible working requests and have adopted a hybrid approach for most of our office-based roles. We ask employees to be present in the office at least three days per week. Petrofac is currently looking to recruit a principal engineer in information management to be based in the UAE. Are you ready to bring the right energy to Petrofac and help us deliver a better future for everyone?JOB TITLE:   PRINCIPAL ENGINEER, INFORMATION MANAGEMENTKEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Manage the contractor IM team, including document controllers and data controllers.\nCoordinate with the company functional support team to set up and configure project document management systems (repository and control) in accordance with this contract.\nManage all paper and electronic document and data flow within the scope of this contract, including sub-contractors or vendors, and report directly to the Technical Services Manager.\nAccountable for the implementation of the requirements of Contract Section C6.9.\nExecutes specific contractual SOW and terms, IM Plan/IM Delivery Plan, input to key project management documents, budget, handover plan, monitoring of QA, and progress management.\nDeliver applicable IM deliverables (EDW, SAP-PM, CIMS, Vendor MRB, Critical Documents, 3D models, and other EDS seed files, etc.) as per the project’s closeout requirements Liaise with COMPANY Engineering and Projects IM Manage interfaces with sub-contractors and vendors.\nDevelop and implement a contract IM strategy and contract IM plan, including associated IM procedures and guidelines and an information handover plan and procedures.\nEnsure that the IM Scopes of Work in this contract are reflected in all sub-contracts and requisitions. Develop contract IM KPIs and reports for monitoring progress against contract IM KPIs and the IM Plan. Establish IM Quality Framework for the Contract Conduct self-assessment IM quality health checks.\nESSENTIAL QUALIFICATION & SKILLS: A minimum of 10 years of experience in projects (oil and gas, petrochemicals, etc.) with more than 5 years’ experience in the information management domain executing specific IM delivery plans\nKnowledge and experience of standards and practices related to project IM strategy and planning, project document control, project data control, and handover\nKnowledge of project management and engineering processes and interaction with project managers, service managers, project engineers, and discipline engineers\nKnowledge and experience of common document and data management tools (such as EDMS, Engineering Data Warehouse, etc.)\nKnowledge and experience of typical interaction with subcontractors and suppliers on document and data flow.\n       #LI-JN1\nAdditional Information ',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Petrofac',NULL),('Principal Engineer - Metallurgy & Corrosion','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Petrofac is a leading international service provider to the energy industry, with a diverse client portfolio including many of the world’s leading energy companies. We design, build, manage and maintain infrastructure for our clients. We recruit, reward, and develop our people based on merit regardless of race, nationality, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, marital status or disability. We value our people and 