-10-25',NULL,NULL,3,7,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Premier Services and Recruitment',NULL),('.NET WPF Developer','Egypt','Cairo','','Key Responsibilities: Design, develop, and maintain software functionality within agreed timeframes and quality standards. Test specific program changes to aid development work. Provide second-level escalation for customer queries. Participate in both design and code reviews to enhance code quality. Document departmental procedures and software changes. Maintain the software build process to ensure consistency and reliability. Provide accurate estimates for development work. Collaborate with other departments and customers to address support issues effectively. Gather and document customer requirements and produce specifications. Stay updated with modern development techniques, design patterns, and quality standards.  ','Essential Skills and Experience: Proficiency in C# . NET Core. Strong knowledge of WPF, XAML, MVC, and MVVM. A deep understanding of the Windows platform, both desktop and server. Experience with web services, REST APIs, XML, and JSON. Test-driven development (TDD) practices. Demonstrable experience in working with N-tier architectures. Knowledge and experience of agile development methods.  ','2023-10-25',6,1,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Premier Services and Recruitment',NULL),('ERP Administrator','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','Main responsibilities Enterprise Applications· Responsible for the design, configuration,implementation , and support the Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP), Enterprise Document Management System EDMS, and other enterprise systems.· Work with end-users on all ERP functional modules (HR, Finance, Project Management, and others) to document business needs and requirements for system upgrades and enhancements.· Respond to business requirements (Finance, HR, Procurement, Project Management, etc.) by developing reports and alerts using SQL scripts