m.','Skills\nQualifications BA/BS degree in Business Administration or related field5+ years experience PMP certificate CIPD L5 certificate Effective written and verbal communicationstrong business acumen Excellent in English.','2023-10-24',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Professional Recruitment',NULL),('Infrastructure Engineer','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','We are currently seeking an experienced and highly skilled Infrastructure Engineer to join our team. As an Infrastructure Engineer, you will play a crucial role in designing, implementing, and maintaining the technology infrastructure to support our organization\'s operations. You will work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure the availability, reliability, and scalability of our systems and networks. The ideal candidate has a strong background in infrastructure design, experience with cloud technologies, and a passion for implementing innovative solutions. Responsibilities Collaborate with stakeholders to define and document infrastructure requirements and specifications. Design and implement robust, scalable, and high-availability infrastructure solutions. Set up, configure, and troubleshoot servers, switches, routers, and other network devices. Optimize system performance and ensure the smooth operation of our technology infrastructure. Monitor and analyze system and network performance, implementing proactive measures to identify and address potential issues. Develop and maintain infrastructure documentation, including network diagrams, configurations, and standard operating procedures. Manage and resolve infrastructure incidents and service requests, ensuring timely resolution and minimal impact to operations.','Skills\nRequirements Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field. Proven experience as an Infrastructure Engineer or a similar role. In-depth knowledge of infrastructure technologies, such as virtualization, cloud computing, and