cts of employee terminations, including exit interviews and the processing of final payments','Skills\nRequirements Bachelor\'s degree in Human Resources or a related field Proven experience in manpower administration, preferably in a large organizationknowledge of employment laws and regulations Excellent organizational and time management skills Strong attention to detail and accuracy Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite and HR software systems Exceptional interpersonal and communication skills Ability to handle sensitive and confidential information with discretion','2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Professional Recruitment',NULL),('Microsoft Dynamics Senior Technical','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','We are currently seeking a highly skilled and experienced Microsoft Dynamics Senior Technical professional to join our team. As a Microsoft Dynamics Senior Technical, your primary responsibility will be to provide technical expertise and support in the design, implementation, and enhancement of Microsoft Dynamics CRM solutions. This position requires exceptional knowledge of the Microsoft Dynamics platform and a strong understanding of CRM business processes. As a Microsoft Dynamics Senior Technical, you will be responsible for analyzing business needs and translating them into functional requirements. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and configure Microsoft Dynamics CRM applications in line with best practices. Additionally, you will be responsible for troubleshooting and resolving complex technical issues related to the Microsoft Dynamics CRM environment. To be successful in this role, you must possess excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work collaboratively with technical and business stakeholders. You should have a deep understanding of Microsoft Dynamics CRM capabilities and possess expert-level knowledge of programming languages such as C#, . NET, Java Script, and SQL. Strong communication 