ervisor and IT manger Communicate with purchasing departments regarding any IT devices spare parts needed ( Roll paper – batteries – charges – cables – USB cables – PCs)','Bachelor degree .1-3 years of experience. Good command at Microsoft excel Previous work experience at FMCG companies','2023-10-01',5,3,1,3,5000,5000,0,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'Rashideen Egypt for Trade',NULL),('Infrastructure Manager','Egypt','Cairo','','Leading the infrastructure engineering team by planning and designing for all development and operations infrastructure needs\nResponsible about designing and implementation Information Security policies for AMAN Holding network and infrastructure\nResponsible for managing AMAN Holding hardware & Data Center equipment’s/ RAC maintenance, troubleshooting and new batch processing with the suppliers and coordination of hardware repair with appropriate vendors to ensure system availability according to the agreed upon function SLA\nResponsible for hardware implementation for any new deployment to fulfill the capacity planning requirements and ensures that system hardware, operating systems, and related procedures adhere to organizational values to ensure business compliance\nResponsible about designing HA, and DR from infrastructure perspective \nManages infrastructure operations (Backup, Logs, and Infra Monitoring)\nResponsible for Operating systems through installing OS and software updates, maintaining network connectivity and integrity and monitoring for free disk space to ensure system performance optimization at all times to ensure business continuity\nResponsible for analyzing system logs, audit and identifying potential issues with the servers, storages to take preventive actions \nActing as the main focal point between AMAN and Raya Data Centre or any external providers for hosting AMAN servers',NULL,'2023-10-11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raya Holding for Financial Investments',NULL),('Senior Engineer (Customer Services)','Egypt','Cairo','','You are about to apply for a job in a certified Top Employer 2023!\nReady to be part of one of the Market Leaders in Egypt? Apply now!\nRaya Information Technology: one of Raya’s subsidiaries is hiring Engineer (customer services):\n \nWhat will you do?\nReport daily activities to CS TL/ CS SV and service helpdesk\nRespond to customers’ calls and fix them based on agreed upon quality standards and customers’ SLAs.\nPerform new ATM installations, ATM staging or sites inspection and other planned preventive maintenance visits\nAssist Customers in regards to (training, phone support, onsite support, …..)\nClose effectively his calls on incidents management system \nKeep and maintain all his HW & SW tools in a healthy condition and keep reporting continuously the cases of tools failure or any extra tools needed to his Senior / Team leader\nProvide 2nd level support for team & customers\n',NULL,'2023-10-30',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raya Holding for Financial Investments',NULL),('Senior Manager E-Payments Development','Egypt','Cairo','','Manages the development teams responsible for Payment Gateway, Acceptance Bill Payment, POS APP\nPlans technical projects with technology director listing needed tools, human resources and resources to fulfill applications/systems roadmaps\nResponsible for developing any Payment or External Integration solutions\nResponsible for leading the development cycle (Code Design, Assessment, and Review)\nProvide 3rd line of support to operations team\nSupports project management in defining technical projects milestones and phases to achieve objectives \nSupports in maintaining applications and systems architectures ensuring capacity of systems to new business objectives\nConducts technical presales activities with business development team to engage partners and service providers\n',NULL,'2023-10-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raya Holding for Financial Investments',NULL),('Information Technology Analyst','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Date Posted:2023-10-15Country: Saudi Arabia Location: SAU01115: RTN SA Riyadh Front HQ, 9054 King Khaled International Airport Street, S1, King Khaled International Airport District, Riyadh, 01, 13413-3677, Saudi Arabia Position Role Type: Unspecified About Us: At Raytheon Missiles & Defense, you have the opportunity to try new things and make a bigger difference across a broader end-to-end solution, a richer technology and product set, an expanded range of disciplines, a growing global footprint and a more diverse team of colleagues and customers. Job Summary: We are currently seeking an intelligent and proactive Information Technology Analyst who is ready to advance their career and contribute to service delivery and customer excellence at our office locations in Saudi Arabia. This role encompasses providing support not just at our Riyadh office but also to employees across all our sites throughout the country. Working closely with your supervisor and other DT team members, you will play a pivotal role in driving positive changes within our Workplace Services Team. By joining our team, you will benefit from the support of a local team as well as access to global expertise. We are dedicated to your professional growth and offer a tailored development program to ensure your success in this role. This is an excellent opportunity to make a significant impact and contribute to our mission of delivering exceptional IT services while providing excellent customer experiences. Join us on this exciting journey and help shape the future of our service delivery in Saudi Arabia. Responsibilities to Anticipate: Address the day-to-day IT support needs of end users by providing exceptional support for incident, service request, and problem management. Attend to end user requests through various channels such as phone, walk-ups, and online ticketing systems. Configure, deploy, and relocate desktops, laptops, printers, and any other related devices. Ensures optimal performance of the local area network (LAN) and workstations. Identify, troubleshoot, resolve, and document end-user system issues requests. Open and follow up with tech support from global DT team. Identifies problems and provides guidance to clients on corrective steps. Writes and maintains documentation to enhance client references. Enhances system performance by solving problems and recommending effective changes. Qualifications You Must Have: University degree in computer science, Information Technology, or a related field.and less than 2 years priorrelevant experience. Excellent collaboration skills and ability to work across diverse organizations and teams. Proficient in Arabic and English (both written and oral); must be able to communicate effectively with all levels of management via email, telephone, and in person. Demonstrated analytic expertise – to include ability to think critically and logically in a dynamic, high-pressure, fast-paced environment. Understanding of systems integrations for applications Qualifications We Value: Display exceptional communication and presentation skills with a willingness to learn and provide an innovative approach.  Analytical and problem-solving skills to effectively troubleshoot and diagnose issues. Strong time management skills to provide timely updates and fixes within promised time frames. Excellent customer service skills to interact professionally and positively with employees and coworkers. Analyze service data and evaluate results to choose the best resolutions to customer service challenges. RTX is An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age or any other federally protected class. Privacy Policy and Terms: Click on this link to read the Policy and Terms',NULL,'2023-10-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raytheon',NULL),('Interactive Learning Specialist (KSA)','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Date Posted:2023-10-11Country: United States of America Location: TX001: El Paso 7201 Montana Avenue , El Paso, TX, 79925 USAPosition Role Type: Onsite At Raytheon, the foundation of everything we do is rooted in our values and a higher calling – to help our nation and allies defend freedoms and deter aggression. We bring the strength of more than 100 years of experience and renowned engineering expertise to meet the needs of today’s mission and stay ahead of tomorrow’s threat. Our team solves tough, meaningful problems that create a safer, more secure world. Job Description The Interactive Learning Specialist will perform duties and responsibilities on the Hawk Patriot Sustainment Contract (HPSC) in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. This individual will be assigned to the Air Defense Forces Institute, and will be responsible for making changes to, and converting the Patriot Training Department curriculum into an interactive curriculum that will enable cadets to interact with the courses. This individual will also create scenarios in 3D that are covered under the currently approved TAA. The specialist should possess information technology skills, knowledge of multimedia software and hardware, and an ability to correct the difficulties and problems associated with modern technology.  Advises instructors and cadets on the use of the 3D interaction material used in the curriculum. Reviews progress of assigned class or students and makes recommendations to improve the quality of patriot training at the Air Defense Forces institute. Participates in all other functions of the training department as directed. The individual will also provide Technical Instruction and Training at the Air Defense Forces Institute (ADFI) using conference and practical exercise teaching methods. Topics would include Patriot System operations and maintenance. Performs other related duties as directed by the section officer. Participates in on-the-job training programs, and assists the section officer in enforcing safety policies, procedures, and standards. Identifies faulty work practices and demonstrates proper maintenance and troubleshooting techniques. Required Skills: Ability to develop training programs for certifying Soldiers in Air Defense systems and posture. Demonstrated experience in the technical support and operations of the ICC, ECS, RS, CRG, BMC, IFF, AMG, GMT, LRPT AND LS. Possess two (2) years or more experience in system programming and full knowledge of the following systems and programming languages: C# , C++, ADP. NET, MYSQL, and SQL Server At least one (1) year of experience working in a multimedia work environment or equivalent work experience Desired Skills: Experience in the frequent use and general knowledge of industry practices, techniques, and standards. Minimum of 4 years of direct experience with organizational level maintenance on Patriot Missile Systems. Required Education: Bachelor degree in one of the following majors: Science, Computer Engineering, or Information System or 4 years of relevant experience High School diploma or 8 years of relevant experience What We Offer: Whether you’re just starting out on your career journey or are an experienced professional, we offer a total rewards package that goes above and beyond with compensation; healthcare, wellness, retirement, and work/life benefits; career development and recognition programs. Some of the benefits we offer include parental (including paternal) leave, flexible work schedules, achievement awards, educational assistance, and child/adult backup care. Additional Information: Onsite: Employees who are working in Onsite roles will work primarily onsite. This includes all production and maintenance employees, as they are essential to the development of our products. This requisition is eligible for an employee referral award.  ALL eligibility requirements must be met to receive the referral award. RTX is An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age or any other federally protected class. Privacy Policy and Terms: Click on this link to read the Policy and Terms',NULL,'2023-10-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raytheon',NULL),('Senior Administration Analyst','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Date Posted:2023-10-19Country: Saudi Arabia Location: SAU01115: RTN SA Riyadh Front HQ, 9054 King Khaled International Airport Street, S1, King Khaled International Airport District, Riyadh, 01, 13413-3677, Saudi Arabia Position Role Type: Unspecified About Us: At Raytheon Missiles & Defense, by combining our vast resources and investments, we are able to dedicate ourselves to solving mission-level vs. product-level customer challenges – together we can anticipate more, move faster and make a bigger impact on the big picture. Job Summary: Raytheon Arabian Systems Company (RASC) is currently seeking a highly competent and professional Office Administrator to oversee and meticulously manage all aspects of correspondence, document control, data files, and overall office operations. A successful candidate will demonstrate exceptional organizational skills and uncompromising attention to detail. Responsibilities to Anticipate: Preparation and typing of correspondence and documents. Maintenance of correspondence and document filing system Document control Review of documents for completeness and accuracy Preparation of periodic reports as requested by the Department Manager Assist in the preparation of various presentations. Planning for meetings, travel and hotel bookings Perform other administrative duties as assigned. Qualifications You Must Have: Bachelor’s Degree, preferably in Business Administration, International Studies, or Political Science. A minimum of two years of prior relevant experience Proven ability to compose written correspondence. Well versed with personal computer and business application software (Word, Excel, Power Point, Excellent command of English language (oral and written)Qualifications We Value: Demonstrated ability to work effectively with coworkers from diverse communities and cultures. Demonstrated ability to work with colleagues who represent a diversity of work and conflict resolution styles. This position requires a Saudi national who is eligible to obtain any required Export Authorization. RTX is An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age or any other federally protected class. Privacy Policy and Terms: Click on this link to read the Policy and Terms',NULL,'2023-10-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raytheon',NULL),('Senior Analyst, Procurement','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Date Posted:2023-10-11Country: Saudi Arabia Location: SAU02113: Raymes Compound, 7040 Kahlil Al Azdi Street, Al Zahra District, Jeddah, 02, 23522-6943, Saudi Arabia Position Role Type: Unspecified About Us: Raytheon Saudi Arabia (RTN SA) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Raytheon Technologies Company (RTX) headquartered in Riyadh, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. Established in 2017, RTN SA builds on Raytheon’s fifty years of continuous presence providing comprehensive defense and security solutions to Saudi Arabian government and commercial customers. These innovative solutions and services are increasingly developed by Saudi citizens and delivered in Saudi Arabia and to the global market in a way that contributes to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia’s lasting security and economic development. RTN SA is a strategic supporter of Saudi Arabia’s Vision 2030. Job Summary: This position is responsible for executes, monitors & follows up on purchasing daily activities, so the company gets its needs in accordance with RTX policies. Verifies requirements, communicates with Requestor and Suppliers. Performs local market search for requirements for best price, quality, delivery.  Obtains RFQ, quotes and goods/services as required. Register new Suppliers/Vendors in ESD Website. Verifies purchase request., prepares, generates and forwards purchase orders. Generate PO in SAP. Coordinates with WH receipt of Items & Goods. Responsibilities to Anticipate: Policies & Procedures Development Develops and implements procurement policies and procedures. Ensures compliance with Saudi Market & Commerce policies and regulations. Performs regular self-assessments and updates to procurement processes and systems. Recommends and suggests new methods to improve the procurement process. People Management Provides clear direction and prioritizes tasks to others. Monitors the workflow of the procurement department. Provides guidance and support to other procurement team members. Influences internal and external customers to comply with company policies and regulations. Operational Management Reviews and approves purchase requisitions and specifications. Negotiates with suppliers to secure the best possible prices, terms, and conditions. Creates and issues purchase orders. Communicates with suppliers and internal stakeholders to ensure the timely and accurate delivery of goods and services. Performs other related tasks as assigned to ensure the efficient and effective functioning of the procurement department. Main Contacts Requestor / CAM / User Units / End Users (Internal)Vendors (External)Qualifications You Must Have: Bachelor level degree in supply chain/ Business Administration or any related filed. Minimum three years of experience in procurement & local market. Regularly contributes to the development of new concepts, techniques, and standards. Organizes and prioritizes unit workload to meet deadlines and operating needs. A valid Saudi driver\'s license is required. Knowledge of local marketing practices and Local procurement experience. Advanced English and Arabic language skills (Oral, Written)Qualifications We Value: Prior experience in using the SAP. Ability to work with all levels of employees, management, suppliers and Customers. RTX is An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age or any other federally protected class. Privacy Policy and Terms: Click on this link to read the Policy and Terms',NULL,'2023-10-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Raytheon',NULL),('Sales Account Manager','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','Meet and exceed targets for net-new revenue and sales pipeline, accurately forecast sales, pipeline and usage for the products and solutions in scope. Generating and contacting sales leads and set up appointments to present company products. Effectively turn prospects and qualified leads into opportunities and revenue pipeline by filtering them through different criteria Lead designated territory, including accounts, account relationships, prospect profiling, and sales cycles. Maintaining an accurate record of all leads, customer accounts, and sales. Strategically negotiating with potential and existing customers to close sales. Generating and submitting sales reports on time. Establish, develop and maintain positive business and customer relationships. Coordinating sales effort with team members and other departments. Supplying management with reports on customer needs, problems, interests, competitive activities, and potential for new products and services. Demand Generation, Pipeline and Opportunity Management. Actively seek out new sales opportunities through cold calling, networking, and social media. Prepare and deliver appropriate presentations on products and services. Define price schedules and discount rates after approval from the higher management. Follow-up through CRM on the projects and cases related to his customers. Meeting daily, weekly and monthly KPI’s in order to hit targets provided.','5-7+ years of software sales experience with a proven track record of success. A self-starter with a track record of outstanding performance and achieving goals. Fluency in English is required. Good business sense. General knowledge of the IT industry, with the capacity to learn and retain knowledge about individual products and business solutions quickly and accurately. Solid time management skills and ability to work independently or under supervision with a high level of integrity. Team working capability. The ability to build relationships quickly and effectively. Experience in B2B AI solutions (OCR, Speech-to-text, Text-to-Speech, NLP, ...) is a plus. Analytical and problem-solving skills. Strong technical skills and product knowledge. Self-motivated.','2023-10-24',0,0,5,7,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','RDI',NULL),('Senior Android Developer','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','RDI is looking for individuals who enjoy the thrill of a growing organization and who can work with an expert team to deliver cutting edge technology services. RDI is looking for an Senior Android Developer who possesses a passion for pushing mobile technologies to the limits. The developer will work with our team of talented engineers to design and build the next generation of our mobile applications. Android programming works closely with other app development and technical teams. Responsibilities: Build advanced applications for the Android platform. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features. Work with outside data sources and APIs. Unit-test code for robustness, including edge cases, usability, and general reliability. Ensure the best possible performance, quality, and responsiveness of the application Work on bug fixing and improving application performance. Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize development efficiency.','Requirements:3+ years of experience with Android SDK. Strong understanding of interactive application development, memory management, file I/O, network programming, concurrency and multi-threading. Proven software development experience and Android skills development Proven working experience in Android app development Experience working with remote data via REST and JSONExperience with third-party libraries and APIs Working knowledge of the general mobile landscape, architectures, trends, and emerging technologies. Solid understanding of the full mobile development life cycle. Strong and innovative approach to problem solving and finding solutions. Flexible and proactive/self-motivated working style with strong personal ownership of problem resolution. Skills: Strong knowledge of Android SDK, different versions of Android, and how to deal with different screen sizes Familiarity with RESTful APIs to connect Android applications to back-end services Strong knowledge of Android UI design principles, patterns, and best practice Understanding of Google’s Android design principles and interface guidelines Proficient understanding of code versioning tools, such as Git Familiarity with continuous integration Experience with offline storage, threading, and performance tuning Familiarity with the use of additional sensors Published apps in the market Knowledge of other web technologies and UI/UX standards Experience with performance and memory tuning with tools Experience with code refactoring, design patterns, design-driven development, continuous deployment, highly scalable applications, and application security','2023-09-01',0,0,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','RDI',NULL),('Senior iOS Developer (Native)','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','Development and delivery of i OS native apps. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features. Ensure all apps meet technical standards set by our industry. Unit-test code for robustness, usability, and general reliability. Work with outside data sources and API. Help in architecting and developing new features following our product roadmap. Other duties as assigned.','A Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or Engineering or equivalent work experience3+ years’ experience developing native mobile for i OSExcellent Native Mobile Development in i OS (Swift)Knowledge of UI/UX standards for mobile apps Excellent communication skills Experience in releasing apps on the App Store Understanding of Hybrid Apps & communication between webpages and native code Source Control Management Experience on 3rd Party SDKs integration','2023-09-01',0,0,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','RDI',NULL),('Senior Python / Django Developer -Part Time','Egypt','Giza','Dokki','RDI is looking for a design-minded Python / Django senior developer who must bring extensive, expert-level experience in Python / Django with the desire to deliver quality code. The developer will work on projects related to machine learning algorithms that will allow you to wear many hats and flex both technical development, collaborative and communication skills. Responsibilities: Participating in architectural, design and product discussions. Working closely with UX and Front-end Developers. Develop cloud-based Python Django software products. Designing and creating RESTful APIs for internal and partner consumption. Writing reusable, testable, and efficient code.','3+ years of on-the-job software engineering experience with a proven track record of delivering highly scalable solutions rapidly. Solid database skills in a relational database (i.e. Postgres SQL, My SQL, etc.)Knowledge of 