ing. Develop security protocols for restricted access systems','2023-10-01',10,0,1,5,5000,7000,0,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Shotmed',NULL),('Senior Analyst - Business Application - Oracle Fusion','Qatar','Doha','','Senior Analyst - Business Application - Oracle Fusion \'Job Details\' Job Description JOB SUMMARYThe Senior Analyst – Applications - Oracle Fusion is responsible for the leading and executing the Analysis, Design and Build related to the ERP. The Senior Analyst – Applications - Oracle Fusion will be responsible for the execution and schedule to meet the business needs of the organization. The Senior Analyst –Applications - Oracle Fusion has a solid background in ERP solutions. The incumbent analyses complex solutions, creates designs, develops and reviews build, executes and manages testing of the build and prepares build documentation and evidence to meet the business needs of the organization. S/he manages and maintains the schedule against the constantly changing priorities of the organization and ensures that the activities are completed on schedule. KEY ROLE ACCOUNTABILITIES Provides technical support and incident resolutions for ERP applications Raises tickets with vendors to provide fixes and patches to key incidents Leads the technical development of the ERP applications Designs, develops and quality tests for all ERP applications and interfaces Develops and supports Paa S solutions Customizes application software to support the business requirements as required Analyses and investigates business requirements related to ERP system Assists in ERP application implementations and assists in testing end user processes using defined guidelines Collects data and creates reports in response to business requests Supports in the analysis of business needs and documents technical requirements to support system enhancements Creates communication plans (correspondence, presentations, and other materials) for knowledge transfer to leadership. Performs other technical tasks related to ERP space Logs and tracks basic problems/work tickets with external product vendors or support organizations. Responds quickly and efficiently to any application related incident that is sent via help desk to the team Apply a basic understanding of the underlying principles of a professional discipline -typically obtained through formal study. Works with other Sidra IT teams around the integrated systems and business processes to enable fully integrated business flows. Analyzes user requirements and challenges to create technical solutions that add value to the business as a whole. Ability to relate actual day-to-day work to business priorities. QUALIFICATION & EXPERIENCEEducation Bachelor’s Degree in relevant field Experience5+ years of experience in Oracle ERP applications  3+ years of Oracle Fusion implementation experience in in organizations of similar size and function. Hands-on functional and technical experience supporting Oracle Fusion ERP in large, complex enterprise environments. * With extensive knowledge of business processes as relates to Oracle Fusion ERP. Strong understanding of Oracle Fusion ERP data structures, configurations, and processes.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Sidra Medicine',NULL),('Senior Engineer – Biomedical','Qatar','Doha','','Senior Engineer – Biomedical \'Job Details\' Job Description JOB SUMMARYThe Senior Engineer - Biomedical is responsible for the supervision of assigned BME Technicians and Technologists and functions in a senior technical capacity on a variety of assigned medical equipment (working supervisory position). Supervises, coordinates and influences all functions related to the daily safety testing, repair and maintenance of biomedical patient care equipment. Provides on-site leadership for all components of the medical equipment management plan, and participates in the development of departmental policies, programs and continuous quality improvement initiatives. Maximizes patient safety by supporting proper use, application and operational performance for patient care equipment. Acts as a technical resource to other BME staff for repair and maintenance activities on selected equipment and systems. KEY ROLE ACCOUNTABILITIES Contributes to the day-to-day management of the Biomedical Engineering operations according to departmental policies and processes. Provides critical problem solving and decision-making including work prioritization of equipment with higher clinical repair needs. Provides autonomous management of time in coordination with the BME Director and in consideration of departmental-wide strategies, policies and systems for workforce planning, occupational health and safety, education and training and performance management. Demonstrates an on-going commitment to service quality improvement and ensures a high-level commitment to professional job performance and customer service throughout Sidra. Promotes and maintains effective communication with all team members of the BME department towards achieving the departmental objectives. Participates in the use of a paperless, CAFM integrated, equipment maintenance program incorporating the transfer of test data from BME specific automated test equipment to generate accurate data and relevant histories in compliance with JCIA standards. Supports implementation and ongoing improvement of BME department service-related programs, including operational standards and relevant key performance indicators. Ensures the availability of relevant electronic data to the BME Director for analysis of maintenance operations and performance as required in support of selected KPI’s. Develops balanced work schedules within the CAFM program for self and subordinate staff, while considering flexible leave schedules. Evaluates assigned staff productivity, efficiency and other specific work quality performance indices. Participates in staff evaluations for assigned staff. Ensures subordinate staff has adequate resources to perform assigned repairs and maintenance. Coordinates with BME Trainer to ensure that all technical staff have been trained or demonstrated competence on assigned equipment. Monitors monthly expenses and works with management in recommendations for controlling operational costs. Coordinates test equipment repairs and scheduled testing for JCI compliance. Functions as a resource person for assigned equipment, which may include providing scheduled or on-the-spot instruction to clinical staff regarding the safe and proper use of medical equipment. Collaborates with other support departments (FM, or IT), to develop support plans for those devices requiring multi-disciplinary support. Adheres to Sidra’s standards as they appear in the Code of Conduct and Conflict of Interest policies. QUALIFICAITIONS & EXPERIENCEEducation Bachelor’s degree in electronic/ biomedical engineering Experience A minimum of 5+ years progressively more advanced technical experience in the Biomedical Engineering field ranging from hands-on to senior technical roles, followed by a minimum of 3+years supervisory level experience (i.e., a minimum 8+ years total BME experience). Demonstrated experience participating in JCAHO or JCIA accreditation surveys. Full understanding of the IEC 80001-1 standard Combinations of education and experience will be considered.* Multicultural workplace experience',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Sidra Medicine',NULL),('Technician - Respiratory','Qatar','Doha','','Technician - Respiratory \'Job Details\' Job Description The Respiratory Technician initiates the assembly, testing, and delivery of all Respiratory Care medical equipment, supplies, devices and consumables. S/he ensures that consumables are ordered and restocked in a timely manner, and along with medical equipment and are made available and placed for efficiency of access for staff and patients. S/he demonstrates professionalism in the services affecting planning and delivery of patient care at all times. The Respiratory Technician may possess novice knowledge of pediatric and/or neonatal cardiopulmonary anatomy and physiology. S/he may have novice knowledge and clinical acumen in the use of some medical devices and techniques used in respiratory therapy for the pediatric and/or neonatal population. S/he may demonstrate the knowledge and skills relevant for patient assessment and administration of low-acuity clinical therapeutic care. KEY ROLE ACCOUNTABILITIES: Collaborates with clinical Respiratory Therapy staff and Leadership, representatives of Supply Chain, Sterile Processing and Biomedical Engineering to ensure that all medical devices, stock and supplies are available for patient care. Under the direction of the Respiratory Therapy Services Leadership, prepares and assembles medical devices for safety check. Regularly updates the Respiratory Leadership team regarding any issues with equipment and consumables, or any delays in ordering or restocking equipment and consumables. Participates in the assembly, cataloging, mobilizing, and quality testing, of Respiratory Services medical devices. Maintains stock and delivers medical devices to clinical areas as required for patient use. Ensures the performance of routine departmental equipment and analyses the equipment to ensure quality and safety is maintained. Organizes and monitors supply areas in a safe and efficient manner. Participates in quality improvement planning in relation to equipment and stock management systems. Tracks normal and high priority Health Devices Alerts from ECRI and FDA and refers applicable medical device reports to Manager - Respiratory Services. Under the direction of the clinical Respiratory Therapy staff, provides clinical patient assessments including diagnostic and therapeutic interventions as needed. Responsible for maintaining up to date mandatory Life Support Training requirements as directed by Mo PH and 