ful?Bachelor Degree or equivalent (Professional or Legal degree is beneficial)3-4 years of experience working in compliance programme within a business Openness to travel within the market (Middle East & Africa)Strong analytical skills. Ability to detect risk areas and red flags. Solution-minded; desire to solve problems. Project management skills Effective stakeholder engagement, management and business partnering. You. Unlimited. We believe in creating the greatest good for society. Our strongest investments are in our people and the patients we serve.    Inclusion, Diversity and Equity: committed to welcoming, celebrating and thriving on diversity, learn more about our Employee Inclusion Groups on our website Your Future: annual bonus, company stock saving plan Work/Life Balance: paid volunteering hours, flexible approach Your Wellbeing: Employee Assistance Program Flexibility: possibility of working in hybrid model Training: Hands-On, Team-Customized Extra Perks: referral bonus, recognition program, mentoring program Stay connected and receive alerts for jobs like this by joining ourtalent community. We\'re more than just a company - we\'re a community! Follow us on Linked In to see how we support and empower our employees and patients every day. Check our Glassdoor page for a glimpse behind the scenes and a sneak peek into You. Unlimited., life, culture, and benefits at S+N. Explore our new website and learn more about our mission, our team, and the opportunities we offer.',NULL,'2023-10-21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Smith+Nephew',NULL),('Senior iOS and Flutter Developer','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','Develop and maintain mobile applications for i OS and Android devices using the Flutter framework. Develop and maintain native i OS applications. Architect, design, and implement business required functionalities. Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications. Collaborate with other developers, designers, and product managers to deliver high-quality products. Mentor and provide guidance to junior developers on the team. Conducts code reviews and provides mentorship, sharing knowledge with team members to maintain high code quality standards. Contribute to the continuous improvement of our mobile development processes. Implement best practices for software development, including unit testing, code review, and continuous integration.','At least 5 years of experience in developing i OS Native and Flutter applications. Excellent understanding of OOP concepts. Strong knowledge of the Swift, Objective C and Dart programming languages. Experience with i OS and Flutter SDKs and frameworks. Solid understanding of mobile application design patterns. Solid understanding of the full mobile development life-cycle. Solid understanding of mobile UI/UX principles and best practices. Experience with RESTful APIs and JSON, to connect applications to back-end services. Experience with offline storage, threading, and performance tuning. Proficient understanding of code versioning tools. Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills. Experience in the publishing process of applications on the App Store. Write clean and efficient code, conduct code reviews, and refactor existing code to improve reliability and scalability. Good communication skills, verbal and written.','2023-10-17',15,13,5,8,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Softec Technologies',NULL),('Senior Scrum Master','Egypt','Cairo','','We are looking for a senior scrum master to help lead the organization\'s agile transformation strategy. Scrum masters will be critical in ensuring that development teams and scrum masters follow  Agile framework principles and practices, mentoring and motivating teams to improve processes, facilitating agile ceremonies and decision-making processes, and removing team impediments. To be successful in this role as a senior scrum master, you should have past expertise with agile transformations, a strong understanding of agile methods, and the ability to effectively lead and mentor development teams. A great scrum master should have strong interpersonal, project management, and problem-solving abilities. Scrum Master Key Responsibilities: Scrum Master Leadership: Provide leadership to multiple scrum teams and support them in adopting and adhering to Agile principles, values, and practices. Foster a culture of continuous improvement and self-organization within the teams, helping them take ownership of their processes and outcomes. Act as a role model for Agile values and behaviors, setting a high standard for the organization. Agile Transformation and Framework Implementation: Support in the organisation agile transformation strategy Ensure the effective implementation of the agile framework principles and practices across the organization, including the coordination and alignment of Agile Release Trains (ARTs) with portfolio objectives. Collaborate with Portfolio Managers, Product Owners, and business team roles to ensure consistent and synchronized delivery. Facilitation: Facilitate various Scrum ceremonies, Daily stand-ups, Sprint planning, retrospective, and Quarterly Program Increment (PI) Planning, bringing cross-functional teams together to plan and prioritize work backlogs for the upcoming PI. Lead Inspect and Adapt (I&A) workshops at the end of each PI, focusing on the identification and resolution of systemic issues and continuous improvement. Team Coaching: Provide guidance and coaching to Agile teams and individuals, helping them understand and embrace Agile practices and principles. Support the development of high-performing, self-organizing teams by offering feedback and guidance on Agile roles and responsibilities. Performance Monitoring: Continuously monitor team velocity performance, progress, and the execution of their commitments. Identify impediments, bottlenecks, and roadblocks that hinder progress, and work with teams to resolve issues promptly. Conflict Resolution: Effectively manage team and priorities conflict and obstacles that may arise within scrum teams, ensuring teams remain focused on their goals and commitments. Encourage open communication, collaboration, and problem-solving among team members. Stakeholder Engagement: Actively engage with stakeholders, Program Managers Business Owners, and Product Owners to understand their needs and provide visibility into the progress and delivery of value. Ensure scrum teams alignment and customer satisfaction. Collaboration: Foster collaboration among scrum teams, Agile Release Trains (ARTs), and other parts of the organization to promote a culture of transparency and shared objectives. Encourage knowledge sharing and cross-team collaboration to leverage synergies and reduce duplication of effort. Training and Development: Support the professional development of Scrum Masters and scrum teams by providing training, guidance, and resources. Encourage continuous learning and skill development to help teams adapt to evolving Agile practices.','Scrum Master Requirements: Bachelor\'s degree in computer science, information technology, or a relevant field preferred. Certified scrum master, SAFe preferred.3+ years of experience as a scrum master or in a similar role. Working knowledge of agile methodology, techniques, and frameworks, such as Scrum or Kanban. Leadership and management experience. Excellent people and project management skills. Strong communication and presentation skills. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.','2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,5,7,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Softec Technologies',NULL),('Software Application Support Engineer','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','SLA Management and Technical Support: Take ownership of customer issues reported and see problems through to resolution according to agreed standard SLA’s. Research, diagnose, troubleshoot and identify solutions to resolve customer reported issues. To provi