urity policies and protocols.','Adequate bachelor degree (Information technology and computer science is preferred). Certified CCNS, CISSP & MCSE is an excellent advantage. Minimum 5 years of experience in networks administration, hardware and software maintenance and configuration. Engineering companies background is an advantage. Experience in cloud ERP maintenance is an advantage Active and multitasking personality. Strong diagnostic, analytical and problem solving skills Good verbal and written communication Good English language.','2023-09-01',0,7,5,7,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'TMA For Industrial Supplies','M'),('Oracle Developer','Egypt','Cairo','Heliopolis','Job Role: To develop, enhance, support and admin programs and systems to maximize support to TMGT application users Accountabilities: Receive the user documented requirements and specifications. Convert the business requirements into applications. Develop and maintain applications that meet the requirements and specifications set by the Business Analyst or received from users. Design forms and reports meeting the business requirements. Document all developed programs following the documentation standards. Test programs and ensure that they satisfy the specifications written by the Business Analyst. Participate in the User Acceptance Test with the Business Partners. Administrate and support running systems. Communicate with vendors (Foreigners/Locals) to be person in charge for first line support. Using Ticketing system to handle all users’ requirements. Manage meetings with vendors and business owners. Ensure continuous self-development to keep up to date with the latest technology in order to maintain up to date IT management at the company. Keep up to date with company\'s standards, policies and procedures that affect the implementation of IT responsibilities. Performing any other jobs assigned by direct manager. Make the analysis for the business requirement  Write the technical document to be used in design and implementation phase Support our customers on their offices inside Egypt Support on call during holidays and weekends if needed','Qualifications: The requirements listed below are the knowledge, skills and abilities required to hold and perform this position: University degree preferably Computer science.4-6 years of work experience in similar role. Strong Experience with Oracle Application Development Framework, forms and reports. Experience with Oracle SQL, PL-SQL. Excellent understanding of object oriented concept. Excellent communications skills with a high customer service orientation. Excellent interpersonal skills and team spirit. Highly motivated with an ability to handle work pressure and to meet tight deadlines. Strong problem solving skills. Good organizational skills. Keen on self-development. Very good written & spoken English and Arabic.','2023-10-09',26,5,4,6,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Tokio Marine Egypt General',NULL),('CRM Business Analyst','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','About the job CRM Business Analyst\nWe are ﻿seeking a \' CRM Analyst\' for a leading Electronic Trading & Contracting Company in Saudi Arabia. The position will be based in Riyadh and reporting to the Managing Director & ﻿CMO. Key Responsibilities﻿:﻿ Liaise with business group representatives and stakeholders across lines of business to help identify automation opportunitiesof existing processes leveraging technology tool sets supporting the end to end client lifecycle. Apply business acumen to help define and improve business process flow in the CRM and connecting platforms (throughdefinition of best practices, generate ideas for improvement and management of special projects). Provide front-line business process support across the entire Sales lifecycle leveraging best practices and facilitating enhancedbusiness metrics across multiple platforms.﻿Execute ongoing release management to ensure an informed, efficient and confident user base.﻿Own the release communication planning, execution, success definition, measurement and post implementation efforts. Apply critical thinking to troubleshoot issues quickly and effectively. Develop practices to maintain and improve data quality inside the CRM. Train on salesforce.com. Give / prepare Presentations regarding salesforce.com.﻿Qualifications:﻿Bachelor\'s degree in a related field, such as business administration, product management, or computer science. 3+ years of proven experience in Multiple Salesforce.com Products such as Salesforce Platform and CRM applications. Profound knowledge about Flows, Workflows and automation in general. A proactive attitude to Salesforce enhancements like automation and clean data-model. To cover: industrial products, manufacturing, Technology, and professional services. Skills﻿:﻿Maintain the customer relationship management tool Communication skills Strong technology skills Data Analysis and pattern recognition skills',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Top Notch Consultancy',NULL),('Pre-sales Solution Architect','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Pre-sales Solution Architect\nA leading company specializing in AI and data driven solutions is looking for a \'Presales Solution Architect\' to join their team in Doha, Qatar. The ideal candidate will be supporting the pre-sales team and technical activities in the Middle East Area. You are a great fit if﻿﻿:﻿﻿Are enthusiastic about Infrastructure as Code. Like to be involved in project qualification/validation process with our Sales teams.know what SRE is. Would like to work with A+ colleagues and the region\'s most experienced GCP developers. Find the quality of service most important, thus you fancy dealing with the whole lifecycle from the tiniest code fragments to virtual machines. Want to participate in spreading the cloud culture both in Hungary and internationally. Don\'t  just absorb knowledge, but also like to share it with others. You will be responsible for﻿:﻿﻿Collaborating with our Sales teams on the technical requirements of potential new projects. Implementing and managing cloud infrastructure based on GCP. Migrating our clients IT infrastructures to the Google Cloud. Automating deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. providing technical support in pre-sales Having a deep understanding of GCP solutions and keeping up-to-date with what\'s new in the cloud.﻿Skills and Requirements:﻿﻿Minimum of 5 years of Dev Ops experience, of which 2 years is in a cloud environment. Familiarity with containerization, Terraform, scripting languages, CI/CD, and microservice architectures. Familiarity with cloud services, Linux, security, networking, and Kubernetes. a comprehensive systems approach. A learning attitude. Good communication skills in English and Arabic. Would be preferable if﻿﻿:﻿﻿Real work experience with GCP. Some knowledge of AWS, Azure, or Open Stack.﻿',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Top Notch Consultancy',NULL),('Technical Consultant','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Technical Consultant\nA prominent real estate development company ﻿is looking for a \'Technical Consultant\' to join their team in ﻿Doha, Qatar﻿. The ideal candidate will be responsible for ﻿Creating Technical designs from functional specifications and implementing as working software applications through configuration, development, customization, or selection of third-party solutions in support of business processes.﻿You will be responsible for﻿: ﻿﻿Provide Support for implemented system solutions by assisting in deployments, addressing posts implementation technical issues. Develop dashboards, custom reports in Microsoft Dynamics 365. Develop custom triggers, procedures in SQL based on business requirements. Server Maintenance, server cloning, build test instances of existing on prim SQL applications. Learn required technologies, standards, and methodologies as needed to support new and existing business systems solutions as well as remain a breast of emerging technologies not yet explored. You should have experience in﻿: ﻿﻿Experience in data migration (using DIXF, third party tools, Atlas and custom development). Experience in integration development (web services, DIXF, .net custom client-server applications, knowledge of standard web services and integration protocols OData, SOAP, JSON, REST, SSIS, direct SQL, Azure logic apps). Experience in performance optimization (X++ application code, troubleshooting D365 components, AXPerf, LCS Environment monitoring, SQL performance optimization). Good in writing Business logic and customizing functionalities for D365 F&O. Technical design, develop and testing of core Dynamics 365 granules and add-on\'s. Work with internal stakeholders/teams to understand the technical requirements and scope out modifications and custom development. Convert functional requirements to technical specifications and design documents. Make technical recommendations for modification and latest upgrades recommended by Microsoft. Experience in release and environment management Application Lifecycle Management experience, TFS, build process. Experience in Integration projects (Power app, etc..) with OData, CDS (data integration), Rest API, AIF. Knowledge in Reporting, Integration, Data Migration and extensions, Data structures, custom data entities and data models. Experience on Upgrade of D365 F&O with MS latest version release and trouble shoot the issues. Minimum Requirements﻿: ﻿﻿A minimum experience of 5+ years in Microsoft Dynamics 365 technical design and development (X++, C#, SSRS and BI development). Experience with Visual Studio and in . NET development Must have experience in MS SQL Database knowledge along with server Management skills including IIS (Internet Information services), ADFS (Active Directory Federation Services) & IFD (Internet Facing Deployment) configuration. Candidates should have participated in a minimum of 2-3 MS full life cycle Dynamics 365 F&O implementations projects in a role of a Developer, Technical consultants, or Technical Architect.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Top Notch Consultancy',NULL),('UI UX','Saudi Arabia','Jeddah','','About the job UI UX\nOur client in Jeddah is seeking a talented and experienced UI/UX Designer to join a startup company. As a UI/UX Designer, you will play a crucial role in creating intuitive, visually appealing, and user-centered digital experiences for our products/services. Responsibilities: Conduct user research to understand user behaviors, needs, and motivations. Create user personas, user flows, wireframes, and interactive prototypes to visualize and communicate design concepts. Design intuitive and visually appealing user interfaces that align with branding guidelines and enhance the overall user experience. Collaborate with developers to ensure the feasibility and implementation of UI/UX designs. Conduct usability testing and gather feedback to iterate and improve the user experience. Stay up to date with industry trends, best practices, and emerging technologies in UI/UX design. Advocate for user-centered design principles and contribute to a culture of design thinking and innovation within the organization. Collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams, including product managers, developers, and stakeholders, to ensure successful project delivery. Present and communicate design concepts and ideas to internal teams and stakeholders. Requirements: Bachelor\'s degree or equivalent in UI/UX design, human-computer interaction, graphic design, or a related field.5 years proven experience in UI/UX design, either through internships, freelance work, or professional positions. Proficiency in UI design tools such as Sketch, Adobe XD, Figma, or similar software. Strong understanding of design principles, typography, color theory, and layout composition. Familiarity with user research techniques and usability testing. Knowledge of HTML, CSS, and Java Script to effectively collaborate with developers. Excellent communication and presentation skills to articulate design decisions and receive feedback. Strong problem-solving skills and ability to think creatively to overcome design challenges. Experience working in an Agile development environment and ability to adapt to iterative design processes.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Top Notch Consultancy',NULL),('IT Technical Support Specialist - Tanta','Egypt','Gharbia','Tanta','Installing and configuring computer hardware, software, networks, printers and scanners. Monitoring and maintaining computer systems and networks and its confidentiality. Tracking and following-up the IT hardware stock. Setting up new users\' accounts and profiles and dealing with password issues. Troubleshooting system and network problems and diagnosing and solving hardware or software faults. Providing support, including procedural documentation and relevant reports. Undertaking scheduled maintenance upgrades. Communicate with employees to determine the nature of problems. Responding to breakdowns. Investigating, diagnosing and solving computer software and hardware faults. Repairing equipment and replacing parts if needed. Notify IT Senior Technical Support Specialist about hardware`s pieces if it needed. Obtaining replacement or specialist components, fixtures or fittings. Checking computer equipment for electrical safety. Managing stocks of equipment, consumables and other supplies as scheduled.','Bachelor Degree in computer science and MIS.2-5 Years of experience. Hands-on computer network administration, hardware and installation. CCNA and MCSA certificates is preferred.','2023-10-01',31,14,2,5,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Town Team',NULL),('IT Administrator','Egypt','Giza','Abu Rawash','Book meetings and schedule events Order office stationery and supplies Maintain internal databases Submit expense reports Keep employee records (physical and digital)Maintain a filing system for data on customers and external partners Distribute incoming and outgoing mail Prepare regular reports and presentations Organize, store and print company documents as needed Answer and redirect phone calls Make travel arrangements Handle queries from managers and employees Update office policies and ensure compliance with them',NULL,'2023-10-25',1,0,2,3,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Trans World Trading',NULL),('Account Manager-Facilities Management Soft Services','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Transguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees!\nWe are currently recruiting for an Account Manager to join our Facilities Management Soft Services team at Transguard Group.\nScope \nManage allocated customer accounts in line with the commercial agreement, ensuring we maintain 100% of clients, grow the accounts as well as manage the relationship in line with the commercial agreement. \nResponsibilities\nCommercial Management\nResponsible for developing the business growth of the account\nImplicitly understand the commercial aspects of the contract and manage the service delivery within the boundaries of the contract\nPrepare a quarterly report with monthly operational data to support the review of the financial performance of the contracts in question\nInvestigate with the Divisional Manager the reason why any expected gross profit on the contract is not met. Explore %u201Cmanagement solutions%u201D to address the issue.\nEnsure invoices are prepared, delivered and paid\nMonitor billable vs non billable staff \nReport any variations to the contract to the Divisional Manager and ensure that these are reviewed and agreed with the client\nClient Management\nDevelop a good working relationship with the client and hold regular client meetings to ensure the smooth running of the contract \nUndertake site visits to view staff performance and discuss and resolve any issues raised by the client regarding the quality of the service \nMonitor that the service delivered is within the contract terms. If not discuss variations with the client and Business Unit Head \nExplore further business opportunities with the client \nPlan ahead and agree with the client for any new staff requirements to meet any future peaks and troughs \nEnsure the work schedules developed for the staff match the client requirements \nStaff Management\nManage the team structure and develop it as required to ensure the operations run smoothly and within budget\nManage operational Team Members \nHold staff meetings, monthly or as required\nConduct site visits to view staff performance and help to motivate staff\nPlan mobilization of staff according to agreed timescales with the client \nArrange site specific induction and training of new staff\nCheck and sign off the monthly payroll\nResolve staff issues together with relevant departments, including salary discrepancies, emergency leave, reallocation of staff to other contracts, accidents, etc.\nMonitor absence and accident rates and undertake any correction actions required\nApprove staff leave\nMonitor staff performance and nominate staff for the Employee of the Month award\nMonitor that work schedules are being followed by the operations team\n',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('PCS7 Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','','Transguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees! We are currently recruiting for a Process Control  Engineer PCS7  for our trusted client to be based out of their office in Dubai.\nPurpose:\nProcess control engineers are responsible for developing and maintaining systems for monitoring, controlling, and regulating operations.\nResponsibilities:\nResponsible for control system hardware and software documentation preparation. ( Material submittal, FDS, DCSD, O&M etc..)\nEngineer will be mobilized on panel builder place and site for testing and commissioning.\nS7 400H, ET200SP HA, CP443, S7 communications, PROFIBUS, MPI, IE communications hands on experience.\nDomain server knowledge\nBackup and restoring\nInformation Server\nReporting\nModbus TCP / IP\n ',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('Project Administrator','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Transguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic, and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees! We are currently recruiting for Project Administrator to be based out of their office in Dubai.\nJob Purpose:\nTo support a key organizational goal of developing an integrated hub of company-wide processes, policies, SLAs and related supporting content.\nDevelop Process Maps, Policy and SLA documents in accordance with company standards mapped with internal organization roles.\nWork with the Organizational Effectiveness Team members for all the requirements related to the integrated hub development and launch.\nBe accountable for creating content on the integrated hub platform as per given guidelines.\nSupport the Organizational Effectiveness Team in other related projects from time to time as per business need.\nJob Description:\nTo create content like Process maps, SLAs, Policies that are required on an integrated and digital platform. \nTo manage all activities related to content development on a digital platform requiring technical proficiency.\nDevelop Process Maps and flow charts with additional linked content across Roles, Teams and other Processes.\n\nDevelop ‘How To’ guides and training documents for future reference.\n\n\nConstantly manage progress visibility for senior management with a Project Plan approach.\n\n\nLiaise with multiple teams within Organizational Effectiveness team and other teams to ensure scope clarity and content approvals.\n\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('Senior Analyst - Forecasting and Research','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Transguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees! We are currently recruiting for a Senior Analyst - Forecasting and Research for our trusted client to be based out of their office in Dubai.\nJob Purpose:\nThe job purpose is to offer analytical support for aviation market research and development initiatives aimed at enhancing traffic growth and gaining Customer Insights for Dubai International and Dubai World Central airports. This role involves analyzing traffic performance, on-time performance, market opportunities, and risks, as well as assessing customer sentiments. Additionally, it entails the responsibility of producing routine traffic analysis reports and maintaining data repositories vital for diverse market development and customer experience (CX) activities, encompassing tasks like traffic analysis and forecasting, evaluating airline performance, schedule development, and customer sentiment analysis, among others.\nResponsibilities:\nMarket Research & Analysis • Conduct in-depth market research to assess specific airlines\' network and market sizes in their catchment areas to Dubai.• Collaborate with the manager and senior analyst to analyze and devise effective marketing strategies for Dubai Airports in these markets.• Prepare and deliver presentations that communicate the findings and analysis effectively.\nPerformance Reporting and Trend Analysis • Generate routine reports, including monthly management information reports that track airport performance metrics such as passenger numbers, cargo volumes, aero-revenue, and flight schedules.• Provide comprehensive written commentary on observed trends, backed by thorough analysis that identifies opportunities and risks related to airport performance.\n \n ',NULL,'2023-10-20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('Senior Manager - Assessment Design & Delivery','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Transguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic, and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees! We are currently recruiting for Senior Manager - Assessment Design & Delivery to be based out of their office in Dubai.\nJob Purpose:\nThe purpose of this role is to be responsible for the design and implementation of robust, valid and reliable assessment and selection criteria and tools across the business, to select and support the development and growth of talent.\nThe role holder governs DA’s approach to assessment to identify and develop talent and is primarily responsible for collaborating with business stakeholders, Talent Partners, Talent Acquisition, the Development function and leadership teams to identify and develop appropriate assessment tools in line with talent requirements. The role holder is also expected to project manage assessment activities and provide subject matter expertise to support the business with appropriate assessment techniques, scoring and selecting talent.\nJob Responsibilities:\nWork closely with colleagues across the Talent Management function and the wider HRD team (such as Talent Acquisition and Talent Partners) to manage assessment related activities across all levels of the organisation to meet business and project requirements.\n Project manage all assessment related activities on a day to day basis and line manage activities of assessors and coordinators delivering assessments.\nImplement the Talent assessment/development process organisation wide, training and supporting 20 Talent Partners and Line Managers in the execution stage on elements such as assessment practices, ethical considerations, best practice, use of data and confidentiality, etc.\nProvide support in a variety of formats such as workshops (e.g. assessor briefing sessions) and/or written guidance so that DA’s approach to assessments is well understood.\nHelp implement and manage new innovative processes, leading edge concepts, approaches and 10 technology as led by the Head of Assessment to support the delivery of high quality, robust, effective and efficient assessment and development practices, and drive continuous improvement.\nEvaluate the reliability and validity of assessment tools and practices being implemented, and quality assure assessment processes across key activities to ensure that the Assessment function is delivering outcomes that are beneficial to employees and the wider business, and support the delivery of DA’s strategic objectives.\nReview data analysis conducted to help evaluate the reliability and validity of assessment tools and practices.\n Work closely with relevant business departments, Talent Management and wider HRD teams to 15 inform appropriate solutions for assessment and development requirements, providing a seamless service to identify and support the growth and development of talent, and meet DA’s business requirements.\n',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('System Administrator - ICT Infrastructure','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','',' \nTransguard Group was established in 2001 and has diversified significantly, we lead in the fields of Cash Services, Security Services, Manpower Services, Facilities Management & Aviation. Transguard Group is the UAE’s most trusted business support and outsourcing provider and has a large, dynamic and culturally diverse workforce with 50,000 employees!\nWe are currently recruiting for a Senior System Administrator – ICT Infrastructure to join our ICT team at Transguard Group.\nScope \nThe Senior System Administrator role requires the holder to analyze, design, troubleshoot and maintain the corporate ICT Server Infrastructure. This includes cloud-based computing platforms and on-premises. The individual must participate in high large complexity project, execution of the end-to-end technology architecture and technical operations methods to enable continuity innovation within the infrastructure. The Senior System Administrator will be accountable for the following domains: physical and virtual servers, storage, backup, and emails.\nResponsibilities\nGeneral\nAdministration of all Server infrastructure\nReview L1 and L2 network reports and send summary to ICT Operation manager\nL3 Administration of all Server infrastructure\nMaintain change documentation related to system changes\nProvide all necessary information to Level 1 and Level 2 support\nProvide weekly project status report to ICT operation Manager\nProvide Level 3 support via phone calls, emails, or in person\nResolve complex system-related issues to the end user’s satisfaction\nProvide advanced end user training and information when required\nUnderstand and follow all ICT SOP and Policies\nCreate and maintain detailed advanced system documentation\nAbility to read, analyze and interpret technical instructions and manuals\nAdvanced understanding of ITIL framework\nHands-on experience on the following hardware: HP Blade infrastructure and storage, VMware and Hyper-V virtualization, and backup solution\nHands-on experience on the following solutions: Office365, Email security gateway, Microsoft Azure, and Microsoft System Center Suite\nBasic understanding of PMP framework\nAssist with technology planning through ongoing research\nAbility to manage multiple activities and tasks simultaneously\nTake ownership for resolving L3 system-related issues\nInformation Security\nFamiliarize with and adhere to the information security policies and procedures along with the policies and procedures applicable to their area of responsibility\nProtection of the issued equipment (e.g. laptops, mobile devices, etc.) against unauthorized access and damage\nResponsible for clearing the desk from all the sensitive material and logging off or locking workstations at the end of the day and when leaving their desk\nShall report security incidents, suspected weaknesses in the security system, software malfunctions and/or failures to the information security team as soon as possible\n',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Transguard group',NULL),('BI Developer','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','• Translate business needs to technical specifications • Maintain and support data analytics platforms • Conduct unit testing and troubleshooting • Evaluate and improve existing BI systems • Collaborate with teams to integrate systems • Develop and execute database queries and conduct analysis • Create visualizations and reports for requested projects • Develop visual reports, KPI scorecards, and dashboards using Power BI desktop. • Connect data sources, importing data, and transforming data for Business intelligence. • Think analytically for translating data into informative reports and visuals. • Capable of implementing row-level security on data along with an understanding of application security layer models in Power BI. • Should have an edge over making DAX queries in Power BI desktop. • Expert in using advanced-level calculations on the data set. • Responsible for design methodology and project documentaries.','• 4-6 years of experience in developing reports • Bachelor’s degree in engineering, Computer Science, etc. • Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate is a plus • MS SQL knowledge is a must • MS Power BI is a must  • Knowledge of MS Office, with a particular focus on MS Excel • Windows Servers 2008 or later versions Familiar with all databases • Familiar with Microsoft Azure • Experienced in virtualization • Excellent command of written and spoken English','2023-10-01',0,0,5,7,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Transmar International',NULL),('Senior Field Support Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Job Summary: The Senior Field Support Engineer Role is part of Customer Support Team to provide technical support for a Transportation Software Product that is in use by Large Government Organization at UAE. To provide day-to-day Technical Support to customers by maintaining their systems, investigating, and tracking all issues, along with testing and deployment of software changes and new releases. Job Description: Key Duties and Responsibilities This role reports to the Customer Support Manager – Trapeze Group Middle East for providing technical support for Transportation Application and Hardware Products. The role is also responsible to provide extendable support for implementing Projects driven by Professional Services Manager. An ongoing commitment to customer satisfaction by meeting their requirements proactively and ensuring all SLA and Project Timelines. Provide Technical Support to Trapeze Group Middle East customers by maintaining their systems; investigating and tracking reported issues; testing and deploying new software releases. Installation of Electronic and Telecom devices and demonstration functionality to the customer on-site whenever required. Lead Hardware support team and ensure Customer deliverables are met. Diagnose and repair problems with malfunctioning Electronics devices, ineffective electronic pieces, and inoperative parts. Support on managed large scale Transportation Systems applications software and Hardware. Ensuring calibration or proper functioning of equipment and scheduling replacement when needed. Provide onsite support for all requirements and issues at customer sites including installation of In-Vehicle (Mobile Data Terminals) devices and Transportation services. Lead all Trapeze activities with defined process are followed and documentation of all activities or tasks. Proactively support the management team to achieve Trapeze ME goals and identify opportunities for improvements. Communicate to both customers and colleagues in a professional, clear, and respectful manner. Education and Experience Three-year Diploma or Bachelor of Science Degree in Electronics and communication Engineering, or a similar technical field will be highly regarded. Minimum of 2 to 3 Years experience in In-Vehicle Devices or ITS devices installation, IT Systems installation, trouble shooting and technical demonstration. Strong knowledge of Electronics circuitry and Functional skills. Knowledge of Electronics Repair workshop management tools. Personal Attributes Effective communication and interpersonal skills in dealings with team members, customers, and other stakeholders. Possess the ability to adapt to the various internal procedures of a client while still adhering to company procedures and policies. Ability to develop and comprehend concepts and learn new skills quickly and thoroughly. Ability to build strong relationships quickly, both internally and with customers. Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills within a multi-facetted environment. A passionate ‘can-do’ mindset focused on understanding and addressing customer needs.positively in a team environment, appreciate each team member\'s contributions and effectively utilize each team member to his/her fullest potential. Worker Type: Regular Number of Openings Available:1',NULL,'2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Trapeze',NULL),('Flutter developer','Egypt','Dakahlia','Mansoura','Job Title: Flutter Developer Company: Trauxit Location: Mansoura City, Egypt Job Description: Trauxit is a dynamic and innovative company in the transportation and logistics industry, and we are looking for a talented Flutter Developer to join our team in Mansoura City. As a Flutter Developer at Trauxit, you will play a key role in developing and maintaining our mobile applications, ensuring they are user-friendly, efficient, and visually appealing. You\'ll work in a collaborative environment alongside other developers, designers, and product managers to deliver cutting-edge mobile solutions. Key Responsibilities: Mobile App Development: Design, develop, and maintain mobile applications using Flutter to ensure high-quality user experiences on both i OS and Android platforms. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and refine project requirements and translate them into technical specifications. UI/UX Design: Implement visually appealing and responsive user interfaces that align with Trauxit\'s design guidelines and user experience standards. Continuously improve the app\'s UI/UX based on user feedback and industry best practices. Integration and Connectivity: Integrate RESTful APIs, third-party libraries, and services to enhance app functionality. Implement real-time features, push notifications, and location-based services to improve user engagement. Testing and Debugging: Conduct thorough testing, including unit testing and UI testing, to identify and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks. Ensure the application runs smoothly across various devices and screen sizes. Optimization and Performance: Optimize app performance for speed, responsiveness, and efficient resource utilization. Stay up-to-date with Flutter updates and industry trends to incorporate best practices. Code Documentation: Maintain clear and concise code documentation for future reference and team collaboration. Continuous Learning: Stay informed about the latest mobile app development trends and emerging technologies to suggest improvements and innovations. Qualifications: Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience). Proven experience in mobile app development using Flutter and Dart. Strong understanding of software development principles, design patterns, and best practices. Proficiency with version control systems (e.g., Git). Familiarity with RESTful APIs and third-party integrations. Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail. Strong communication and collaboration skills. Ability to work in an agile development environment. Knowledge of app deployment processes for i OS and Android platforms. Experience with other mobile development technologies (e.g., native Android or i OS development) is a plus. Joining Trauxit in Mansoura City means becoming part of a dynamic team that is committed to transforming the transportation and logistics industry. If you are passionate about mobile app development, excited about Flutter, and eager to contribute to innovative solutions, we encourage you to apply. Feel free to modify this job description further to align it with your specific needs and company culture.','BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related subject Proven software development experience and Android skills development Proven working experience in Android app development and Have published at least one original Android app Experience with Android SDKExperience working with remote data via REST and JSONExperience with third-party libraries and APIs Working knowledge of the general mobile landscape, architectures, trends, and emerging technologies Solid understanding of the full mobile development life cycle.','2023-10-01',6,0,1,2,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)',NULL,'TRAUXIT',NULL),('Front End Developer - React & Next.js','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Travolic is the first free flight search website in the Middle East and Africa that brings you flights prices from various airlines and online travel agencies all in one trusted place. We help you search, find and compare cheap flights. Once you choose your best travel deal, with one click, we connect you to the airline or travel agency you have chosen for instant booking. We are in search of a dedicated Front End Developer proficient in Java Script, React.js, and Next.js. The candidate should ideally possess knowledge of React Native as a valuable addition. This role will involve creating and enhancing web user interfaces, with potential involvement in mobile application development. Responsibilities Collaborate with the product and design teams to develop innovative solutions for product visuals and user experience. Design, develop, and maintain responsive web applications primarily using React.js and Next.js. Transform UI/UX design wireframes into high-quality code. Implement and optimize components for maximum performance and scalability. Ensure seamless integration of front-end applications with backend services through APIs. Stay updated with the latest in front-end technologies and best practices to keep our platforms modern and competitive. Optionally, assist in developing and enhancing mobile applications using React Native.','Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field. Minimum [1 years] of hands-on