UPA Change Manager','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Role: COUPA\nChange Manager Job Type: Full-time, On-site, Dubai, UAEContract Duration: Initial 3 months contract\nwith option to extend As the Change Manager, you will be responsible for delivering the full change\nmanagement scope within the Group’s Companies. You will always strive to\nimprove the rollout and change approach to make the Group efficient in\nachieving the Coupa implementation targeted effects in close collaboration with\nPMOs, PMs, and other key stakeholders. The Change Manager will be\nresponsible for the quality and efficiency of the change effort and must make\nsure the group reaches the targeted future state in accordance with the change\nplan. Requirements Role: COUPA\nChange Manager Job Type: Full-time, On-site, Dubai, UAEContract Duration: Initial 3 months contract\nwith option to extend As the Change Manager, you will be responsible for delivering the full change\nmanagement scope within the Group’s Companies. You will always strive to\nimprove the rollout and change approach to make the Group efficient in\nachieving the Coupa implementation targeted effects in close collaboration with\nPMOs, PMs, and other key stakeholders. The Change Manager will be\nresponsible for the quality and efficiency of the change effort and must make\nsure the group reaches the targeted future state in accordance with the change\nplan. Benefits UAE Work Visa and Medical Insurance (both, only if required) for the duration of the contract only.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UHRS',NULL),('Power Apps and Power Automate Developer','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','','Position Overview: We are seeking an experienced Power Apps and Power Automate Developer to join our dynamic team. This role will focus on creating, implementing, and optimizing applications built with Microsoft Power Platform tools, primarily Power Apps and Power Automate. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of business processes and the capability to translate these processes into automated workflows and applications. Key Responsibilities: 1. Design, develop, and implement business solutions using Microsoft Power Apps.2. Create automated workflows using Power Automate to streamline business operations.3. Collaborate with business stakeholders to gather requirements and ensure that the Power Platform solutions meet their needs.4. Troubleshoot, debug, and optimize Power Apps applications and Power Automate flows to enhance performance.5. Integrate Power Apps and Power Automate with other Microsoft 365 tools and external systems.6. Ensure data integrity and security by implementing appropriate data protection measures.7. Continuously monitor and maintain the applications, ensuring they are up-to-date and functional.8. Provide training and support to end-users to ensure seamless adoption of new applications.9. Stay updated with the latest features and best practices in the Power Platform ecosystem.10. Document design decisions, workflows, and user guides for future reference. Requirements1. Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field. 2. Proven experience in developing applications using Microsoft Power Apps and creating workflows with Power Automate.3. Experience building and using custom connectors, integrating with both standard and custom APIs.4. Familiarity with Microsoft Dataverse (formerly Common Data Service) and its integration with Power Platform.5. Strong understanding of relational databases and data modeling.6. Experience integrating Power Platform tools with other Microsoft 365 services like Share Point, Teams, and Dynamics 365.7. Knowledge of Power BI is a plus.8. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.9. Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.10. Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment as well as independently. Benefits NA',NULL,'2023-10-21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UHRS',NULL),('Programme Associate-2 Months Contract','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Opportunity Responsibilities: As the Associate, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the seamless\ncoordination and support of content and programming development. Your primary focus will be on supporting the Programme\nteam on facilitating content production, speaker outreach and close\ncoordination with speaker managers, documentation and contributing to the\nsuccess of our events. You will be an essential part of the Programmes and\nEvents Advisory pillar. Key Responsibilities: Speaker\nOutreach: Support the speaker invitation process through invitation\nletter production (on a rolling basis), RSVP follow-up and updating speaker\ntrackers/databases. Coordination\nwith Speaker Managers: Collaborate with the speaker\nmanager to loop them in as soon as speakers are confirmed. Content\nCoordination: Collaborate with the speaker manager and other\nstakeholders to ensure all event content is produced (ex: marketing material) and\nconsolidated for each event. Content\nProduction: lead producing some material needed for events that require\nin-house production (such as PPT holding slides) when the need arises. Speaker\nMaterial: support the production of speaker briefs and other prep\nmaterial required for events. This will require close coordination with speaker\nmanagers to set up regular briefing calls ahead of events. Documentation: Maintain organized records of all event content-related material. This will\ninclude updating agenda details, post event summary/reports, and other forms of\ndata capture needed. Calendar\nManagement: Serve as the main point of contact for enquiries and requests\nfor calendar bookings and requests, working closely with the programming\nmanager on maintaining version control and accurate dissemination of\ninformation to relevant teams. Event\nSupport: Provide dedicated support leading up to and during the event,\nassisting with any last-minute needs, speaker management support and set-up. Guest\nlist:\nsupport guest outreach and management of RSVPs for special invite only events. Stakeholder\nCollaboration: Lead coordination with\ninternal teams and partners to ensure the successful execution of content deliverables\nfor the event. Continuous Improvement: Stay updated on emerging trends within the conference/events space and suggest\ninnovative approaches to enhance programming formats and ideas. Requirements Skills: The ideal candidate for the Associate role should possess the following skills\nand qualifications: Undergraduate\ndegree and a minimum of 2 years in an office administrative/supporting role;\nexperience working with events preferable Strong\nworking knowledge of project management tools and software (preferably\nproficient in event management software)Flexibility\nand adaptability, able to work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment Exceptional\norganizational and communication skills. Strong\nattention to detail and the ability to multitask effectively. Problem-solving\nabilities to address challenges. Detail-oriented\nmindset with a focus on accurate documentation and foresight to management\nneeds. Collaborative\nteam player with the ability to work cross-functionally. Previous\nexperience in event development and coordination is a plus. Benefits Visa and Medical Insurance (if required) for the duration of contract only',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UHRS',NULL),('Speaker Manager-2 Months Contract','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Job Title: Speaker Manager Opportunity Responsibilities: As the Speaker Manager, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the seamless\ncoordination and support of speakers who have been confirmed for events. Your\nprimary focus will be on enhancing the speaker experience, facilitating their\nengagement with our programs, and contributing to the success of our events.\nYou will be an essential part of the Programmes and Events Advisory pillar. Key Responsibilities: Speaker\nLiaison: Serve as the main point of contact for confirmed speakers,\nbuilding and maintaining strong relationships to ensure their needs and\nexpectations are met throughout the speaker journey. Travel\nCoordination: Collaborate with the travel agency to coordinate all\ntravel arrangements for speakers, including flights, accommodations, and\ntransportation, ensuring a hassle-free travel experience. Information\nGathering: Gather comprehensive details from speakers for marketing and\ncommunication purposes, including bios, headshots, presentation materials, and\nany specific requirements they may have. Communication\nHub: Establish and maintain open and clear lines of communication with speakers,\naddressing their queries, providing event details, and ensuring they are\nwell-informed about the event logistics. Event\nSupport: Provide dedicated support to speakers leading up to and during\nthe event, assisting with any last-minute needs, technical setups, and ensuring\ntheir comfort and preparedness. Speaker\nEngagement: Develop strategies to enhance speaker engagement and\nparticipation in programs, fostering a sense of belonging and enthusiasm among\nspeakers. Logistical\nManagement: Manage the logistical aspects of speaker\nparticipation, such as scheduling, session assignments, and ensuring speakers\nare well-prepared and confident in their roles. Feedback\nCollection: Gather feedback from speakers post-event to assess\ntheir experience, identify areas for improvement, and implement enhancements to\nthe speaker program. Content\nCoordination: Collaborate with content teams to ensure that speaker\nmaterials are integrated seamlessly into the event program, including\npresentations, panel discussions, and workshops. Emergencies\nand Contingencies: Develop contingency plans and protocols to address\nany unforeseen challenges that may arise during a speaker\'s participation in an\nevent. Budget\nMonitoring: Assist in monitoring and tracking the budget related\nto speaker logistics, travel, and accommodation, ensuring cost-effectiveness. Stakeholder\nCollaboration: Collaborate with internal teams, partners, and\nvendors to ensure the successful execution of speaker-related activities and\ndeliverables. Documentation: Maintain organized records of all speaker-related communications, agreements,\nand documentation for future reference and reporting. Continuous\nImprovement: Stay updated on industry best practices in speaker\nmanagement and suggest innovative approaches to enhance the speaker experience. Requirements Skills: The ideal candidate for the\nSpeaker Manager role should possess the following skills and qualifications: Exceptional\norganizational and communication skills. Strong\nattention to detail and the ability to multitask effectively. Problem-solving\nabilities to address speaker-related challenges. Customer\nservice-oriented mindset with a focus on speaker satisfaction. Proficiency\nin event management software and tools. Adaptability\nto work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment. Collaborative\nteam player with the ability to work cross-functionally. Previous\nexperience in speaker management or event coordination is a plus. Benefits Visa and Medical Insurance (if required) for the duration of this contract only',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UHRS',NULL),('Technical Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','1. Attends Project and technical meetings with clients/consultants to Coordinate and plan the installation to be in line with the project schedule. 2. Programming, Testing and commissioning of the Systems, conducting tests & inspections as per the cause and effects to ensure operational effectiveness and documents it properly. 3. Day-to-day management of the multiple site, including supervising and monitoring the site labour force and the work of any subcontractors. 4. To be able to attend coordination meetings with client/consultant/contractor etc… 5. To have technical knowledge about ELV, IT and security systems which are mandatory during coordination and meeting with all stakeholders. 6. Coordinating with internal team for installation, testing and commissioning of all systems in the project. 7. Handing over the projects in proper way and completing all close out documents and get it signed by concern team. 8. Managing a proficient team in ELV systems and on-site building practices. Responsible for the IT, Telecom, ELV, Electronic and Security systems design contents as assigned together with its follow-up for Authorities and Client\'s approval. 9. Responsible for chairing coordination meetings with the contractors to ensure that the intended design is implemented Responsible for regular site visits to ensure installation standard is satisfactory. 10. Liaison and coordination with all applicable Local Authority Departments to obtain approval at all stages of the project. 11. Design & Implementation of Extra Low Voltage (ELV) systems: Telecommunications, PAVA, AV Systems, CCTV, Access Control, Biometrics, Structured Cabling System Passive and Active components: design phase to construction phase. 12. Produce necessary ELV calculations including CCTV Field of View, lens Calculation, Recording Time and Capacity Calculation, Wi-Fi Heat maps, Design drawings, single line diagrams, technical design report, schedules and specifications etc. 13. Coordinating with internal team for installation, testing and commissioning of all systems in the project. 14. Handing over the projects in proper way and completing all close out documents and get it signed by concern team. Requirements1. Highly Professional in dealing with clients. 2. working under pressure and negotiating delegating abilities. 3. Self-motivated and ability to learning new technologies4. B. tech In Electronics and communication Engineering',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UHRS',NULL),('Tech