tc. Full awareness of all safety policies and procedures. Have control of recognized hazards to achieve an acceptable level of risk. Self-Perform Works. Additional Responsibilities 3 Job Knowledge & Skills • Excellent knowledge of material engineering properties and local/global availability of materials. Excellent technical skills and ability to organize and oversee preparation of technical drawings. Excellent communicator: verbal, written and presentation skills. Proficient in computer applications and Systems. Professional Client Management Skills. Effective Time Management Skills. Logical decision-making ability.• ERP knowledge preferably SAP functional skills are a requirement to be successful in this role. Job Experience 7 years Total2 years GCC Competencies Collaboration Accountability Resilience Quality Leadership Creates Strategy - Developing Drives Performance - Developing Develops Future Leaders - Developing Contingency Workforce Management L3Commercial & Residential Construction L3Project Planning L3Construction Budgeting L3Project Management L3Education Profesional degree in MMUP Engineer Registration (UPDA)Bachelor\'s Degree in Civil Engineering or any related field',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UrbaCon Contracting & Trading Company',NULL),('Senior Project Engineer - Electrical','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Summary To Lead, manage, supervise, follow up on all construction Mechanical/Electrical systems Installation, Inspections, Testing & Commissioning Job Responsibilities 1 To manage self, to manage others and to liaise with the CM, MEP coordinators, Site engineers and foremen.\nTo ensure the project discipline works are executed in accordance with the relevant discipline drawings, specifications, method statement, execution program in coordination with all other disciplines.\nTo ensure that the Mechinacal/Electrical works are executed efficiently within the target schedule in the best quality without materials wastage.\nTo ensure the Mechanical/Electrical works are executed in compliance with local authorities that has jurisdiction over the discipline scope of work i.e. KM, QCDD, Ooredoo, Health and Safety and all standards applicable to the project such as QCS2014 and the project specifications.\nTo ensure adherence to the relevant company\'s policies and procedures.\nTo ensure the satisfaction of the client, consultant and main contractor and MEP project manager/CM always.\nJob Responsibilities 2 To guide the site engineers through the work activities management process throughout the duration of the project.  Assign specific targets to the various work activities.\nTo plan and allocate responsibilities to team members.\nTo review and approve Mechnical/Electrical shop drawings.\nTo review and approve Mechnical/Electrical design calculations.\nTo review and sign-off Mechanical/Electrical material technical submittal before issuance to consultant.\nTo review and sign-off material requisitions.\nTo prepare schedule of method statements.\nTo review and approve method statements in compliance with project specifications and budget.\nTo liaise with technical department for the relevant authority approvals.\nAdditional Responsibilities 3 Job Knowledge & Skills • Strong Knowledge of the Construction Field • Mechnical/Electrical codes and Standards • NFPA• Local Regulations • UPDA Certified Engineer or Certification with attestation• ERP knowledge preferably SAP functional skills are a requirement to be successful in this role. Job Experience Total   9 year(s)On Job     7 year(s)GCC    4 year(s)Competencies Collaboration Electrical power design L3ELV cabling L3Electrical wiring L3Voltage drop calculation L3Electrical load diagrams / schedules and calculation L3Accountability Resilience Quality Leadership Creates Strategy - Developing Drives Performance - Developing Develops Future Leaders - Developing Education Profesional degree in MMUP Engineer Registration (UPDA)Bachelor\'s Degree in Electrical Engineering or any related field',NULL,'2023-10-23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UrbaCon Contracting & Trading Company',NULL),('Senior QA/QC Engineer','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Summary The Senior QA/QC Engineere Ensures that work / projects are delivered based on good work practices and project specifications to guarantee completion of work at the given time with quality of work that meets or even exceeds the client’s expectations by implementing international quality standards plans and quality procedures in all the construction activities. Job Responsibilities 1 Manages and oversees the quality and workmanship of every activity, thorough knowledge of all phases of engineering construction relating to Civil, Architectural and Structural discipline interfacing the multidisciplinary operations. Manages the QA/QC documents of the entire project including certificates, calibration, test results, inspection requests, non-compliance reports and site instruction/observations, permanent materials delivered and other QA/QC documents. Develops and determines all standards to perform inspection and tests on all procedures and oversee all testing methods and maintain high standards of quality for all processes. Follows the QA/QC Plans, Approved Method of Statements, Approved Test Plans and Approved Drawings during the project in order to meet the project quality requirements and client’s expectations. Ensures that all available Method Statements, ITPS and Drawings are approved and the last revision. Ensures that all approved Method statements, ITPs and Drawings are followed on sites. Ensures that all superseded documents are removed from the site. Prepares work inspection requests (WIR) for each construction activity and submits to consultant to ensure it covers all the construction activities done on site. Job Responsibilities 2 Ensures that all site items are inspected properly thoroughly before calling the consultant for inspection. Ensures that work inspections are carried out as per the plans and advises the construction team for the corrections/corrective actions to avoid the rejection of work. Ensures that all drawings used in the inspection are approved and last revision. Ensures that 90% of work inspections shall be passing during the first submission. Conducts the quality tool box and method statements briefing for all the activities. Ensures that method statements briefing is carried out for each and every activity and records are maintained in the monthly Quality report. Ensures all incoming materials are checked as per the project specifications and approved material submittals. Ensures that all materials are inspected internally before offering inspection to the consultant, and before using in site. Raising an NCR to the supplier in case of rejecting any material delivered to site. The record of inspection shall be recorded in the monthly Quality report. Additional Responsibilities 3 Job Knowledge & Skills • Knowledge of work related standards, specifications, and quality systems such as: ISO 9001, QCS, ASTM, BSI, BSEN, ACI and AASHTO. Have enough technical experience the QC issues. Ability to prioritize and multitasks as well as proactive and deadline-oriented. Ability to interact effectively in English. Ability to read drawings, specifications, standards , data sheets..etc. Proficient in computer applications and Systems such as Microsoft Office, Auto Cad, Primavera. Ability to supervise/execute whole sections of a Project with minimum management supervision.• ERP knowledge preferably SAP functional skills are a requirement to be successful in this role. Job Experience 10 years Total5 years On Job3 years GCCCompetencies Collaboration Accountability Resilience Quality Leadership Creates Strategy - Developing Drives Performance - Developing Develops Future Leaders - Developing Quality Assurance L3QA Reviews and Inspections L3Quality Control and Conformance L3Standard Operating Procedures L3QA Audits L3Education Bachelor\'s Degree in Civil Engineering or Engineering Professional Qualification in MMUP Engineer Registration (UPDA) or Lead Auditor certification (ISO 9001 or equal) or ASQC certification (CQM/CQE).',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UrbaCon Contracting & Trading Company',NULL),('Senior Technical & Design Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Summary Responsible for all designing/technical aspects of the company’s operations, inclusive of value engineering opportunities, construction and overall methodology, method statements, engineering design drawings, shop drawings and material submittals and follow up approval.  This position also  manages the preparation/verification of detailed constructional drawings,  negotiation and securing of technical and statutory approvals to achieve and monitor the optimum effectiveness. Job Responsibilities 1 Principal Accountabilities Provides supports implementation of all technical and engineering strategy and strategic operational goals to exceed customer expectations for product development, quality, cost and delivery, maximizing efficiency, optimizing and driving engineering excellence.\nManages the Technical and Engineering function and quality of service delivery, striving for best in class products and business practices to deliver to the customer’s expectations.\nEnsures to maintain a safe working environment within Company workplaces, and applying the Company Health & Safety Policy\nEssential Functions\n1. Management / Leadership\nLeads the team, manages key stakeholders relationships, resources, budget and team members to ensure the achievement of quality outcomes and reports. Manages the engineering team on the project site, provide directions, strategy, daily/weekly/monthly tasks and work plan for the team members.\nMaintains good relationship with all project key stakeholders and the engineering team member.\nSubmits weekly and monthly reports for the engineering deliverables.\nIncreases the efficiency of the technical team performance using smart approaches,\nEnsures the quality of deliverables with minimum budget for the staff.\nContributes in all important strategic decisions/ directions for project  \nJob Responsibilities 2 Strong practical experience with ability to prepare detailed method statement.\nAdvanced Knowledge in engineering principles, techniques, policies, and procedures\nExcellent knowledge of material engineering properties and local/global availability of materials\nExcellent technical skills and ability to organize and oversee preparation of technical drawings\nKnowledge of Project Management\nAdditional Responsibilities 3 Job Knowledge & Skills • Proven leadership and management skills with the ability to optimize team performance and development.• Strong and confident negotiator with the ability to negotiate at all levels• Excellent communication, interpersonal and influencing skills• Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities• Results orientated with ability to plan and deliver against project deadlines• Demonstrable experience of leading an engineering function with a proven track record in strategic engineering leadership delivering effective engineering strategies, policies, processes and systems• • ERP knowledge preferably SAP functional skills are a requirement to be successful in this role. Job Experience Total    12 year(s)  On Job      6 year(s) GCC     4 year(s)Competencies Collaboration Accountability Resilience Quality Leadership Creates Strategy - Proficient Drives Performance - Proficient Develops Future Leaders - Proficient QA/QC L4Geotechnical Engineering L4Drawings/Specifications L4Construction design Software L4Value Engineering L4Education Bachelor\'s Degree in Civil Engineering or Engineering Profesional degree in MMUP Engineer Registration (UPDA)',NULL,'2023-10-14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UrbaCon Contracting & Trading Company',NULL),('Senior Technical Engineer 2','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Summary The Senior Technical Engineer performs design management of various types of projects residential commercial, warehouse/industrial buildings. Reviews the structural design of projects. Initiates value engineering exercises and identifies potential issues/constraints in design and construction during the early stages of design. Checks appropriateness of structural system and correctness of design criteria proposed by consultants. Provides direction to consultants to ensure complete submission of structural deliverables within project schedule. Performs the task of managing the documentation of the structural drawings in coordination with architectural and MEP Works. Job Responsibilities 1 Reviews the design criteria (basic structural components, geotechnical properties, wind loads, seismic loads, loads, fire protection ….) and ensure adequacy of design. Analyzes the structural elements to ensure the quality of the design. Analyzes and reviews the loading plan and ensure compliance with codes and the project operational purpose. Determines the pressures that each component, such as a beam or lintel, will experience from other parts of the structure due to human use or environmental pressures such as weather or earthquakes. Studies the impact of the temporary works (formwork, tower cranes foundations and supports) on the structural elements, provide calculations, details and ensure compliance. Provides safe structural solutions to suite the architectural & MEP requirements. Prepares / contributes in preparation of the structural Shop DWG list. Reviews the IFC DWGs (Architectural, Structural and MEP) to ensure coordination with all disciplines. Job Responsibilities 2 Manages the structural draftsman in preparation of structural shop DWGs and ensure efficiency and quality. Liaises with the subcontractors to produce and deliver structural shop DWGs (by specialist) as per the time schedule. Reviews the produced shop DWGs (self performance and subcontractor SD) and ensure coordination with all disciplines, quality and accuracy. Ensures the accuracy of the BBS and other structural production schedules. Reviews the Formwork DWGs and ensure adequacy of design and review Formwork MOS and coordinate the requirements with the concrete works. Ensures to produce the General arrangement DWGs for all horizontal and vertical elements in coordination with the Architects and MEP engineers. Ensures that all submitted DWGs are signed by all discipline engineers (Architects, MEP, specialists). Submits coordinated structural shop DWGs, BBS, other technical submittals, structural calculation, geotechnical reports, material submittals on time as per the project time schedule. Additional Responsibilities 3 Job Knowledge & Skills • Knowledge of STAAD Software. Extensive structural knowledge for Buildings, Heavy Civils and Infrastructure works. Knowledge in preparing reports, designs and drawings. Good level of previous faÃ§ade engineering design experience including analysis of structures and detailed design of elements in all major materials. Knowledge of Project Management. Practical knowledge and ability in Structural Engineering design and construction. Working knowledge of Auto Cad or other drafting software Extensive experience of structural engineering building design on multi-disciplinary building envelope projects• ERP knowledge preferably SAP functional skills are a requirement to be successful in this role. Job Experience 9 years Total4 years On Job3 years GCCCompetencies Collaboration Accountability Resilience Quality Leadership Creates Strategy - Developing Drives Performance - Developing Develops Future Leaders - Developing Cost Management L3Drawings/Specifications L3QA/QC L3Geotechnical Engineering L3HSE L3Education Bachelor\'s Degree in Engineering or Civil Engineering',NULL,'2023-10-10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'UrbaCon Contracting & Trading Company',NULL),('Techn