are product. Write technical documentation.','Proven experience as a Full Stack Developer or similar role Experience developing desktop and mobile applications Familiarity with common stacks Knowledge of multiple front-end languages and libraries (e.g. HTML/ CSS, Java Script, XML, j Query)Knowledge of multiple back-end languages (e.g. C#, Java, Python) and Java Script frameworks (e.g. Angular, React, Node.js)Familiarity with databases (e.g. My SQL, Mongo DB), web servers (e.g. Apache), and UI/UX design Excellent communication and teamwork skills Great attention to detail Organizational skills An analytical mind Degree in Computer Science, Statistics or a relevant field Ability to develop and execute a technical vision focusing on business value.','2023-09-01',30,10,5,7,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'webSTDY',NULL),('Research Specialist Level 3','Qatar','Doha','','Position Summary Working under the direction of the Principal Investigator (PI) or more senior staff on sponsored research projects develops and performs complex standard laboratory procedures and also assists technical specialists in advanced research. Job Responsibilities Performs a variety of moderately complex cell/tissue assays, culture preparation and/or analyses; also prepares moderately complex stains solutions, media, buffers, solutions and reagents for non-standard prescribed tests. Operates, calibrates and performs routine maintenance on standard and specialized laboratory equipment. Manipulates, computes and analyzes data using complex statistical computer software. Prepares and maintains detailed records, logs and summary reports of procedures and results including graphs, scientific calculations and statistical analysis charting Responsible for Quality Control and Assurance of samples, reagents, and data. Ensures laboratory compliance to all guidelines and standards of WCM-NY and WCM-Q. Cleans and maintains laboratory hygiene, disposes of laboratory waste. Orders laboratory supplies, maintains laboratory equipment and related records, expenditures, including inventory control and material receipt. Develops and documents methods to improve processes in the laboratory. Assists in the review and development of new laboratory standard operating procedures. Cross trains on equipment, coordinates vacations, etc with other team members to ensure smooth lab flow. Performs other job related duties as required.','Skills\nEducation Bachelor\'s Degree Experience Three or more years prior experience working in a research or similar laboratory Knowledge, Skills and Abilities Previously exhibited individual initiative Previously demonstrated advanced proficiency in written and spoken English Previously demonstrated ability to communicate in both scientific written reports and professional presentations.','2023-10-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Weill Cornell Medicine-Qatar',NULL),('Great Schedule for an Active & Fun-loving Nanny','Egypt','Alexandria','','Location Chevy Chase Education Requirements No Education requirement Experience Requirements 4+ years Description This wonderful and active family in Chevy Chase is looking for enthusiastic, social, and engaging nanny to help keep their joyful home running smoothly. They have 4 children, ages 8 (twins), 6, and 2 ½ years old. The youngest will be in preschool until 12pm, and the older kids until 3pm. Key responsibilities include kids’ laundry, meal prep, and errands before walking to pick up the 2.5 year-old from school. When the 3 older kids get home there may be homework supervision and driving to and from activities until your end time (4:30 pm!). The kids’ schools are all walking distance from the home and a car will be provided for any activities you need to drive to. This is a wonderful role for someone playful and proactive, who likes to get the kiddos out of the house. If you enjoy being around kids, and value an active and nurturing environment, we’d love to hear from you!Qualifications⭐️ At least 5 years of professional nannying experience⁣ ⭐️ Must be legal to work in the US ⭐️ Must be local to the DC-metro area (DC, MD, VA) ⭐️ Licensed driver with a clean driving record & car⁣ ⭐️ Must be COVID-Vaccinated & Boosted if eligible Why Work With Us Free for Job Seekers Highest Paying Jobs Benefits Ongoing Training & Support* Community',NULL,'2023-10-16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'White House Nannies, Inc.',NULL),('Ideal Hours for Nanny Job w/ 1 Baby','Egypt','Alexandria','','Location Alexandria Education Requirements No Education requirement Experience Requirements 4+ years Description Responsibilities include attending to the baby\'s needs, including feeding, diaper changes, and nap time, preparing nutritious foods and snacks for baby, keeping the baby\'s laundry clean and organized, maintaining the baby\'s room and play area in a clean and organized state, running errands, and driving the kid as needed. Ability to teach a second language to the baby would be great for this role. Great Pay + Paid time off + Competitive Benefits Qualifications⭐️ At least 5 years of professional nannying experience⁣ ⭐️ Must be legal to work in the US ⭐️ Must be local to the DC-metro area (DC, MD, VA) ⭐️ Experience and knowledge around developmental milestones⁣ ⭐️ Licensed driver with a clean driving record & car⁣ ⭐️ Must be COVID-Vaccinated & Boosted if eligible Why Work With Us Free for Job Seekers Highest Paying Jobs Benefits Ongoing Training & Support* Community',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'White House Nannies, Inc.',NULL),('Technical Support Engineer','Egypt','Cairo','','Technical Support Engineer’s primary focus will be ensuring that all customers are very satisfied with the effectiveness and efficiency of the support they receive. Utilizing knowledge of the customer environment, the will deliver timely and high-quality incident resolution focusing on root cause analysis, prevention, and knowledge transfer. They will effectively manage cases and sub-cases to ensure timely and high-quality communication with customers and resolution of all issues. They will develop a relationship with their technical peers for the technology they support and related technologies to ensure improved collaboration and satisfaction in support. Responsibilities Applying strong verbal and written communication skills in the supported language, and solid technical knowledge of supported customer products, to represent and communicate with end user through telephone, email and web response, carrying out the following activities as needed:• Represent and communicate with customer end users• Manage relationships with multiple customers, partners and collaborate with business contacts within customer organization• Use standard processes, implement existing diagnosis methods, solutions/workarounds to effectively deal with customer and technical issues to achieve problem resolution and customer satisfaction• Document incidents, report end user suggestions and technical issues to customer• Respond to voice of end user, utilize internal escalations and meet response, resolution, efficiency, productivity and utilization targets required by customer• Communicate and collaborate with cross-group peers and customer resources both proactively and reactively in order to identify and leverage the right resources to arrive at solutions to tough and hot problems• Produce quality documentation and share with the appropriate team members and tech lead as appropriate• Compliance with the service operation processes for execution excellence• Adherence to the customer Business Code of Conduct in all end user interactions and interactions with customer, and• Strict adherence to data privacy guidelines – never putting end user PII at risk','Preferred Competencies:• Windows Operation System administration and programming.  OR• Active Directory Deployment and AD/Networking Management.  OR• Exchange Online/On Prem, Outlook or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• Share Point Online/On Prem or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• Teams or industry similar products and technologies. OR• Office or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• Security, or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• SQL Server or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• Azure, or industry similar products and technologies.  OR• Networking, e.g. TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP and RPC.  OR• Scripting languages, e.g. Power Shell, batch script Preferred Certifications if applicable:• Industry acknowledged certificates, e.g. MCP, MCSE, MCSD, MCDBA, CCNA etc.','2023-10-24',2,0,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Wicresoft',NULL),('Technical Support Engineer-Freelancer','Egypt','Cairo','','Job Summary: Get ready to revolutionize customer support! We are thrilled to announce our project: the Microsoft Forum Program. You need to deliver support and elevate the user experience on the Microsoft Forum platform. Our objective is clear: to provide personalized and efficient assistance to our valued Microsoft product users. Please ensure prompt and accurate resolutions to their queries and issues. Responsibility: Work on Microsoft Answers Forum to reply on M365 related threads: Monitor and respond to user inquiries promptly. Troubleshoot and resolve user-reported issues. Provide expert advice and recommendations. Share knowledge and contribute to discussions. Stay updated with Microsoft products and technologies. Adhere to guidelines, policies, and maintain professionalism. What you can Gain: But it doesn\'t stop there. Our vision extends beyond efficient support. We want to foster a vibrant and engaged community on the Microsoft Forum. By facilitating collaboration between our support team, and users, we create an environment where knowledge is freely shared, empowering users to help one another. Together, we will build a supportive and active community, where every user feels valued and connected. At the same time, you can gain the following when doing this job: Fair compensation for your contributions. Opportunities for professional development and skill enhancement. Valuable experience to add to portfolio. Recognition and visibility among users and organization. Access to continuous learning resources. Personal and professional growth opportunities.','Good English writing and Speaking skills. Microsoft M365 products knowledge (Prefer M365 products, Exchange, Share Point Server)Good Communication skills. Customer Support experience is preferred.','2023-11-01',7,0,2,10,3000,13000,0,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Wicresoft',NULL),('Technical Support Specialist','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','\nInstall and configure computer systems.\nDiagnose hardware/software faults and solve technical problems, printers issues.\nProvide Technical support for all staff and students.\nInstall Operating Systems and applications of all kinds.\nBackup data from PCs when required.\nNetwork implementation, documentation, simulation, testing and troubleshooting.\n','Minimum 1 year of previous experience in Technical Support/Help Desk. Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or Management Information Systems is a must. Excellent knowledge of VLANs, DTP, and Inter-Vlan routing is a must. Preferable Certificates: (MCSE or CCNA or ICDL or A+ and N+)Familiar with Microsoft operating systems (XP, 7, 8, 8.1, and 10) and Microsoft office.','2023-09-01',61,8,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Windrose Academy',NULL),('Graduate Process Engineer-UAE National','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Overview / Responsibilities Wood is currently recruiting for a Graduate Process Engineer to be based in Dubai, UAEThe successful candidate should be able to peform the below duties and responsibilities;Process Design & Detail Engineering including performing process simulations, design calculations, sizing & selection of equipment etc. for Projects. \nPreparation of various engineering deliverables (Drawings & Documents) such as Process Flow Diagrams, P & I Diagrams, Process Datasheets, Cause & Effect Diagrams, Philosophies, HAZOP Studies & reports, etc. and providing necessary engineering inputs to the other disciplines.\nAssigning responsibilities to Draftsmen, and monitoring to meet the project schedule.\n Skills / Qualifications B. E. / B. Tech. / B. S. – Chemical Engineering.\nSpecialization in Petroleum / Petro Chemical Engineering preferred.\nHands on experience in software such as HYSYS, PIPELINESTUDIO.\n\nCompany Overview\nWood is a global leader in consulting and engineering, helping to unlock solutions to critical challenges in energy and materials markets. We provide consulting, projects and operations solutions in 60 countries, employing around 35,000 people. www.woodplc.com\nDiversity Statement\nWe are an equal opportunity employer that recognises the value of a diverse workforce. All suitably qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment on the basis of objective criteria and without regard to the following (which is a non-exhaustive list): race, colour, age, religion, gender, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, protected veteran status, or other characteristics in accordance with the relevant governing laws.',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Wood',NULL),('Lead Piping Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Overview / Responsibilities\nWood is curently looking for a Lead Piping Engineer to be based in Abu Dhabi for pemanent position. The successful candidate will be responsible for the following; Administratively and technically manages all piping personnel under his responsibility.\nResponsible for Proposals Manhours estimation and optimization, CTR inputs, Execution Methodology\nEnsuring Efficient and effective production of project deliverables within the stipulated schedule, budget and delivered to the client.\nProvide skills, integrity, and knowledge in key areas of discipline engineering, including design codes, legislative/Client Specification requirements and current good engineering practices.\nEffectively manage design changes and provide appropriate solutions as and when needed during the Project execution.\nUnderstands clients ’needs, identifies, and addresses design parameters and problems, and develops and implements solutions.\nEnsure recognized onshore engineering practices applicable to piping design and topside/plant layouts are adopted.\nResponsible for the production/review of Piping deliverables such as Study Reports, Design Calculations, Stress Analysis Reports, PMS and Piping Material/Fabrication Specifications/Procedures, Material Requisitions and Technical Bid Evaluations\nResponsible for the review of Piping drawings including 3D Models, Drawings(Layouts, Plot Plans, GADs, Isometrics) and Piping MTOs\nResponsible for conducting Plot Plans, Safety Layouts, and 3D Model Reviews as per the Project requirements.\nParticipates during key project reviews, plot plan reviews, Hazop / SIL reviews, constructability reviews and Design/model review meetings.\nShall be able to work independently/with minimum guidance, and coordinate well with the piping materials, Stress and Layout engineers/designers besides other disciplines.\nPerforms Inter-discipline & discipline QA/QC and engineering compliance checks on all work performed by themselves or junior engineers within the group.\nAdherence to company processes and procedures\nManage discipline-related activities and work share with other work centers.\nAssists the Engineering Manager and the Project Engineers with technical coordination of interfaces and identification of potential deviations or discrepancies. As part of his role, the Candidate should have good knowledge on the below items.\nApplication of Piping Codes including ASME B31.3/B31.1, BS EN 13480.\nApplication and selection of Piping Materials\nApplication of Material and Piping Component Codes ASTM, API, BS, MSS SP\nExposure to Piping Layouts and review of piping deliverables such as Piping Plots, Piping Nozzle orientation Drawings, General Arrangement Drawings, Isometrics and material lists.\nWall thickness calculations.\nPipe stress and Flexibility analysis calculation.\nDesign/specification of pipe supports.\n\n\nSkills / Qualifications\nQualifications: Degree in Mechanical Engineering\n15+ years of experience in \nOil and Gas Projects working with Major Consultancy Companies and minimum 5 years’ experience in the lead role\nDifferent Stages of Projects(Concept, FEED and Detailed Design) of large-sized Onshore projects\nPiping Engineering(Layout Design, Piping Materials and Stress Engineering) of Onshore Processing/Refinery Plants\nLed and supervised a team of Piping Engineers and Designers \nHands-on experience in Piping Software’s -3D Design Software (AVEVA, Smart Plant, etc.) and CAESAR II/Auto Pipe Stress Analysis software.\nGood interpersonal skills and excellent command in English\nCommunicate clearly and professionally both verbally and in writing with superiors, colleagues, and individuals outside of the Company.\n\nCompany Overview\nWood is a global leader in consulting and engineering, helping to unlock solutions to critical challenges in energy and materials markets. We provide consulting, projects and operations solutions in 60 countries, employing around 35,000 people. www.woodplc.com\nDiversity Statement\nWe are an equal opportunity employer that recognises the value of a diverse workforce. All suitably qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment on the basis of objective criteria and without regard to the following (which is a non-exhaustive list): race, colour, age, religion, gender, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, protected veteran status, or other characteristics in accordance with the relevant governing laws.',NULL,